After Yesu was born in Betliem in Judia, when Erod was the ruling man(king), wise men came from the east to Jerusalem. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
When they arrived there, they started asking to the people, "Where is the child which was born who will be the ruling man(king) of Ju people? We saw his star from the east, and we came to worship him.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
When the ruling man(king) Erod heard this, he was upset and all Jerusalem people like that. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
He gathered all the head sacrifice burning people(chief priests) and the teaching men of the law, asked them, "Where will Keriso be born?" {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
They answered him, "In Betliem in Judia, [for] this is what the God's man who make know(prophet) has written:
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
But you.s, Betliem, in the land of Judia,
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 you.s are not small city,
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 because from you.s a leading man will come
