\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
Then Erod called the wise men secretly to know which day the star had appeared. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
He sent them to Betliem and said to them, "Go and search carefully where the child is. When you.p find him, let me know so that I may also go to worship him.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
After hearing the ruling man(king), they went, this star which they had seen from east went ahead of them until it stopped over that place where the child was. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
When they saw that star, they were very happy. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
They went into the house, they saw the child with his mother Meri and they bowed down and worshiped him. Then they took out [gifts] from bag and gave expensive gifts him-gold, liquid with good smelling(perfume) and good smelling medicine. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
With a dream God made them know not to go back to Erod, but they went back to their country by another road.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Josef and his family went to Ijif
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
When they went, a man carrying heavenly message(angel) of the Lord arrived to Josef in a dream. He said, "Get up, take the child and his mother go to Ijif. Stay there until I tell you.s, because Erod will come to search for the child to kill him."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
So he got up, took the child with his mother in the night and they went to Ijif, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
there they stayed until Erod died. It became true for what the Lord said through the God's man who make know(prophet): "From Ijif I called my son."{\super b{\footnote \pard\plain \s212\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28  {\super b}{{\cs214\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 2.15 }
{\cs215\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Osiya 11:1}
}}}

\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
When Erod realized that the wise men had tricked him, he was very angry, so he ordered soldiers to kill all the boys in Betliem and in other close villages young boys who were two years old and under that. He did that, they know through wise men which day when the star had appeared. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
Then what the God's man who make know(prophet) Jeramaya had said became true,
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
"They heard a sound in the village of Rama,
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 weeping,
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Woman descended from Resel are crying for their children;
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 they refuse to be comforted,
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 because their children have died."
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Josef and his family return to Najaret
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
After Erod died, a man carrying heavenly message(angel) of the Lord appeared with a dream to Josef in Ijif, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
and said, "Get up, take the child and his mother [and you.p] go to the land of Israil, because who tried to kill the child have died."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
So he got up, take the child and his mother [and they] went to the land of Israil. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
