In those days Jon the Baptist came, preaching in the desert of Judia, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
and said this talk, "Turn away from your.p sins, because the kingdom of the heaven is near." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
This is he who was spoken of through the God's man who make know(prophet) Aisaya,
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 "A man is shouting in the desert,
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 'Prepare the way for the Lord;
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 make straight road for him.'"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
Jon wore clothes of camel's hair with belt by animal skin, and he ate locusts and honey. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
People went to him from Jerusalem and all Judia and the whole region of the Joden. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
They were confessing their sins, he baptized them in the Joden river.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
When he saw many Farasi men and Saduki men coming to be baptized by Jon, he said to them, "You life of snakes! Don't expect to flee from Lord's anger. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
Do those things to show that you.p have turned from your.p sins. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
Don't think that you.p can run away from punishment by this talk, 'Ebraam is our ancester.' I tell you.p that God is able to raise up children from these stones for Ebraam. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
The ax is lying at the root of the tree, and every tree that are without.fruit will cut down and throw into the fire.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
I baptize you.p with water to show that you.p turned away from sin, but who comes after me his power will surpass me. I am imposssible to carry his sandol. He will baptise you.p with the God Spirit and fire. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
His winnowing fork is his hand. He uses this fork to throw the wheat up for wind to blow to seperate seeds from their chaffs and he gathers seeds into the house to put into and burn the chaff without.ending fire."
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Jon baptized Yesu
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
Then Yesu came from Galili region to Jon in the Joden river to be baptized. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
But Jon tried to say to him, "You.s batptizing me would be straight. Why [do] you.s come to me?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
Yesu answered him, "It should be done now. In this way we do all God's will." Then Jon agreed.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
When Jon baptized Yesu, not.long he went out of water, at once heaven was open and he saw the God Spirit descending like a mamu(dove) [and] set on his body. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
And a talk came from heaven, "This is my son who I love him, I am very happy to him."
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 4
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The story of Yesu's temptation
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
Then the God Spirit led Yesu to the desert in order that S\u225?if\u232?r tempted him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
