\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu talked them about fasting
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
\u8220?When you.p fast, do not put on a sad face as the hypocrites do, because they make their faces appear sad in order that people will see that they are abstaining from food. I tell you.p the truth, they have received their own reward in full. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
But when you.p fast, put oil on [your.p] head and wash [your.p] face. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
Do this so that people will not know that you.p are fasting, but only to your.p Father who is unseen; your.p Father who sees this action in secret will reward you.p.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu talked about treasures there in Heaven
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
Do not gather treasures for yourselves on this earth, where termites and rust destroy, and where thieves come to steal. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
But gather treasures for yourselves into heaven, where termites and rust do not destroy, and where thieves do not come to steal. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
Then where your.p treasure is, there your.p heart will be also.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
The eye is the lamp of the body. If your.p eyes are good, your.p whole body will be full of light. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
But if your.p eyes are bad, your.p whole body will be full of darkness. If the light within you.p has become dark, you.p will be big darkness is!
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
You cannot obey two lords. Either you.p will hate the one and love the other, or you.p will obey to the one and deny the other. You.p cannot work for two lords God and money.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu told them not to worry
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
\u8220?Therefore I tell you.p, do not worry about how to live, what you.p will eat food and water; or also about your.p body, what you.p will wear. Life is very important but food is little, and the body is very important, but clothes are little. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
Look at the birds; they do not do in sowing or reaping or storing, but your.p heavenly Father feeds them. You people are very important in God's eyes and surpass the birds. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
Through worrying you can't make your life long.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
Why do you.p worry about clothes? See how the flowers of the bush grow. They do not make clothes for themselves. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
But I tell you.p that Solomon in all his wealth dressed is not looking as they are. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
That is how God clothes the grass of the bush, which is here today and tomorrow is thrown into the fire. God will clothe you very much. You.p of little big mind(faith)! {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
So do not worry, saying, \u8216?What shall we eat?\u8217? or \u8216?What shall we drink?\u8217? or \u8216?What shall we wear?\u8217? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
Because the Outside people(Gentiles) follow these desires, then your.p heavenly Father knows that you.p need them. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
But seek first God's kingdom and his straight way, and so all these things will be given to you.p as well. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
Therefore do not think about tomorrow, because tomorrow will bring its own worries. Today's trouble is enough for today.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 7
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
"Do not put other people into court/judge, so that God will not put us in court/judge, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
because God will put you into court/judge in the same way you put others into court/judge, and he will do you the same rules you put others into court/judge.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
"Why do you.s see your.p friend's eye booger but you don't see a log in your.s eye? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
How will you.s say to your.s friend, \u8216?Let me take out your.s eye booger,\u8217? when you.s have a log in your.s own eye? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
You.s hypocrite! First take the log out of your.s own eye, then you can see clearly and you.s can take out your.s friend\u700?s eye booger.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
"Do not give dogs what is without.dust(holy) and do not throw your.p pearls to pigs. If you.p do, they will trample that things by their hands and will turn and tear you.p to pieces.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Ask, search, knock
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
"Ask to the Lord, and he will give it to you.p; search, and you.p will find; knock, and the door will be opened to you.p. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
Because all the people who ask will receive, the one who seeks will find, and he who knocks, the door will be opened.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
If your.p son ask for bread, will you give him a stone? No. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
If he asks for a fish, will you give him a biting snake? No. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
You, who are evil, know how do you.p give good gifts to your.p children. So your Father God in heaven surely will give good gifts to those who ask him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
Therefore in everything, do to other people what you.p like other people will do to you.p. This is the basis of what the law of Moses and the people who make know God's knowledge(prophets)'s book teach us.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The narrow and wide doors
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
"(You.p)Enter through the narrow door. Because the door is wide and the road which puts easily to the fire(hell), and many people enter through it. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
But the door is small and the road that leads to true life are difficult and only few people find that road.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 A tree and its fruit
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
"Watch out for false God's people who make know(prophets). They come to you.p with sheep\u700?s clothing, but inside they are dangerous wild dogs. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
You.p will recognize them by their fruit. Do people pick y\u233?ro from thorns, or mangoes from small bush trees? No {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
Every good tree bears good fruits, but a bad tree bears bad fruits. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
A good tree cannot bear bad fruits, and a bad tree cannot bear good fruits. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
Every tree if does not bear good fruits is cut down and thrown into the fire. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
So, you will know the false God's people who make know(prophets) in their action."
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 True disciples and false disciples
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
"Everyone who says to me that, \u8216?My Lord, my Lord,\u8217? will not enter the kingdom of heaven, but only the one who does my Father's will who is in heaven. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
Many people will say to me on the day of jundgment, \u8216?My Lord, my Lord, in your.s name we were saying God's talk and in your.s name were casting evil spirits and performing surprising things(miracles)?\u8217? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
Then I will tell them, \u8216?I don't knew who you.p are. Get away from me, you.p evildoers!\u8217?
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The wise and foolish house builders
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
"Therefore, the people who hear these talks of mine and follow them.p are like a wise man who built a house on the stone. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
The rain started falling, the river started flooded over, and the winds blew and beat against that house; but that house did not fall down. Because its house post had stand on the stone. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
But the people who hear these talk of mine but don't follow them.p are like a foolish man who built house on sand. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
The rain started falling, the river started flooded over, and the winds blew and beat against the house, and that house fell down completely."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
When Yesu had finished talk about two house builders, the crowds were surprised at his teaching, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
because he taught with authority, not as their teaching men of the law.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 8
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Man with bad skin
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
When Yesu came down from the mountain, large crowds followed him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
A man with skin disease came suddenly to him and knelt down before him and said, \u8220?Lord, if you.s want to, you.s can make me good in God's eyes.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
Yesu reached out his hand and touched the man. He said, \u8220?I want to do, become good!\u8221? At once he found healing from his skin disease. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
Then Yesu said to him, \u8220?Don't tell anyone about it, but go, show to burning sacrifice men that you.s became good and prepare the gift according to what Moses's talk [said] for them to know.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Faith of Roman soldier's head man
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
When Yesu entered Kafenam town, a Roman soldier's head man came to him and asked him for help: {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
He said, \u8220?Lord, my without.payment working man(servant) is lying at home parayzed and in big suffering.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
Yesu said to him, \u8220?I will go and make him well.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
The Roman soldier's head man answered him, \u8220?Lord, I am not good to have you.p come into my house. But just say talk, then my without.payment worker will become good. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
Because I myself am a man under the power/authority, with soldiers who are under me. I say to him, \u8216?Go!\u8217? then he goes; and I say to him, \u8216?Come!\u8217? then he comes. If I say my without.payment working man, \u8216?Do this!\u8217? then he does it.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
When Yesu heard this, he was surprised and said to them who were following him, \u8220?I tell you.p truth, I didn't see any in Israil with big mind(faith) man like this man. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
I say to you.p that many people will come from the east and the west, and will take their places at the feast with Ebraam, Aisek, and Jeikof in the kingdom of heaven. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
But Ju people who should be in the kingdom they will be thrown out into the outside, into the darkness, where they will be crying and grinding their teeth.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
Then Yesu said to the Roman soldier's head man, \u8220?Go! Let it be done how you.p truly approve(believe) it be happen.\u8221? Then his without.payment working man became good at that moment.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu make good many people
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
When Yesu entered Fit\u232?'s house, he saw Fit\u232?'s mother-in-law was lying in sleeping place with a hot body disease. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
Yesu touched her hand; and body hot disease left her. And she got up and shared food for Yesu.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
When it was getting dark, people brought to Yesu who evil spirit leads, and he cast out the evil spirits with a talk and healed all the sick people. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
This thing came true for what the God's man who make know(prophet) Aisaya had said:
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 \u8220?He had healed our pain
