The Son of Man came eating and drinking, and they said, \u8216?Here eats too much food and drinks too much alcohol; he is a friend of tax collectors and sinners.' But God's wisdom is shown in its deeds.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Woe without.repentant towns
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
Then Yesu began to rebuke those towns where he had been performed many miracles in these regions, because they did not turn away from sin. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
\u8220?Woe to you.s Korasin! Woe to you.s, Betsaida! I did miracles among you.p, but you.p did not repent from sin. If I had done the same miralces I did among you.p among Taire and Sidon, they would have turn away from their sin long time ago by putting on sackcloth and by sprinkling ashes. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
But I tell you.p, later on the day of judgment, the punishments Taire and Sidon will carry will be big, but the punishments you.p will receive will surpass theirs. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
And you.s, Kafenam, will you.s be lift to the heaven? No! You.s will go down to hell! If I had done the same miracles I did among you.s in Sodom, that would still be in existence today! {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
But I tell you.p, later on the day of judgment, the punishments Sodom will carry will be big, but the punishments you.p will receive will surpass theirs.\u8221?
