\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 A tree and its fruit
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
\u8220?If a tree is good, it will produce good fruit, and if a tree is bad, it will produce bad fruit. Men look at a tree's fruit and know whether that tree is good or bad. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
You.p snakes, you.p sinner. How can you.p say good talk? The mouth speaks what the heart is full of. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 35\~}
A good man produces good things from good heart, a bad man produces evil things from evil heart.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 36\~}
"I tell you.p this, on the judgment day everyone will report why they speak all meaningless talks. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 37\~}
God will judge you by your words, call you.p straight or put the judgment.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 They asked Yesu to do a showing thing(sign)
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 38\~}
Some teaching men of the law and some Farasi men said to him, \u8220?Teaching man, we want to see you.s do a showing thing(sign) for us.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 39\~}
Yesu said, \u8220?How evil and godless are the people of this day! You.p ask me for doing a showing thing(sign)? No! The only his showing thing(sign) I will give you the God's man who make know(prophet) Jona. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 40\~}
Jona spent three days and nights in the belly of a big fish, the Son of Man will also spend three days and nights in the grave. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 41\~}
At the judgment the people of Nin\u233?fa will stand up with this generation and accuse them, because they turned away from the sin in the preaching of Jona; I tell you.p that there is someone here big, Jona is not like! You also should repent from the sin. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 42\~}
At the Judgment the Queen of Sefa will stand up with this generation and accuse them, because she came from far away her country to listen to King Solomon's wisdom; I tell you.p that there is someone here big, Solomon is not like!
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 An evil spirit returned
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 43\~}
When an evil spirit goes out of a person, it goes into desert looking for a place to rest. If it can't find place, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 44\~}
it says to itself, \u8216?I will go back to my house.\u8217? So it goes back and finds the house empty, clean and be ready. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 45\~}
Then evil spirit goes out and brings along 7 other evil spirits who are very big evil surpassed its own, [and] then they enter in and live there. After this person's life is very bad from first how he was. This is what will happen to this evil generation.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu' mother and younger brothers
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 46\~}
Yesu was still talking to the people when his mother and younger brothers arrived. They stood outside, asking to speak with him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 47\~}
Someone told him, \u8220?Look, your.s mother and younger brothers are standing outside, and they want to speak with you.s\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 48\~}
Yesu replied to him, \u8220?Who is my mother? Who are my younger brothers?\u8221? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 49\~}
Then he pointed to his following men and said, \u8220?Look! They are my mother and my younger brothers! {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 50\~}
Whoever does my Father's will in heaven is my younger brother and my sister and my mother.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 13
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The Parable of the garden man(farmer)
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
On that same day Yesu left the house and went and sat next to the lake to teach. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
Many crowd gathered and surrounded Yesu. In this reason Yesu went and got into a bout and he sat there and the people stood on the shore. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
He told to the people many things in parables.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 \u8220?There was a man who went out to sow seed. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
When he scattered the seed, some fell along the path, and the birds came and ate them. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
Some fell on stony ground, where there was little ground. The seeds start to grow up quickly, because the ground wasn't deep. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
But when the sun power caught them, the trees(plants) started wilting; and they died because the roots had not grown deep enough. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
Some of the seed fell among thorns, which grasses grew up and thorns choked them. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
Some seeds fell in good ground, and [the plants] bore seed: some one hundred [grains], others sixty, and others thirty. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
Whoever has ears to hear, he must hear it.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
His following men came to Yesu and asked him, \u8220?Why do you.p speak to the people with parables?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
Yesu answered to them, \u8220?The secret knowledge about the kingdom of heaven I told you.p, but not them. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
If someone has the knowledge, God will give many knowldges. But if someone does not have the the knowledge, God will take away form him whatever little he has. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
In this reason I speak to them with parables:
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Even they look, but do not see,
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 and even they listen, but do not hear or understand.
\par\pard\plain \s61\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
"So the making known talk(prophecy) of Aisaya became true about them,
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 \u8216?You will always listen, but not become knowledge;
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 you.p will always look, but you will not understand.
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
Because these people's heart are hard,
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 and their ears can't hear well
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 and they have closed [their] eyes.
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Their eyes will not see,
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 their ears will not hear,
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 and their hearts will not become knowledge(understand),
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 and they will not turn to me,
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 and I will not make good them.\u8217?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
"But your.p eyes are blessed because they see, and your.p ears are also blessed because they hear. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
I truly tell you.p, many God's people who make know(prophets) and straight people strongly wanted to see what you.p see, but could not, and to hear what you.p hear, but did not hear.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
Listen to what is the meaning of the parable of the garden man: {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
When anyone hears the talk about the kingdom of heaven and does not become knowledge(understand) it, the evil one comes and takes away what sown in his heart. These are seeds which fell along the road. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
The seeds which fell on stony ground, these people are who hears the talk and receives it with joy. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
But because their root hasn't, and their life is not long. When trouble or persecution comes because of the talk, they fall quickly. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
The seeds which fell among thorn places, these people stand for/describe who hear the talk; but seeking this world are full and seeking for money and for materials are full. By which talk became wick and unfruitful. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
But the seeds which fell on the good ground, he hears the word and gets the meaning of the talk. Those kind of men bear [fruit] one hundred, others sixty, and others thirty.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The parable of the bad grasses
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
Yesu told them another parable: \u8220?The kingdom of heaven is like a man sowed good seed in his field. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
One night, when every people was asleep, his enemy came and planted bad seeds among the good seeds and left. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
When the good seeds started growing and the heads of grain began to form, and then bad seeds also grew.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
"The owner's without.payment working men(servants) came to him and said, \u8216?Bigman, you.p sow good seed in your.s field. Where did bad grasses come from?\u8217?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
"He replied to them, \u8216?An enemy did this.\u8217?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The without.payment working men(servants) asked him, \u8216?Do you.p want us to go and pull up the bad grasses?\u8217?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
"He answered them, \u8216?No, because when you.p gather the bad grasses you.p might pull up some of good seeds along with them. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
Let them grow together until harvest. At that time I will tell the harvesting people: First collect the bad grasses and tie them in bundles for burning them, and then to gather in the good seeds and put it in my store house.\u8217?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The parable of the small seed and the dust for flaw\u233?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
Yesu told them another parable: \u8220?The kingdom of heaven is like small seed, a man takes a small seed and sows it in his field. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
Though it is the small seeds, but when it grows up, it became the very big plants and becomes a tree, put branches where birds make the nests in.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
Yesu told them another parable, \u8220?The kingdom of heaven is like a dust for flaw\u233?. A woman takes some yeast and mixes it with a big bag of flour until the flour become big.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
Yesu spoke all these things to the crowds only in parables; he would not say a thing to them without using a parable. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 35\~}
It was fulfilled for what the God's man who make know(prophet) had said:
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 \u8220?I will open my mouth for parables,
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 I will tell them hidden things since the creation of the world.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Explaining the parable of the bad grasses
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 36\~}
Then Yesu left the crowd and went into the house. His following men came to him and said, \u8220?Explain us the meaning of the parable about the bad grasses in the field.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 37\~}
He answered to them, \u8220?The man who sowed the good seed is the Son of Man. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 38\~}
The field is the world and the good seed is the people who belong to the heavenly kingdom; the bad grasses are the people who belong to the Evil One; {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 39\~}
this enemy who sowed the bad grasses is the S\u225?if\u232?r. This harvest is the harvesting of the end of earth, and the harvest working people(servants) are men carrying heavenly message(angels). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 40\~}
Just as the bad grasses are gathered up and burned in the fire, so the same thing will happen at the end of the age. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 41\~}
The Son of Man will send out his men carrying heavenly message(angels) and they will take out from his kingdom all those who cause people to sin and all other people who do evil things. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 42\~}
They will throw them into the unstopped fire, there they will cry and grind their teeth. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 43\~}
Then straight men will shine like the sun in their Father's kingdom. Whoever has ears, they must hear this talk.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The parable of the hidden treasure and the pearl
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 44\~}
\u8220?The heavenly kingdom is like hidden treasure in the ground. When he found it, he hid it again, and then in his joy he went and sold everything he had, and bought that ground.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 45\~}
Also Yesu said the heavenly kingdom is like. A merchant was going around looking for high payment pearls. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 46\~}
When he found very expensive pearl, he went away and sold everything he had, and bought that pearl.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The parable of the net
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 47\~}
Also, the heavenly kingdom is like a net that was let down in the lake and caught all kinds of fish. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 48\~}
When the net is full, fish catching men pull it with fish to shore. Then they sat down to collected the good fish in baskets, but threw the bad away. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 49\~}
In the same way it will be at the end of the world: the men carrying heavenly message(angels) will go out to seperate the evil people from among the straight people {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 50\~}
and will throw the evil into the stopless fire, there they will cry and grind the teeth."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 51\~}
Yesu asked them, \u8220?Do you.p become knowledge(understand) these all things?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 They answered him, "Yes."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 52\~}
He said to them, \u8220?This talk's meaning is that every teaching man of the law who becomes a following man in the heavenly kingdom is like a owner of a house who takes out new things and old things from the storage house."
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 They rejected Yesu at Najaret
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 53\~}
When Yesu finished [telling] these parables, he moved from there {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 54\~}
and he came to his hometown, and then started teaching in the meeting house, and they heard and were amazed and they asked themselves, \u8220?Where did this man get such wisdom and these miraculous power? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 55\~}
He is the house building man's son. Meri is his mother, and his younger brothers are Jems, Josef, Saimon, and Judas. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 56\~}
All his sisters are living with us. Where did this man get all this power?\u8221? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 57\~}
Then they rejected him.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu said to them, \u8220?A God's man who make know(prophet) is respected everywhere but isn't in his own town and his own family.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 58\~}
Yesu did not do many surprising things(miracles) there because they have no their big mind(faith).
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 14
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The death of Jon the baptist
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
At that time Erod, the ruling man(king) of Galili region, heard about Yesu, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
and Erod said to his work people, \u8220?This is really Jon the Baptist risen from death to life, and that's why he has this power to perform surprising things(miracles).\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
When Jon was still alive, Erod told them Jon's arrest, and tied him and put in darkness house. He did this in order to make his wife Erodias happy. Before Erod married her, she was before his younger brother Filif's wife. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
Previously Jon had been telling Erod, \u8220?It isn't straight for you.s to be married to your.s younger brother's wife.\u8221? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
Erod wanted to kill Jon, but he was afraid of the Ju people, because they really thought Jon to be a God's man who make know(prophet).
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
On Erod's birthday feast, the daughter of Erodias danced in front of the guestsand Erod, and this made Erod happy. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
Erod strong promised to her, \u8220?Ask me for what you want, I will give you.s!\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
At her mother's talk she asked him, \u8220?Give me now the head of Jon the Baptist on a plate!\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
The ruling man(king) felt very sad, but because of the strong without.lying talk(promise) he said in front of all his guests, he commanded her wish to do. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
So he sent solidiers to cut Jon the baptist's head into darkness house. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
They brought his head on a plate and he gave it to the girl. She took it to her mother. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
Jon's following men came and carried his body and buried it. Then they went and told Yesu.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu feeds 5,000 men
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
When Yesu heard what happened, he went to a quiet place to be alone with a bout. The people heard about this, so they left their towns and followed him thorugh land by walking. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
When Yesu came to the shore and he saw the large crowd, he was full of compassion on them and he made good those who were sick.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
When it was evening his following men came to him and said, \u8220?This is a lonely place and it has becoming night. Send them to the close villages to buy food for themselves.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
Yesu answered them, \u8220?They don't have to leave. You.p give them something to eat!\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
They answered him, \u8220?We have are only 5 breads and two fish.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
He said, \u8220?Bring them to me.\u8221? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
He said to the people to sit on the grass. Yesu took the 5 breads and the two fish and looked up to heaven, he gave thanks to God and broke the breads and gave them to his following men, and his following men gave them to the people. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
Everyone ate and were satisfied, and the following men took up 12 baskets full of foods which was left over. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
There were 5,000 men ate food, but not counted the women and children.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu walked on the water
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
Immediately Yesu said to his following men to get into the boat and go on ahead to the other side of the lake, while he sent crowd away. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
After he sent the people, he went up a mountain by himself to talk with God. When evening came, he was alone. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
This bout with the disciples in it was in the middle of the lake. It was a long way from the land. The wind was blowing against the bout and the water was hitting it.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
It was nearly dawn Yesu came to them walking on the water. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
When the following men saw him walking on the water, they said, \u8220?It's a ghost!\u8221? and shouted in fear.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
Yesu spoke to them at once. \u8220?Take strength! I am. Don't be afraid!\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
Fit\u232? answered him, \u8220?Lord, if you.s are, order me to walk on the water to you.s.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
Yesu answered him, \u8220?Come!\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 So Fit\u232? got out of the boat and walked on the water to Yesu. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
But when he saw the strong wind blowing, so he was afraid and started to sink down. Then he shouted, \u8220?Lord, save me!\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
At once Yesu reached out his hand and grabbed him and said to him, \u8220?What little big mind(faith) do you.s have! Why did you.p doubt?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
They.d got into the boat, and the wind stopped. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
Those who were in the boat worshiped Yesu with this talk, \u8220?Truly you.s are the Son of God!\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu makes good the sick people in Genesaret
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
When they crossed the lake and came to Genesaret. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 35\~}
When the people of that place recognized Yesu, they sent talk to all the close country and they brought all who were sick to him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 36\~}
They begged him to let the sick people at least touch the edge of his cloth and all who touched it for making well.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 15
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 God's law surpasses the way of the ancestors
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
Then some Farasi men and teaching men of the law who came from Jerusalem to Yesu and asked him, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
\u8220?Why do your.s following men break the teaching thing of our ancestors? They don't wash the hands first and later they eat!\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
Yesu answered them, \u8220?Why do you.p break God's law with anscester's way? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
God said, \u8216?Respect your.p father and your.p mother,\u8217? and \u8216?Anyone who curses his father or mother is to be put to death.\u8217? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
But you teach that a person may say to his father or to his mother, \u8220?I would have given gifts to help you. But I cannot do that because I have given them to God.\u8221? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
You.p do that and say that they do not need to respect their parents. With this way you.p deny God's word in order to follow your.p anscestor's teaching. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
You are hypocrites! Aisaya's happening talk(prophesy) was true about you.p:
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
These people honor me only with the lips,
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 but their hearts are far away from me.
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
They worship me without.meaning,
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 because they teach men's law as though they were my laws!\u8217?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
Yesu called the crowd and said to them, \u8220?Listen and understand! {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
What goes into someone's mouth goes into stomach does not make people dirty, but what comes out of his mouth makes him dirty.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
Then the following men came to Yesu and asked, \u8220?Do you.s know that the Farasi men had angry when they heard your.s talk?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
He answered them, \u8220?Every tree which my Father in heaven did not plant, he will pull them out. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
Leave them; don't worry about them! They are blind leading men; and if a blind man leads another blind man, both will fall into a hole.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
Fit\u232? said, \u8220?Explain this parable's meaning to us.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
Yesu said to them, \u8220?Are you.p still no understand? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
You.p should understand what goes into your.p mouth goes into your.p stomach and out of your.p body. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
But what bad things come out of the mouth come from the heart, and these things make people bad. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
Evil thoughts which come from your.p heart lead you.p, murder, adultery, sexual immorality, stealing, lying, evil talk about other people. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
These things make you.p dirty; but to eat food without washing hands doesn't make you.p dirty.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 A woman's big mind(faith)
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
Yesu left that place and went off to region of Taire and Sidon. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
A woman from Kanan who lived in that region came to him and cried out, \u8220?Lord, Son of Deifid! Have mercy on me! My daughter has a evil spirit and is a very big problem.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
But Yesu did not answer her. So his following men came to him and begged Yesu, \u8220?Send this woman out, because she is following us and making a noise.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
Then Yesu answered them, \u8220?He(God) sent me only to the lost sheep of the people of Israil.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
At this talk the woman came and knelt at his feet and said, \u8220?Lord, help me!\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
Yesu answered her, \u8220?It isn't straight to throw the children's food to the dogs.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
She answered him, \u8220?That's true, Lord, but the dogs eat the small pieces that fall from their owner's table.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
So Yesu said to her, \u8220?Woman, your big mind(faith) is very big! What you.s want I will do for you.s." And at once her daughter became good.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu make many people good
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
Yesu left that area and went along the sea of Galili. He climbed a mountain and sat down. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
Large crowds came to him, bringing with them the lame, the blind, the crippled, the mute and many other sick people, whom they laid at Yesu' feet, and he made them good. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
The people were amazed when they saw the mute in speaking, the crippled made well, the lame on walking, and the blind seeing, and so they praised the God of Israil.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu feed 4,000 men
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
Yesu called his following men to him and said, \u8220?I am sorry for these people, because they have been with me for three days and now have nothing to eat. I don't want to send them away with hungry because they might fall down on their way.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
The following men answered him, \u8220?Where will we find food in this desert to feed this crowd?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
Yesu asked them, \u8220?How much bread do you.p have?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 They answered him, \u8220?Seven breads and a few small fish.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 35\~}
Yesu told the crowd to sit down on the ground. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 36\~}
Then he took the 7 breads and the fish and gave thanks to God, and broke them [and] gave them to the following men; and they gave them to the people. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 37\~}
All the people ate and were satisfied. After this following men took up 7 baskets full of pieces left over. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 38\~}
There were 4,000 men in eating, but not counting the women and children.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 39\~}
After Yesu sent the crowds away, he got into a boat and went to the area of Magadan.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 16
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 They demanded for doing a showing thing
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
The Farasi men and Saduki men came to Yesu and tested him by asking him to show them a showing thing to show that God gave him this power.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
Yesu answered them, \u8220?When the evening comes, you.p say, \u8216?There will be no rain, because the sky is red.\u8217? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
Early in the morning you.p say that, \u8216?Wind is going to blow and rain is going to fall, because the sky is red and with rain clouds.\u8217? So, you.p see whatever signs are in the sky, and say what they mean, but you.p do not know the showing things of the days! {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
A wicked and big without.mind(unfaithful) generation looks for a showing thing, but I will give it only the showing thing of Jona." Then Yesu left them [and] went away.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The yeast of the Farasi men and Saduki men
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
When they crossed over to the other side of the lake, the following men forgot to take cooked flaw\u233?(bread). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
Yesu said to them, \u8220?Be careful! Be on your.p guard about the yeast of the Farasi men and Saduki men.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
They became discussing among themselves and said, \u8220?[it is]because we didn't bring any bread.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
