\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Who cause ordinary men to sin
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
\u8220?It would be bad for him to have a large stone tied around his neck and be drowned in the deep sea. But if anyone causes one of these ordinary man who truly approve(believe) me to fall into sin would be very bad to him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
How bad for the world because world life make people fall into sin! These things will always happen but how bad for the person who causes these things!
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
If your.s hand or your.s foot makes you.s to do sin, cut it off and throw it away! It is bad for you.s to enter life with one hand or one foot, but it is real bad for you have both hands and both feet and be thrown into the eternal fire. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
And if your.s eye makes you.s to do sin, take it out and throw it away! It is bad for you.s to enter life with only one eye, but it is real bad for you.s have both eyes and be thrown into the eternal fire.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The parable of the lost sif
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
"Be careful! You.p don't look at one of these ordinary men low. Because I tell you.p that their men carrying heavenly message(angels) there in heaven are always seeing the face of my Father.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
\u8220?What do you.p think? If a sif watching man has 100 sif and one of them gets lost, will leave the other 99 sif on the mountains and go to look for the lost sif? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
I tell you.p the truth, when he finds sif, his rejoicing about that would surpass his rejoicing about 99 sif which were already there. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
In the same way your.p Father in heaven does not want any of these ordinary people to be lost.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 When someone sins to you.s
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
\u8220?If your.s believing friend do sin to you.s, go to him and show him his sin. But do it alone just in yourselves. If he listens to you.s, you.s have won your.s believing friend back. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
But if he will not listen to you.s, take one or two people with you to speak to him. They will know what wrong things your.s believing friend has done. Remember how the Bible says: \u8220?There must be two or three people to say that another person has done something wrong. Two or three people must agree what has happened.\u8221? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
If he will not listen to them, then tell everything to my family(church). If he will not listen the talk of the my family(church), then don't help and leave him as Outside man(Gentile) or a evil tax collecting man.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
I tell you.p the truth, whatever you.p bind on earth will be bound in heaven in the same way, and when you.s loose here on earth will be loosed in heaven in the same way.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
I also tell you.p, if two of you.d agree here on earth what you.d ask, my Father in heaven will do it for you.d. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
For where two or three gether in my name, I am there with them.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The parable of the without.forgetting(forgive) without.payment working man(servant)
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
Then Fit\u232? came to Yesu and asked him, \u8220?Lord, if my friend keeps on sinning to me, how many times shall I forget him his sin? 7 times?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
Yesu answered him, \u8220?No, not 7 times but 70 times 7."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
Then Yesu said, "I will tell you a talk to show what the kingdom of heaven is like. A the ruling man(king) called his workmen to come and repay to him what they.p had got from him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
Then the ruling man(king) began to do. His people led a without.payment working man(servant) to him who had a many money without payback. He must pay back 10 millions kina to him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
He couldn't pay, so the ruling man(king) said that he and his wife and his children and all of that he had be exchanged for money to pay back his payment.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
The without.payment working man(servant) knelt down before the ruling man(king) and begged, \u8216?Give me some more time, and I will pay back you.s every payment.\u8217? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
The ruling man(king) felt sorry for him, so he forget his payment and let him go.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
Then the man went out and met one of his fellow without.payment working men(servants) who did not pay back to him 3,000 kina. He grabbed him and started choking him with this talk and said, \u8216?Pay back my money!\u8217?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
His fellow without.payment working man(servant) knelt down and begged to him, \u8216?Give me some more time, and I will pay it back!\u8217?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
But he was refusing and went out and put this man into darkness house until he could pay the debt.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
When the other without.payment working men(servants) saw what had happened, they became very without.joy and went to the ruling man(king) and told him everything. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
Then king called the without.payment working man(servant) in and said to him, \u8216?You evil without.payment working man(servant)! I forgot the whole your payment without.payback to me just because you.p begged me to do. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
You should have mercy on your.s fellow without.payment working man(servant), just as I had mercy on you.s. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
In this anger the ruling man(king) sent this man to the darkness house to be punished until he should pay back the whole payment.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 35\~}
And Yesu said last talk, \u8220?That is how my Father in heaven will do you.p, if you.p don't forget your.p other believing people's sin from your.p heart.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 19
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu teaches about sending away wife
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
When Yesu finished this teaching talk, he left Galili region and went to the region of Judia on the other side of the Joden river. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
Large crowds followed him, and he made the sick people good there.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
Some Farasi men came to him [and] tried to trap him by asking talk, \u8220?Does our law allow a man to send away his wife for doing any things?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
Yesu answered them, \u8220?Have you.p read the Buk which says that in the beginning God made man and woman? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
And God said, \u8216?For this reason a man will leave his father and mother and joined to his wife, and the two will become one.\u8217? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
So they.d are not two, but one. No man must separate what God made them.d one.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
The Farasi men asked him, \u8220?So why did Moses give the law for a man to send her with sending away paper?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
Yesu answered them, \u8220?Moses permitted you.p to send away your.p wives because your.p heart were hard. But it was not this way from the beginning. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
I tell you.p this, whoever sends away his wife, and marries another wife, he commits adultery. If his wife commited adultary, then he is not commit adultary.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
His following men said to him, \u8220?If a man and wife live underneath that talk, it would be good if they.d did not marry."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
Yesu answered them, \u8220?This without.marrige do not for every people, but only to those people God has given it. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
There are many reasons why men cannot marry: some, because they were born that way; other people, because men made them that way; and other people do not marry for the sake of the kingdom of heaven. If a man who can live without marry, let him do so.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu blesses children
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
Some people brought children to Yesu for him to to place his hands and to talk with God for them. But his following men stopped the people. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
Yesu said, \u8220?Let the children come to me, do not stop them, because the kingdom of heaven belongs to such as these children.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
He placed his hands on them and then went away.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The rich young man
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
A man came to Yesu and asked, \u8220?Teacher, what good thing must I do to receive eternal life?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
Yesu answered him, \u8220?Why do you.s ask me about good things? There is nobody but only God. If you.s want to enter life, do what the law says."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
He asked, \u8220?What kind laws are?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu answered him, \u8220?Do not kill people; do not commit adultery; do not steal; do not testify falsely about other people; {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
respect father and mother; and love your close people just as yourself.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
The young rich man replied, \u8220?I have obeyed all these laws. What do I still miss?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
Yesu said to him, \u8220?If you.s want to be without.flaw(perfect), go and exchange sell all things you.s have for money and give the money to the poor, and your.p riches will be kept in heaven; then come and follow me.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
When the young man heard this talk, he went away sad, because he was very rich.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
Yesu said to his following men, \u8220?Truly I tell you.p: it will be very hard for rich people to enter the kingdom of heaven. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
I say again: it is hard for a camel to go through the eye of a needle, but a rich man to enter the ruling of God is very hard and its difficulty surpasses that.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
When the following men heard this, they were very surprised and asked, \u8220?Who can be saved?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
Yesu was looking straightly at them and answered them, \u8220?This is impossible for men, but for God is possible everything.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
Fit\u232? said, \u8220?Look, we have left everything for following you.s. What will we have?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
Yesu said to them, \u8220?Truly I tell you, when God will make all things become new, the Son of Man will sit on his big light(glorious) ruling sitting place, you.p 12 followers of mine will also sit on ruling sitting place, to rule the 12 tribes of Israil. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
And soemone who has left his own houses or brothers or sisters or father or mother or children or fields for my sake, will receive 100 times reward and I will give him eternal life. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
But many people who now are first will be last, and many who now are last will be first.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 20
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The workers in the grape fruit vine garden
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
\u8220?The kingdom of heaven is like this. A landowner went out early in the morning to hire some men to work for money in his grape fruit vine garden. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
He agreed to pay them the wage, for normal daily pay, and sent them to work in his grape fruit vine garden.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
He went out again to the marketplace at 9 o'clock and saw some men standing without.working. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
So he told them, \u8216?You also go and work in the grape fruit vine garden, and I will pay you.p straightly.\u8217? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
So they went. Then at 12 o'clock and again at 3 o'clock he went to the exchanging place and picked some more workers. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
It was close to 5 o'clock when he went to the marketplace and saw some other people are still standing there. He asked them, \u8216?Why are you.p standing long day without working?\u8217?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
They answered him, \u8216?No one asked us for mani work.'
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 He told them, \u8216?Okay you.p go to work in the grape fruit vine garden.'
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
When evening came, the owner told his guarding man(manager), \u8216?Call the workers and pay them their wages, from who joined work later and ending to who joined work first.\u8217?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
These men who had begun to work at 5 o'clock were paid normal daily pay to each one. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
So when these first workers came to be paid, they thought they would get more. But they were also given only normal daily pay each. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
When they took their money and started grumbling to the owner. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
\u8216?These men worked only one hour, but you've paid them just as much as you paid us who worked all day in the very hot day\u8217? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
The owner answered one of them, 'Listen, friend. I am being same to you.p. You.s agreed to do a day's work for normal daily pay. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
Now take your.p pay and go home. I want to give paymet this man who was hired last the same amount I gave you.s. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
I have the straight to do what I want with my money! Or are you.p jealous because I am good man in giving?\u8217?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
And Yesu said closing talk, \u8220?Those who are last will be first, and those who are first will be last.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu speaks about his death a third time
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
When Yesu was going up to Jerusalem, he took the 12 following men moved aside and spoke to them in themselves, as they walked along. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
He told them \u8220?Listen, we are going up to Jerusalem, where they will hand the Son of Man over to the leading sacrifice burning people(priests) and the teaching men of the law. They will say he must die {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
and hand him over to the side people, who will make fun of him, whip him, and put on cross tree. But three days later he will rise to life.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 A mother's request
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
Then the Jefedi's sons, Jems and Jon their mother came to Yesu with her two sons, bowed before him, and asked Yesu to do her want.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
Yesu asked her, \u8220?What do you.s want?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 She answered him, \u8220?Give me without.lying talk that my two sons will allow to sit at your.s right and your.p left when you.p take name of King.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
Yesu answered them, \u8220?You.d don't know what you.d are asking for. Can you.d drink the cup of suffering that I am about to drink?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 They answered him, \u8220?We.d can.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
Yesu told them.d, \u8220?You.d will possible to drink the cup of suffering which I am going to drink. But I do not have the power to make who will sit at my right and my left. These places belong to those for whom my Father has prepared them.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
When the other 10 following men heard about this, they became angry with these two men. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
So Yesu called them all and said, \u8220?You know that the rulers of the Side people have power over them for ruling, and the leaders force people to follow whatever rules they set down. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
This is not happened to you.p like they are. Whoever wants to be big, he must become your.p without.payment working man(servant), {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
and if one of you.p wants to be first, you.p must be your without.payment working man(servant). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
The Son of Man did not come they would serve him, but to serve them and to give his life to save many people.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu heals two blind men
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
Later, Yesu and his following men were leaving Jericho, a large crowd was following. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
Two blind men who were sitting by the road heard that Yesu was passing by, so they.d began to shout, \u8220?Son of Deifid! Have mercy on us.d, Lord!\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
The crowd rebuked them.d "Be quiet!" But they.d shouted even more loudly, \u8220?Son of Deifid! Have mercy on us, Lord!\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
Yesu stopped and called them.d. \u8220?What do you.d want I will do for you.d?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
They.d answered him, \u8220?Lord, we.d want you we.d can see!\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
Yesu felt sorry for them and touched their.d eyes. At once they.d saw, and they.d followed Yesu.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 21
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu entered Jerusalem
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
When Yesu and his following men approached Jerusalem, they came to Betfage at the Mount of Olif. Yesu sent his two following men on ahead {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
with these talks: \u8220?Go to the village ahead of you.d, and at once you.d will find a ndonki and her colt tied up there. Untie them.d and bring them.d to me. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
And if anyone asks to you.d, tell him, \u8216?The Lord wants,\u8217? and then he will let you take them at once.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
This happened for what God's man who make know(prophet) said:
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
\u8220?Sat to the Jerusalem people,
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Look, your.p the ruling man(king) is coming to you.p!
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 He is lowers himself(humble) and rides on a young ndonki.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
So the two following men went and did what Yesu had told them.d to do. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
They brought the ndonki and the young ndonki, set on their clothes on them, and Yesu got on. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
A large crowd also spread their clothes on the road while other people cut branches from the trees and spread them on the road. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
The crowds who went ahead of Yesu and those who were following shouted,
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 \u8220?Lift up Deifid's Son!
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 God blesses him who comes in the name of the Lord!
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Lift up God!\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
When Yesu entered Jerusalem, the whole people in city were surprising and confusing and the people asked "Who is he?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
The crowds answered them, \u8220?This is the God's man who make know(prophet) Yesu, from Najaret in Galili region.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu goes to the worshipping house
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
Yesu went into the worshipping house courts and started chasing out those who were buying and selling things there. He turned over the tables of the moneychangers and the sitting tables(chairs) of those who sold mamu(pigeons), {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
and said to them, \u8220?It is written in the Scriptures that God said, \u8216?They will call my house a house of talking with God.\u8217? But you.p have changed it into hidding place for thieves!\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
Blind people and crippled people came to Yesu in the worshipping house court, and he made them good. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
The leading sacrifice burning people(priests) and the teaching men of the law became angry when they saw the surprising workings(miracles) he was doing and the children shouting in the worshipping house court, \u8220?Lift up Deifid's Son!\u8221? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
So they asked Yesu, \u8220?Do you.s hear what they are saying?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu answered them, \u8220?Yes I heard. Did you read this Scripture?
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 'Lord God, children a babies praise you.
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 You yourself have taught them to do that.'\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
Yesu left them and went out of the city to Betani, where he spent the night.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu curses the fig tree
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
Early in the morning, Yesu was going back to Jerusalem. In the middle he felt hungry. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
He saw a fig tree by the side of the road and went there, but could not find any fruit on it only leaves. So he said to the tree, \u8220?You.s will never again bear fruit!\u8221? At once the fig tree dried out.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
When the following men saw this doing and were surprised and asked, \u8220?How did this fig tree dry out quickly?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
Yesu answered them, \u8220?I tell you.p truth, that if you.p have big mind(faith) and do not doubt, you.p can do what I have done to this fig tree. And not only this, but you.p can say to this mountain, \u8216?Go and throw yourself in the sea,\u8217? and it will happen. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
If you.p truly approve(believe), you.p will receive whatever you.p ask for in talking with God.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The question about Yesu' authority
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
Yesu came back to the worshipping house courts, and while he was teaching, the leading sacrifice burning people(priests) and the head people came to him and asked, \u8220?What authority do you.s have to do these things? Who gave you.s this authority?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
Yesu answered them, \u8220?I will ask you.p one asking talk, and if you.p give me an answering talk, I will also tell you.p what authority I am doing these things. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
Where did Jon's baptism come from: from God or from men?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 They started to argue among themselves, \u8220?What shall we say? If we answer, \u8216?From God,\u8217? he will say to us, \u8216?Why did you.p not truly approve(believe) Jon?\u8217? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
But if we say, \u8216?From men,\u8217? we are afraid of what the people might do, because all the people think that Jon was a God's man who make know(prophet).\u8221? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
So they answered Yesu, \u8220?We don't know.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 And he said to them, \u8220?I also will not tell you.p by what authority I do these things.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The parable of the two sons
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
\u8220?What do you.p think about this parable? There was a man who had two sons. He went to the older one and said, \u8216?Son, go to work in the grape fruit vine garden today.\u8217? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
He answered him, \u8216?I don't want to.\u8217? But later he changed his mind and went. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
Then that their father went to the other son and said the same thing. He answered him, \u8216?Yes, father.\u8217? But he did not go. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
Which son of the two heard what their father wanted?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 They answered him, \u8220?The first son.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 So Yesu said to them, \u8220?I tell you.p the truth, the money collectors and the prostitutes will be in the kingdom of God ahead of you.p. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
Because Jon the baptist came to you.p showing you.p the straight way to take, and you.p would not truly approve(believe) him; but the tax collectors and the prostitutes truly approved(believed) him. Even when you.p saw these things, you.p did not turn away and truly approve(believe) him.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The parable of the farmers in the grape fruit vine garden
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
Yesu said, \u8220?Listen to another parable. There was a landowner who planted a vines in garden to grow grape fruit there, put a fence around it, dug a hole for the grape fruits press, and built a high watchtower. Then he gave short term the grape fruit vine garden to farmers in order that he will receive some grape fruit from this garden and went to the long place. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
When harvesting time came, he sent some without.payment working men(servants) to the farmers in order that they are going to receive some grape fruit from this garden. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 35\~}
But they grabbed his without.payment working men(servants), whip one, killed one, and stoned one.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 36\~}
Then again he sent many other without.payment working men(servants), and the farmers did them the same way. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 37\~}
Finally he sent his son to them. He said, \u8216?Surely they will respect my son.\u8217? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 38\~}
But when the farmers saw the son, they said to themselves, \u8216?This is the owner's son. Come on, let's kill him, and so this garden will become ours!\u8217? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 39\~}
So they grabbed him, threw him out of the grape fruit vine garden, and killed him.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 40\~}
Yesu asked them, \u8220?So then, when the owner of the grape fruit vine garden comes, what will he do to those farmers?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 41\~}
They answered him, \u8220?He will kill those evil men and give short term(rent) for money the grape fruit vine garden out to other farmers, who will give him his grape fruit in the harvest time.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 42\~}
Yesu said to them, \u8220?Have you.p read this talk in the Scriptures?
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 \u8216?The stone which the builders rejected
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 later became the head stone.
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The Lord has done this,
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 [it is] a so good in our eyes.\u8217?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 43\~}
Yesu said more, \u8220?So I tell you.p, the kingdom of God will be taken away from you.p and given to a people who will produce the good fruits.\u8221? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 44\~}
Anyone who falls on this stone will be broken to pieces and anyone on whom it falls will be crushed.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 45\~}
When the leading sacrifice burning people(priests) and the Farasi men heard Yesu's parables and knew that he was talking about them, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 46\~}
so they tried to arrest him. But they were afraid of the crowds, who thought that Yesu was a God's man who make know(prophet).
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 22
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The parable of the wedding feast
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
Yesu spoke to them again in parable talks: {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
\u8220?The kingdom of heaven is like this. There was the ruling man(king) who prepared a wedding feast meal for his son. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
He sent his without.payment working men(servants) to bring those who were invited before, but they did not want to come.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
"So he sent again other without.payment working men(servants) to say those who were invited before: \u8216?My feast is ready now. I killed my male cow and some fat young cows, and every feast is ready! Come to the wedding feast.\u8217?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
"But the guests who are invited before did not agree to come and went away to do their want: one went to his field, another to his store, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
while other people grabbed his without.payment working men(servants), beat them, and killed them. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
The ruling man(king) was very angry. So he sent his soldiers to that city where those people lived. They killed the people who killed the ruling man(king)'s without.payment working men(servants) and destroyed their town with fire.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
"Then he called his without.payment working men(servants) and said to them, \u8216?My wedding feast is ready, but the people I invited are not enough to come. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
Now go to always [using] road and invite to the feast as many people as you.p find.\u8217? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
So the without.payment working men(servants) went out into the roads and took all the people who they has found, good and bad people, and people filled the wedding feast house.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
"The ruling man(king) went in to see the guests. He saw one man who was not wearing wedding clothes. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
The ruling man(king) asked him, \u8216?Friend, how did you.s get in here without wedding clothes?\u8217? But the man did not answer.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
"Then the ruling man(king) told the without.payment working men(servants), \u8216?Tie up his hand and foot, and throw him outside in the dark place. There he will cry and grind his teeth.\u8217?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
"Yesu said final talk, 'Many are invited, but few are chosen.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The question about putting money to Rom high ruling man, Kaisar
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
The Farasi men went out and made a trap with lying talk Yesu what he would say for what they could arrest him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
Then they sent their following men to Yesu and some people from Erod's group and they said, \u8220?Teacher, we know that you.s are the man who are telling the truth. You.s teach the truth what God's will for people. You.s are not afraid what other people think of you.s, because you.p see all the people same standard. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
Then tell us, how do you.s think? Is it straight to pay taxes to the Rom high ruling man(Emperor), Kaisar or not?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
But Yesu knew their bad mind and he said, \u8220?You.p see good outside but inside not! Why are you.p putting to trap me with lying talk? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
Show me the coin which is paying tax to him!\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 They brought him a coin, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
and he asked them, \u8220?Whose face and name is this?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
They answered him, \u8220?Kaisar's.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 So Yesu said to them, \u8220?Give to Kaisar what is his, and give to God what is his.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
When they heard this, they were surprised and they left him and went away.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The question about rising from death
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
At that same day some Saduki men came to Yesu asking. They believed that people will not rise from death. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
They said, \u8220?Teacher! Moses wrote the law that if a man who has no children dies, his younger brother must marry the widow and produce children for his elder brother. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
7 brothers lived here among us. The first born married and died without having children, so he left his widow to his younger brother. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
The second married and died, and third married her. It happened until 7th who was. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
Finally the woman died. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
On that day when the dead rise to life, whose wife will she be? Because all of them had married her.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
Yesu answered them, \u8220?Your mind are wrong. Because you don't know the Scriptures or God's power. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
When dead people rise to life, they will be like the men carrying heavenly message(angels) in heaven and will not marry. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
As for dead people rising to life, have you.p not read what God has told you.p? God said, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
\u8216?I am the God of Ebraam, the God of Aisek, and the God of Jeikof.\u8217? He is the God of the living, not the God of the dead.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
When the crowds heard this, they were surprised at his teaching.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The big law
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
When the Farasi men heard that Yesu had stopped the Saduki men, Farasi m\u233?n gathered together, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 35\~}
and one of Farasi men who was a teaching man of the law, thought test Yesu with a question. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 36\~}
He asked him, \u8220?Teacher! Which law surpasses the other laws?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 37\~}
Yesu answered him, \u8220?\u8216?Love your. s Lord God with all your.s heart, with all your.s spirit, and with all your.s mind.\u8217? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 38\~}
This is the first and very big law. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 39\~}
The second very big law is, \u8216?Love your.s neighbor as yourself love.\u8217? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 40\~}
These two laws are basis of all the law of Moses and the teachings of the God's people who make know(prophets).\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The question about Keriso
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 41\~}
When some Farasi men gathered together, Yesu asked them, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 42\~}
\u8220?How do you.p think about that Keriso? Whose descendant is he?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 They answered him, \u8220?He is Deifid's descendant.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 43\~}
Yesu asked them, \u8220?then why did God Spirit lead Deifid to call him 'Lord'? David said,
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 44\~}
\u8216?The Lord God said to my Lord:
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Sit here at my right side
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 until I put your.s enemies under your.s feet.\u8217?
\par\pard\plain \s61\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 45\~}
If Deifid called that Keriso \u8216?Lord,\u8217? how can Keriso be his descendant?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 46\~}
No one could give Yesu any answer, and from that day and another day, everyoen was afraid to ask Yesu any more questions.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 23
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu let them know about the teaching men of the law and the Farasi men
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
Then Yesu spoke to the crowds and to his following men. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
\u8220?The teaching men of the law and the Farasi men have power to explain of meaning of Moses' law. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
You.p must hear and follow everything what they tell you.p to do, but do not copy their actions, because they don't put action what they teach. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
They put the heavy things up people's shoulders which are heavy and hard to carry, but their helping hand is not to carry this burden.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
"They do everything so that people will see them. They wear small boks with writing Buk verses in them, but they make these boks very big. They tied long tassels on their clothe! {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
They always want to get honarable places at feasts and the the best sitting places in the meeting houses, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
their joy is people greet them in the marketplaces and call them \u8216?Teacher.\u8217?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
"People must not call you.p \u8216?Teacher,\u8217? because you.p are all equal and have only one Teacher. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
And you.p must not say anyone here on earth \u8216?Father,\u8217? because your.p Father in heaven is only the one. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
Others must not call you.p \u8216?Leading man,\u8217? because your.p one and only leading man is that Keriso. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
The very high person among you.p must be your.p without.payment working man(servant). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
Whoever lift himself up God will put them low, and whoever be low himself God will put him high.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu talks about bad things of Farasi men and teacher of Moses's law
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
\u8220?How bad for you.p, teaching men of the law and Farasi men. You.p see good outside but inside not! You.p lock the door to the kingdom of heaven in front of the people. You.p yourselves don't go in, and you.p do not allow those who want to enter!{\super e{\footnote \pard\plain \s212\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28  {\super e}{{\cs214\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 23.14 }
{\cs215\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 In some Greek books verse 14 is there, but in many Greek books it is not. That talk is: \u8220?You.p teachers of the law and Farasi men who looks good outside but inside not. How bad you are. You.p deceive widows and take their.p houses and possessions as your.p own, and you.p make very long prayers so that others will see you.p. Later on the last day you.p will receive very big heavies.\u8221?}
}}}

\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
\u8220?How bad for you.p, teaching men of the law and Farasi men. You.p see good outside but inside not! You.p traveled the seas by bout and cross whole countries to find one follower, and when you.p find this man, you.p make him very bad for without stopping fire, his sin surpasses your.p sin!
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
\u8220?How bad for you.p, blind leading men! You. are in teaching, \u8216?If a man says oaths by the worshipping house's name, he can break his talk. But if he say oaths by the gold in the worshipping house, they must not break his talk.\u8217? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
Blind foolish men! Which is very big, the gold or the worshipping house which makes the gol without.dust(holy)? The worshipping house. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
You also teach, \u8216?If a man says oaths by the table for burning sacrifice(altar), he can break his talk. But if he says oaths by the gift on the table for sacrifice burning(altar), he must not break his talk.\u8217? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
You blind men! Which is very high, the gift or the table for burning sacrifice which makes the gift without.dust(holy)? The alter. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
Therefore, when a man says oaths by the table for burning sacrifice, he is swearing by it and by all the gifts on it. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
And when he says oath by the worshipping house, he says oath by it and by God, who lives there. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
And whoever says oath by heaven, he says oath by God's ruling sitting place and by God who lives on it.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
\u8220?How bad for you.p, teaching men of the law and Farasi men! You.p see good outside but inside not! You.p give to God one tenth even of small things such as ginger, green leaves, but you.p neglect the really big teachings what is in the law, such as straightness and mercy and big mind(faith). You.p should do small things' one tenth of it, but you.p also should do these big things. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
Blind leading men! You.p take a fly out of your.p cup, but swallow a kemol!
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
\u8220?How bad for you.p, teaching men of the law and Farasi men! You.p see good outside but inside not! You.p wash the outside of your.p cup and plate, while the inside is full of evil thinking and selfishness. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
Blind Farasi men! You.p must wash the inside of the cups and plates first, and the outside will be clean too!
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
\u8220?How bad for you.p, teaching men of the law and Farasi men! You.p see good outside but inside not! You.p are like outside white but inside decayed graving house, which look fine on the outside but the inside are full of dead people's bones and decayed body. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
In the same way, on the outside you.p appear good to everybody, but inside you.p are full of decay and sins.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu says their punishment
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
\u8220?How bad for you.p, teaching men of the law and Farasi men! You.p see good outside but inside not! You.p make good graves for them the God's people who make know(prophets) and decorate the graves of those who lived straight lives. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
You.p say, 'If we had lived during the time of our ancestors, we would not have done what they did [and] killed the God's people who make know(prophets). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
You.p really say that you.p are the descendants of those who murdered the God's people who make know(prophets)! {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
Then go on and continue to do the same thing what your.p ancestors did sin!
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
"You.p snakes and children of snakes! Which way will you.p save from you.p go the hell for your.p sin? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
I tell you.p that I will send you.p God's people who make know(prophets) and wise men and teaching men. You.p will kill some of them, nail them on the cross, and whip other people there in the meeting houses and chase them from town to other town. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 35\~}
Murder of the straight people's punishment is for you.p, from straight man Abel to Jakaraya son of Berekia, whom you.p murdered between the worshipping house and the table for burning sacrifice. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 36\~}
I tell you.p the truth: the punishment of the murder for all these people will be to this generation!
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu' love for Jerusalem
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 37\~}
"Jerusalem, Jerusalem! You.s kill the God's people who make know(prophets) and throw stones the messengers God has sent you.p! How many times I wanted I surrounded my arms all your.s people, just as a mother chicken gathers her chicks under her wings, but you.s would not let me! {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 38\~}
Now your.s worshipping house will left and empty. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 39\~}
From now on, I tell you.s Jerusalem, you.s will never see me again until you.s say, \u8216?God bless him who comes in the name of the Lord.\u8217?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 24
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu talks about the future
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
Yesu left the worshipping house. While he walking away, his following men came to him and they show him the good worshipping house and its buildings. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
He said, \u8220?Enough/o.k., you.p see all these buildings. I tell you.p the truth that, not any stone here will remain on the top of another stone, every things are in throwing.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Happening things of last time
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
As Yesu sat on the Mount of Olif, the following men came to him in private and asked him, \u8220?Tell us when these things will happen to the temple and what will happen to show that the day has come for your.s coming and the end of the world.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
Yesu answered them, \u8220?Watch out, do not let anyone deceive you.p. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
Many people will come in my name and say, \u8216?I am Keriso!\u8217? and they will deceive many people. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
You.p are going to hear of war close by and the news of battles far away; but do not be afraid. Those things must happen, but this meaning is not that the end of the day has come. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
One country will fight with other country each other, the king's country will attack with other king's country. There will be famines and earthquakes in various places. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
These things are like the first pains when it is in baby born.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
"They will arrest you.p and persecute you.p and put you.p to death. All the people of the world will hate you.p because of me. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
At that day, many will give up their big mind(faith), and they will give teeth(betrayed) and hate each other.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
"Many false God's people who make know(prophets) will appear and deceive many people. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
This evil's works will be wide and people's love will stop. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
But whoever holds strong to last day God will save him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
They will preach this good talk about the kingdom of heaven through all the world to all the people to know, and then the end will come.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Very bad things
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
\u8220?You.p will see \u8216?The very bad things\u8217? of which the God's man who make know(prophet) Daniel spoke. Very bad thing which will stand will cause the worshipping house unclean. \u8221? (Letter to know to the reader: understand what this talk means!) {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
"Those who are in Judia must run away to the mountains. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
Someone who is on the roof of a house must not go down to get anything out of the house. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
Someone who is in the garden must not go back to get a cloth. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
How bad it will be in those days for women who are pregnant and for mothers with little babies! {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
Talk with God so that you.p will not have to run away during the season of most heavy rain or on a Safat! {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
The trouble at that time will be very big bad there were not from the beginning of the world to today. In the future such thing will never be again. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
But if God will not make short the days, nobody can be saved. But for the sake of his chosen people, God will make short the days.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
\u8220?Then, if anyone tells to you.p, \u8216?Look, here is Keriso\u8217? or \u8216?There he is\u8217?\u8212?do not truly approve(believe) it. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
False Kerisoes and false people who make know(false prophets) will come. They will perform very big special workings(miracles) and surprising things in order that they deceive all the people, and also God's chosen people, if it is possible. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
Listen! I have told you.p ahead of time.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
\u8220?Or, if people tells you.p, \u8216?Look, he is there in the clear place!\u8217?\u8212?don't go there; or if they tell, \u8216?Look, he is there in that room!\u8217?\u8212?don't truly approve(believe) it. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
Because the Son of Man will come like the lightning which flashes across the sky from the east to the west.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
\u8220?Wherever there is a dead body, the eagles will gather.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The coming of the Son of Man
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
\u8220?Soon after troubling days,
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 the sun will grow dark,
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 also the moon will no light,
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 the stars will fall from heaven,
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 and the powerful things in heaven will be shaking.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
"At that day the marking shape of the Son of Man will appear in the heaven, and all the peoples of earth will weep as they see the Son of Man coming on the clouds of heaven with power and big light(glory). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
With sound of the trumpet he will send out his men carrying heavenly message(angels) to all the lands and village to gather his chosen people from one end of the world to the other.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Take knowledge from the fig tree
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
\u8220?Take knowldge from fig tree. When its branches become green and tender and it sprout starts putting out leaves, you.p know that dry season is near. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
In the same way, when you.p see all these things, you.p will know that time of the Son of Man's coming is near. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
I tell you this: this generation will not all die until all these things happen. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 35\~}
Heaven and earth will pass away, but my talks will never pass away.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 No one knows when the Son of Man will return
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 36\~}
\u8220?No one knows when that day or hour will be in happening\u8212?not the men carrying heavenly message(angels) in heaven and not the Son but only the Father. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 37\~}
The coming of the Son of Man will be like what happened in Noa's day. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 38\~}
In those days before the flood came people were eating water and food, men and women were marrying, up to the day Noa went into the big boat. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 39\~}
They did not realize what was going to happen until the flood came and swept them all away. That is how it will be when the Son of Man comes. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 40\~}
At that time two men will be working in a garden: the Son of Man will take up one man, he will leave the other himself. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 41\~}
Two women will be at a scrapping casava: the Son of Man will take up one, he will leave the other himself. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 42\~}
Watch out, because you.p do not know in which day your.p Lord will arrive. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 43\~}
If the owner of a house knew the time of the thief, he would have kept watch his house and would not have let the thief enter inside. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 44\~}
So you.p must always be ready. The Son of Man will come at a time when you are not thinking about it.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The faithful or the unfaithful without.payment working man(servant)
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 45\~}
\u8220?Who is a faithful and wise (mind) without.payment working man(servant)? This man who his owner put manager to the other without.payment working men(servants) to give them food at the proper time. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 46\~}
How happy that without.payment working man(servant) is if his owner finds him doing this when he comes home! {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 47\~}
Truly, I tell you.p, the owner will put that without.payment working man(servant) to manage all his things. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 48\~}
But if he is a bad without.payment working man(servant), an he will tell himself, 'My owner will not come back quickly,' {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 49\~}
and he begins to beat his fellow without.payment working men(servants) and to eat and drink alcohol with drunkards. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 50\~}
Then that without.payment working man(servant)'s owner will come back one day when he does not be ready and not wait for him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 51\~}
The owner will cut him in pieces and put him to where hypocrites are. There they will cry and grind his teeth.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 25
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The parable of the ten young women
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
\u8220?At that time the kingdom of heaven will be like this. There were ten unmarried women who took their lamps and went out to meet the bridegroom and go to his wedding feast. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
Five of them were foolish, and the other 5 were wise. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
Those foolish young women took their lamps but did not take other ontop(extra) oil, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
but 5 the wise ones took other extra oil in containers for their lamps. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
The bridegroom was still away, so they felt sleepy and fall asleep.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
\u8220?When it became midnight the sound came, \u8216?Here the bridegroom! Come and welcome him!\u8217? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
The ten young women woke up and prepared their lamps to make them work well. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
Then the foolish young women said to the wise young women, \u8216?Give us some of your.p oil, because our lamps are about to go out.\u8217? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
The wise young women answered them, \u8216?No, there is not enough for you.p and for us. Go to the s\u232?tua and buy some for yourselves.\u8217? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
So the foolish young women went off to buy some oil. While they were gone, the bridegroom arrived, the 5 who were waiting with preparation went in with him to the wedding feast, and the door was closed.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
"Later the other foolish young women arrived and begged, \u8216?Lord, Lord! Open the door for us!\u8217? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
The bridegroom answered them, \u8216?I tell you the truth, I don't know you.p.\u8217?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
Yesu said last talk, \u8220?Watch out, because you.p do not know that day or the hour of my return.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The parable of the three without.payment working men(servants)
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
\u8220?At that time I come again, the kingdom of heaven will be like this. There was a man who was about to go to a trip, he gathered his without.payment working men(servants) and gave his money for them to be in charge of. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
He gave money according to their working ability: to one he gave 5,000 gold coins, to another he gave 2,000 gold coins, and to another he gave 1,000 gold coins. After this he went. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
That without.payment working man(servant) who had received 5,000 gold coins went immediately. He took to make more money. When he did this, he found another 5,000 gold coins. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
In the same way the second without.payment working man(servant) who had received 2,000 gold coins found another 2,000 gold coins. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
But the without.payment working man(servant) who had received 1,000 gold coins went off, dug a hole in the ground, and hid his owner's money.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
"After a long time the owner of those without.payment working men(servants) came back and they let him know about money. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
That without.payment working man(servant) whom he gave 5,000 gold coins came in [and] gave another 5,000 gold coins to him and said, \u8216?You.s gave me 5,000 gold coins, lord. Look! Here are another 5,000 gold coins that I have made.\u8217? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
His owner said, \u8216?Well done, you.s good and faithful without.payment working man(servant)! You have been faithful to manage little things, so I will put you.s the place to manage for many things. Come and be happy with me!\u8217?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
"The without.payment working man(servant) whom he gave 2,000 gold coins came in and said, \u8216?You.s gave me 2,000 gold coins, lord. Look! Here are another 2,000 gold coins which I made.\u8217? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
His owner said to him, \u8216?Well done, you.s good and faithful without.payment working man(servant)! You.s have been faithful to manage small things, so I will put you.s the place to manage for many things. Come on in my good and happiness!\u8217?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
"Other without.payment working man(servant) whom he gave 1,000 gold coins came in and said, \u8216?Lord, I know you.s are a hard/strict man and reap seeds from where you.p did not plant, and you.p gather seeds from where you.p did not scatter seed. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
I was afraid, so I went off and hid your.s money in the ground. Look! Here are what belongs to you.s.\u8217?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
"His owner said, \u8216?You wicked and lazy without.payment working man(servant)! You had known that I reap seeds where I did not plant, and gather seeds where I did not scatter seed. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
Well, you.s should put my money in the bank, and I would have received it all back with interest when I returned. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
Then take the money away from him and give it to the one who has 10,000 gold coins. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
To the one who already has plenty, I will give more and what he has will become very big. And to the one who has little, I will take away from him what little he has. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
As for this lazy without.payment working man(servant), throw him outside into the darkness, where there he will cry and grind his teeth.\u8217?
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The final judement
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
\u8220?When the Son of Man comes as king and with all the men carrying heavenly message(angels), he will sit on his glorious ruling sitting place. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
He will gather the people from all the nations before him. Then he will divide them into two groups, just as a watching man divides the sheep from the gouts. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
He will put the straight people at his right and the other people at his left.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
"Then the King will say to the people on his right, \u8216?Come, you.p who my Father blesses! Come and enter the kingdom which prepared for you.p from the creation of the world. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 35\~}
Because when I was hungry and you.p fed me, thirsty and you.p gave me a drink, I was a stranger and you.p received me in your.p houses, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 36\~}
when I was naked, you.p clothed me, and when I was sick you.p took care of me, and when I was in darkness house you.p visited me.\u8217?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 37\~}
"The straight people will answer him, \u8216?Lord, when did we see you.s was hungry, feed you.s food, or when you was thirsty and give you.s a drink? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 38\~}
When did we see you.s a stranger, receive you.s in our houses, or when you was without.clothes to wear, we clothe you.s? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 39\~}
When did we see you.s sick or in darkness house, and visit you.s?\u8217? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 40\~}
The king will reply to them, \u8216?I tell you.p the truth, you.p did it for one small man of my believers, you.p did it for me!\u8217?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 41\~}
\u8220?Then he will also say to those on his left, "Go away from me, you.p who are under God's anger! Go away to the eternal fire which he prepared for the S\u225?if\u232?r and his evil spirits! {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 42\~}
When I was hungry, you.p would not feed me, thirsty, you.p would not give me a drink, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 43\~}
and when I was a stranger, you.p would not welcome me in your.p houses, and when I was naked you.p would not clothe me, and when I was sick you are not look after me, and when I was in darkness house but you.p would not visit me.\u8217?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 44\~}
"Then they will answer him, \u8216?Lord, when did we see you.s hungry or thirsty or a stranger or naked or sick or in darkness house, would we not help you.s?\u8217? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 45\~}
The King will reply, \u8216?I tell you.p the truth, when you.p did not help one little man of my believers, you.p do not help me.\u8217?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 46\~}
"Then they will go away into unstopped pain, but the straight will go to eternal life.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 26
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The leading burning sacrifice man and teaching men of the law made plans to kill Yesu
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
When Yesu's teaching about all things had finished, he said to his following men, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
\u8220?As you.p know, in two days, there will be the Passover festival{\super f{\footnote \pard\plain \s212\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28  {\super f}{{\cs214\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 26.2 }
{\cs217\b0\i\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Passover festival }
{\cs215\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 At that time they remember when, in order for God to get back the Israel people from Ijip, an angel came & passed by the children of Israel & struck & killed the firstborn sons of Ijip }
}}}
, and they will give the Son of Man to be nailed on the crossing tree.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
The leading men who sacrifice(chief priests) and the leading people gathered together in the big house of Kayafas, the high burning sacrifice man(high priest), {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
and they were looking for the thoughts(made plans) to arrest Yesu secretly and put Yesu to death. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
They said, \u8220?We must not arrest him during the festival or the people will be angry to us.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 A woman poured Yesu with good smell liquid at Betani
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
Yesu was in Betani there at the house of Saimon, a man who was previously in suffering from a bad skin disease. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
While Yesu was eating food, a woman came to him with a stone container where were with very big money special smelling liquid, and poured it on Yesu's head. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
When the following men saw this and became angry and asked, \u8220?Why this waste? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
This woman could have sold it for a lot of money. Then she could have given the money to poor people.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
Yesu knew what they were saying, and so he said to them, \u8220?Do not make trouble to this woman. She has done this very good thing for me. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
The poor people will always be with you, but I will not always with you.p. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
She did this good to pour the special smelling liquid on my body to prepare my making the ground(burial). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
I tell you.p the truth, all the places over the world where people tell this good news, they will also tell what this woman has done and they will remember her.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Judas goes for teeth(to betray) Yesu
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
Judas Iskariot, [who] was the one of 12 following men, went to the leading men who sacrifice(chief priests) {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
and asked them, \u8220?What will you.p give me if I give teeth(betray) Yesu to you.p?\u8221? They started counting money and grapped thirty silver coins and gave them to him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
From then Judas was about to look for a good way how he will give teeth(betray) Yesu to them.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu ate the final meal with his following men
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
On the first day of the Festival of without.yeast bread, the following men came to Yesu and asked him, \u8220?Where is your wanting that we are going to prepare the Passover festival food for you.s?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
He said to them, \u8220?Go to one man [who] is in the city and tell him: \u8216?The teaching man says: My time has come, I will eat the Passover festival food with my disciples in your.s house.\u8217?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
The following men did as how Yesu had told them to prepare the Passover festival's food.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
When it became evening, Yesu and his 12 following men sat down to eat. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
While they were eating Yesu said to them, \u8220?I tell you.p the truth, one man here will give teeth(betray) me.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
This talk made following men sad and each one of them said, \u8220? Lord, You.s are talking about me?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
Yesu answered them, \u8220?Here one man who dips his bread in one dish with me he will give teeth(betray) me. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
The Son of Man will die as the Scriptures is written he will do, but how bad for that man who will give teeth(betray) the Son of Man! It would be good he had not been born!\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
Judas, teeth man(betrayor), said, \u8220?Teaching man, you.s are talking about me?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu answered him, \u8220?You.s have said truly.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The Lord's last meal
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
While they were eating food, Yesu took whole bread, give thanks to God, and broke it, and gave it to his following men and said, \u8220?Take and eat it. This is my body.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
Then he took a cup, gave thanks to God, and gave it to them and said, \u8220?Drink it, all of you.p. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
This is my blood of the agreement, which is poured out for the forgetting many people's sins. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
I tell you.p, I will never drink this alcohol until the day I will drink the new alcohol with you.p there in my Father's kingdom.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
Then they sang a song to God and went to the Mount of Olif.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu told Fit\u232?'s denial
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
Then Yesu said to them, \u8220?Tonight all of you.p will run away and leave me, as the Buk(scripture) says, \u8216?I, God will kill the watching man of sif, and the sif will be scattered.\u8217? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
But after I am raised to life, I will go to Galili region ahead of you.p.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
Fit\u232? answered him, \u8220?I will never leave you.s, but only other people will leave you.s!\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
Yesu said to Fit\u232?, \u8220?I tell you.s the truth, firstly you.s will say three times, 'I don't know Yesu.' After that the male chicken crows tonight. \u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 35\~}
Fit\u232? answered him, \u8220?I will never say that, it's okay, I will die with you.!\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 And all the other following men said the same talk.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu talks with God in Getsemane
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 36\~}
Yesu and his following men went to a place named Getsemane, and he said to them, \u8220?Sit here while I go over there to talk with God.\u8221? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 37\~}
He took Fit\u232? and the two sons of Jefedi to go. He felt sad and heavy. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 38\~}
Then he said to them, \u8216?I am very sad. This sadness might kill me. Wait here and stay awake with me.\u8217?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 39\~}
Yesu went not far, he fell down with his face to the ground and talked with God, \u8220?My Father, if it is possible, take this pain [which]is coming to me! But do not what I want, but will happen what you.s want.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 40\~}
Then Yesu turned back to the three following men and saw them asleep, and he said to Fit\u232?, \u8220?You.p were not able to watch(stay awake) with me for one hour? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 41\~}
Stay awake up and talk with God so that temptation will not overtake you.p. The spirit is willing to do good thing, but the body is weak.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 42\~}
Once more Yesu went to talk with God, \u8220?My Father, if you cannot take away this pain unless I drink it, your.s will will be done.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 43\~}
Yesu came back again and saw the following men asleep, because their eyes are heavy.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 44\~}
Yesu left them again and went and talked with God the third time, repeated the same talks. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 45\~}
Then Yesu went back to the following men and said, \u8220?Are you.p still sleeping and resting? Look! The hour has come for they are about to put the Son of Man into the hands of sinners. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 46\~}
Get up, let us go. Look, my teeth man(betrayer) arrived!\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 They held Yesu
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 47\~}
While Yesu was still speaking, Judas arrived who was one of the 12 following men. Many people were carrying clubs and the sharpening knife of both side came to him sent by the leading sacrifice burning people(chief priests) and the head people of Ju people. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 48\~}
Judas, teeth man(betrayer) let them know previously: \u8220?The man I kiss, he is the one. Arrest him!\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 49\~}
Judas went straightly to Yesu and said, \u8220?Good night, teaching man,\u8221? and kissed him.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 50\~}
Yesu answered him, \u8220?Do what you came for, friend!\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Then they arrested Yesu, and held him tight. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 51\~}
One of Yesu' disciples took hold of his sharp knife with both sides(sword). He hit the servant of the leader of the high people offering sacrifice(high priest) with it and he cut off his ear. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 52\~}
Yesu said to him, \u8220?Put your.p sharp knife with both sides back in its place. Who hold the sharp knife with both sides will die by the knife. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 53\~}
You should know that I could ask my Father God to help me. He would immediately send his 72,000 heavenly talk carrying men to fight for me. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 54\~}
They would save me. But then the things that God has said in the Bible about this would not happen. So, it must happen in this way.\u8217?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 55\~}
Yesu spoke to the crowd, \u8220?Why did you.p come with knife and clubs to capture me, like as I were an law breaking man? Every day I sat down and taught in the worshipping house place, and you.p did not arrest me. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 56\~}
But all this has happend in order to make come true for what the God's people who make know(prophets) wrote.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Then all the following men left him and ran away.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 They took Yesu before the Ju head men's meeting
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 57\~}
Those who had held Yesu took him to the big house of the high burning sacrifice man(high priest) Kayafas, where the teaching men of the law and the head people had gathered together. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 58\~}
Fit\u232? kept following him at a distance, when became close the house's place of the high burning sacrifice man(high priest). He went inside that place and sat down with the guarding men to see what will happen to Yesu. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 59\~}
The leading sacrifice burning people(chief priests) and all the Ju head men continued to find some lying talk against Yesu in order to put Yesu to death. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 60\~}
There many people came to and were telling lying talk about Yesu, but they could not find a reason to kill Yesu.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Finally two men stood {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 61\~}
and told this lying talk, \u8220?This man said, \u8216?I am able to destroy God's worshipping house and in three days build it and finished.\u8217?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 62\~}
The high burning sacrifice man(high priest) stood up and said to Yesu, \u8220?Why don't you.s say defending talk for yourself?\u8221? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 63\~}
But Yesu kept being quiet. Again the high burning sacrifice man(high priest) asked him, \u8220?In the name of the living God I now tell strong without.lying talk(oath): tell us if you.p are that Keriso, the Son of God.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 64\~}
Yesu answered him, \u8220?Yes! I am. What you.p say. But I tell all of you.p: from the present time that comes soon you.p will see the Son of Man will sit at the right side of the Almighty God and will come on the clouds of heaven!\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 65\~}
Immediately the high burning sacrifice man(high priest) tore his clothes and said, \u8220?He has spoken spoiling talk to God! We will not hear any watching people saying more! You have just heard his spoiling talk! {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 66\~}
What do you.p think?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 All the people answered, \u8220?He is evil, and we must put him to death.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 67\~}
Then some people are about to spit in his face and beat him with fists. And other people by flat hand {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 68\~}
and said, \u8220?Keriso! Show us that you are a prophet. Tell who hit you.s!\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fit\u232? denies Yesu
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 69\~}
Fit\u232? was sitting outside in the house place when one of without.payment working girl of the high burning sacrifice man came to him and said, \u8220?You are one of this, who were with Yesu of Galili region.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 70\~}
But he denied it in front of them all and answered, \u8220?I don't know what you.p are talking about." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 71\~}
And he went out to the entrance of the house place. Another without.payment working girl saw him there and said to the men, \u8220?He was with Yesu of Najaret.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 72\~}
Again Fit\u232? denied it and answered, \u8220?I tell the true talk that I don't know that man!\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 73\~}
Not long some men who were standing came to Fit\u232? and said, \u8220?Really you.p are one of them. You.s are speaking same as some man from Galili area!\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 74\~}
Then Fit\u232? said, \u8220?I really say strong talk(swear) that I am telling the true talk! May God put me punish if I am lying! I do not know that man!\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Immediately a chick crowed, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 75\~}
and Fit\u232? remembered what Yesu had told him, \u8220?You.s first will deny me three times, after this the chick crows.\u8221? He went out and started crying bitterly.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 27
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 They took Yesu to Failet
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
Early in the morning all the leading sacrifice burning people(chief priests) and the Ju people's leading people deciced and made a plan for Yesu to kill. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
They bound him, led him off, and gave him to Failet the Rom governor.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The death of Judas
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
When Judas, the man who gave teeth(betrayer), learned that Yesu will be put to death, he regreted in mind and took back the thirty silver coins to the leading sacrifice burning people(chief priests) and the leading people. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
He said, \u8220?I have done sins by giving teeth(betraying) an innocent man to death!\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 They answered him, \u8220?That is not our problem, but your.p problem!\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
Judas threw the coins to the land in the worshipping house and left them. Then he went away and hung himself with rope.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
The leading sacrifice burning people(chief priests) picked up the coins and said, \u8220?This money is payment for killing a man, and the law says that we should not put this money with the money of the temple\u8221? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
They decided about it, with this money they bought the field of the man who made clay pots to bury Side people. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
That is why that field is called \u8220?Field of Blood\u8221? to this very day.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
What the God's man who make know(prophet) Jeremaia had said came true: \u8220?They took 30 silver coins, in that measure the people of Israil had agreed to pay for him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
They put this money to buy the land of the man who made clay pots, as the Lord had commanded me.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Failet asked Yesu some questions
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
Yesu stood before the Rom governor, and governor asked Yesu, \u8220?Are you.s the king of the Ju people?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu answered, \u8220?You have said it." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
The leading priests and the leading men were speaking all kinds of talk against him. They said that he had done many bad things, but Yesu did not answer any.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
So Failet said to him, \u8220?Did you.p hear how many hatred talk they put on you.s?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
But Yesu refused answering, in this reason Failet was surprised.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Failet said Yesu must die
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
At every Passover festival the Rom governor was habitually setting free any one darkness house man(prisoner) who did the people ask for. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
At that time there was a well-known darkness house man(prisoner) name Yesu Barabas. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
So when the crowd gathered, Failet asked them, \u8220?Who is your.p favorite man for me will set free for you.p? Yesu Barabas or Yesu who called Keriso?\u8221? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
