"You.s were going to break down the worshipping house and build it again in three days! Save yourself if you.s are God's Son! Come down to the ground from the cross!\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 41\~}
In the same way the leading sacrifice burning people(chief priests) and the teaching men of the law and the leading people made talk(mocked) to him: {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 42\~}
\u8220?He saved other people, but he cannot save himself! He is the ruling man(king) of Israil! If he will come down to the ground from the cross now, we will truly approve(believe) him! {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 43\~}
He believes in God and said, "I am the Son of God." Let us see if God saves him now if he wants him!\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 44\~}
Even the thiefs who they nailed mocked him in the same way.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The death of Yesu
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 45\~}
At noon all the land became dark, this darkness carried until 3 o'clock. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 46\~}
At about three o'clock Yesu shouted with loud voice, \u8220?Eli, Eli, lama sabaktani?\u8221? this talk's meaning is, \u8220?My God, my God, why did you.p abandon me myself?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 47\~}
Some people who were standing close heard Yesu, and said, \u8220?He calls for Elaija!\u8221? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 48\~}
One man at once ran quickly, took a sponge. He soaked it in sour alcohol, tied it on the end of a stick, and lift it to Yesu to drink.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 49\~}
But the other people said, \u8220?Wait, let us see if Elaija is coming to save him!\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 50\~}
Yesu again shouted a very high voice and breathed his last and died.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 51\~}
At that moment, the thick clothes hanging in the worshipping house was torn in two from top to bottom. The ground shook, the rocks split apart, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 52\~}
and the graves were open, and God raised agian many God's people who had died to life. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 53\~}
They rose the graves, and after Yesu's rising, they went into the without.dust city, Jerusalem, where they appeared to many people.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 54\~}
