Among them were Meri Makdalin, Meri their mother of Jems and Josef, and the wife of Jefedi.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The burial of Yesu
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 57\~}
When it was evening, a rich man from Arimatia area, his name was Josef, and he was one of following man of Yesu. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 58\~}
He went to Failet and asked for the body of Yesu. Failet said to his soldiers, 'Give Yesu's body to Josef.' {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 59\~}
So Josef took it, wrapped it in a good white(clean) clothes, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 60\~}
and put it into his own new grave, which he dug into solid rock. Then he moved a large stone across the entrance to the grave and went away. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 61\~}
Meri Makdalin and the other Meri were sitting opposite the grave and watching.
