\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
Again Yesu began to teach beside of the lake. The crowd gathered around Yesu, [so] he got into a bout and sat in the bout out into the lake while all the people remained on outside of water. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
He taught them many things by parables, and in his teaching said: {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
"Listen! A farmer went out to plant the seed. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
As he was scattering the seed, some fell along the road, and the birds came and ate it. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
Some fell on the rocky ground where did not have a good soil. So it sprang up quickly, because the good soil was not in. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
But when the sun came up, the tree scorched, and they died because they have no root. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
Others fell on thorn's place, which tree grew up and choked the trees, so that they did not bear seed. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
Other seed fell on good ground. It came up and produced a crop, 30, 60, and even 100 times.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
Then Yesu said, "He who has ears to hear, let him hear"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
When he was alone, 12 and other people asked him about parables. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
He answered them, "The secret knowledge about the ruling of God was given to you. But to other people everything is said [in] parables {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
so that,
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 'These men may be seeing , but they will not see.
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 These men may be hearing, but they will not understand.
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 If they hear it, they turn to God and he(God) will wash their sins.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
Yesu said to them, "Don't you understand this parable? How do you understand other parables? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
The farmer plants the talk. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
Some people are like [that] men plant seed along the path, which talk is sown. As soon as they hear it, S\u225?if\u232?r comes and take away that was sown in them. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
Others like seed sown on rocky places, hear the talk and quickly receive with joy. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
But they have no root, their big mind(faith) are not long. When trouble or persecution comes because of the talk, they quickly fall away. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
Other, like seed sown into thorn place, hear the talk; {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
but he began to think of the world. Thinking of money and the desires for other things was growing. Therefore talk became to be without fruit. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
Others, like seed sown on good soil, hear the talk, accept it, and produce a crop-30, 60 and 100 times sown.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Light
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
Yesu said like that, "You don't bring in a lamp to put in a pot under a mat. But you put it on the table. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
Whatever cannot be hidden, therefore it will be brought into the open. What was in secret will be brought light. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
If you.s has ears, hear\u451?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
"Consider carefully what you hear\u451?" How do you treat to other people, like this will be treated to you-and even more. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
Whoever listen to my talk, more understaning will be given, but to whom doesn't hear, even what has little will be taken away from him
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The parable of the growing seed
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
Yesu also said, "The ruling of God is like. A man scatters seed to the ground. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
In night and day, [whether] he sleeps or gets up, the seed sprouts and grows, he does not know how to grow. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
All by himself the soil produce the grain-first the stalk, [then]the head, after the grain ripens. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
As the grain is ripe, then farmer harvest it to cut with bush knife.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The parable of little seed
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
Again he said, "How is the ruling of God? What parable shall we describe it? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
It's like little seed is scattered on the ground. This is a very little on the wide ground. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
But it is planted, [and it] will grow and become widely even be the largest of food plants. Its branches is possible that birds can make nest in its shade.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
Yesu said many parables to people, he taught to them to which they could understand. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
He did not teach them without parable. But when he was alone with his following men, he explained the meaning of it to them.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu calms the storm
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 35\~}
