\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu saved a man [who was] controlled by evil spirit
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
They went across the lake(swamp) to the land of Garasanes . {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
When Yesu got out of the bout, a man with evil spirit came from grave, he met him(Yesu). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
This man was sleeping in the grave, and no one [could] tie him and [no one] did it again with the other strong rope. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
They tried to tie him with a strong rope on the leg and the hand. But he was still cutting them and no helped him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
Night and day he was on the grave and the mountain, he was shouting and cutting his leg with stones.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
When that man saw Yesu far away, he came back to Yesu and knelt before him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
He shouted with his voice limitted, "Yesu, the son of the Most high God, what do you want from me? In the name of God, you don't cast me!" {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
Yesu said to him, "Come out of this man, you evil spirit!"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
Then Yesu answered him, "Who(what) is your name?" "My name is the plenty," he answered, "because we are plenty."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
He really wanted Yesu not to take them out of this place.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
They were feeding many pigs nearby mountain. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
The evil spirits asked Yesu, "Send us to the pigs, allow us to go into them." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
Yesu allowed evil spirit to come out and go into the pigs. Those herd of 2,000 pigs came out to the lake and all of them were drowned.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
Who look after the pigs ran and told this [in]the otherside of the town, people came to see what was happening. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
When they came to Yesu, they saw the man who was full of evil spirit, he was sitting down dressed the cloth and with good mind; and they were scared. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
Those who saw him told the people what was happening to the man controlled by evil spirit and told them about the pigs as well. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
The people asked Yesu to leave their place.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
