\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 41\~}
In every year his parents went to Jerusalem to the feast of Passover. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 42\~}
When he became 12 years old, they went there the feast according to custom. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 43\~}
After the feast [was over], his parents were coming back hometown, the boy Yesu stayed in Jerusalem, but they.d didn't know about child. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 44\~}
They were thinking that he might return trip together, [and] they went on for a day. They began looking for him among their relatives and to friends. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 45\~}
When they didn't find him, they went back to Jerusalem looking for him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 46\~}
After three days they found him in the worshipping house, sitting with the teaching men, listening to them and asking them questions. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 47\~}
Everyone who heard him they were amazed at his carrying bright thinking(undersanding) in his answers. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 48\~}
When his parents saw him, they were surprised. and his mother said, "Son, why are you doing like this to us? I with your father were painfully looking for you.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 49\~}
Yesu answered them, "Why were you looking for me? You should know that I am in my Father's house." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 50\~}
But they didn't understand what talk he was saying.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 51\~}
He went back to Najaret with parents and he became obedient man to the parents. But his mother accepted all talks in her heart. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 52\~}
Yesu grew in body and in wisdom and in favor with God and men.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 3
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Jon the Baptist prepared the way
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
When Tiberius Emperor ruled Rom 15 years, when Fontius Failet was governor of Judia, Erod was ruler in Galili region, Erod's small brother Filif was ruler in Itulia and Trakonitis, and Lisanias was ruler in Abilene, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
and at that time Anas and Kayafas were leading burning sacrifice men, God's talk came to Jon son of Jakaraya in the desert. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
He went through all the region of Joden, he preached about baptism and baptized to turn away from sins. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
How [someone] wrote it in the God's talk(is written in the talks of God/scripture), God's man who make know(prophet) Aisaya,
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 "Someone is shouting in the desert,
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 'To prepare the way for the Lord to travel,
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 making a straight paths for him.
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
Every valley shall be smooth,
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 and every montain shall be leveled and lowered.
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Every crooked roads shall be straight,
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 and the bad roads shall bestraighten.
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
And all people will see God's salvation.'"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
Jon said to the crowds which came to be baprtized by him, "You are the people with snack life\u451? Who told you (people) to flee from God's anger? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
You will do these things which you will show that you had turned from (your) sin. And do not try to say among youselves that, 'Ebraam is our ancester.' I tell you that out of these stones God can raise up children for Ebraam. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
The ax is ready to cut the root of the trees, and if which tree does not bear fruits will be cut and thrown into the fire."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
The crowd asked, "What shall we do from here?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
Jon answered, "If the man with two shirts must give it to other, and who has food must do the same way.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
Tax collectors came the same way to be baptized, they asked, "Teacher, what should we do?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
He told them, "Don't collect with your wanting from what had told to." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
Some soldiers also asked him, "What should we do?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 He answered, "Don't steal money from people and accuse them with lying and be content with your pay.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
The people were waiting with saying and were all wondering in their hearts that Jon might be the Keriso. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
Jon answered them all, "I baptize you with water. But one who is coming whose power surpasses me, I cannot untie the thongs of his sandols. He will baptize you with the God Spirit and with fire. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
He is ready to divide chaffs from the fruitful seeds with fork. Then he will sweep the place, will gather fruitful seeds into his house, but he will burn chaffs into the without-end fire. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
And with many other talks Jon advised them and preached the good talk to them.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
But when Jon rebuked the ruler Erod because of Erodias, his young brother's wife, and the other evil things he did, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
Erod added this to them. He put Jon to the darkness house(darkness house).
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The Baptism of Yesu
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
When he baptized all the people, he also baptized Yesu. When he was talking with God, heaven was opened, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
and the God Spirit came down to Yesu with a through bird like a mamu(pigeon). A voice came from heaven, "You are my lovely son, I'm so pleased with you."
