for the forty days Saif\u232? tempted him. He did not eat during these days, after that he was hungry.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
S\u225?if\u232?r said, "If you are God's son, turn this stone into the food."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
Yesu answered, "It is written in the God's talk, 'Man shall not live by food alone.'
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
S\u225?if\u232?r led him to the mountain and showed him all the world. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
S\u225?if\u232?r said to him, "I will give you all the authority and good things, for [these] are mine, I will give it to anyone I want. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
If you worship me, all will be yours."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
Yesu answered, "It is written in the God's talk, 'Worship your Lord God and serve him only.'" {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
S\u225?if\u232?r led him to Jerusalem and had him stand on the highest point of the worshipping house. He said, "If you are the son of God, jump to the land from here." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
It is written in the talk of God that,
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 "He will send men carrying heavenly message(angels) to guard you,
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
they will hold you with their hands
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 so that your foot will not be hurt on a stone.'
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
Yesu answered, "It says that, you don't put your Lord God into the test.'"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
When S\u225?if\u232?r finished his temptation, he left Yesu until other day.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 They rejected Yesu at Najaret
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
Yesu went back to Galili region with the power of God Spirit, talk about him became wide through the whole area. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
He taught them through their meeting houses(meeting houses), and every people praised him.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
He went to Najaret, where he grew up, on the sabbath he went and entered into the meeting house as his custom was. He stood up to read. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
They gave him the scroll book of the God's man who make know(prophet) Aisaya. He unrolled it[scroll] and he found the talks[it is] written,
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
"The Spirit of the Lord is on me, because he anointed me to teach good talk to the poor. He sent me to speak one who put in the darkness house saving, the blind will see, people with problem will be light {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
In this year the Lord's wanting happen."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
Then he rolled up the scroll, gave it back to the meeting house keeper and sat down in the teaching place. Everyone's eyes in the worshipping house was looking at him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
He began to say to them, "Today this talk become true in your hearing.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
