Erod's household mananger Kusa, his wife Joana, Susana and many other women. These women helped them with their things.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
While a large crowd was gathering to Yesu from different towns, he preached parable:
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
"A farmer went out to sow his seed. When he scattered the seed, some fell along the road, it was trampled on, and the birds ate it. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
Some seed fell on the land with stones, when it came up, it died because there is no water(moisture). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
Other seed fell among the thorns place which it grew up with thorns and choked it. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
Other seed fell on good land. It grew and produced a crop 100 times more than was sorn. When he talked this, he said, "He who has ears to hear, he will hear."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
His following men asked him what is meaning of this parable. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
He said, "God is showing to you what he did not show before about ruling of God, but I am speaking to other people with parables, so that,
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The eye will see, but they may not find,
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 they will hear, but they may not understand.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
The meaning of parable is this: The seed is the talk of God. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
Those along the road are ones who hear, and then devil comes and steals [the talk] from their hearts, so that they may not truly approve(believe) and not be saved. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
Those on the land with stone are ones who receive the talk with joy when they hear it, but they have no root. Their big mind(faith) is not long, but in the time of testing they fall away. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
Which seeds fell among the thorns place, they stand for those who hear, but they expect/think/worry about many things to become rich in their life and their big mind(faith) do not grow strong. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
But which seeds on good land stands for those with a good and true heart, who hear the talk, they endure and put it practice and produce other seeds."
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Parable of a light
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
"People don't put lamp in the pot or put under the basket. But he will put on the table. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
What is hidden will be found, and what is secret will be put out the sight. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
Pay attention to how you listen. Whoever have something will be given more, but whoever does not have, and they think that mine are enough will lose."
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu' mother and his younger brothers
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
Yesu's his mother and his younger brothers came to see him, but because there are many people, they can't come to close to him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
Someone told him, "Your mother and your younger brothers are standing outside, waiting to see you."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
He answered, "My mother and younger brothers are those who hear God's talk and put it action."
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu calms big wind(storm)
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
One day Yesu said to his following men, "Let's go to theh lake and pass over to the other side." So they got into the bout and went. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
As they started, Yesu fell asleep. Big wind blew in the lake, so bout almost was sink, they were in the big problem.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
The following men went and woke him, shouted, "Lord, Lord, we're going to drown!"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 He woke up and rebuked the wind and waves. Immediately big wind stopped [and] all became calm. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
He said to his following men, "Where is your big mind(faith)?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The following men came to fear and amazement, they said themselves, "Who is he? When he speak to wind and waves, [they] obey him!"
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu healed man with evil spirit
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
They arrived at the region of Gerasenes, which is across from the Galili region. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
When Yesu stepped out, a man with evil spirit met him. For the long time this man had not worn clothes and didn't stay in the house, but in the grave place. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
When he saw Yesu, he shouted and fell at his feet, shouted loudly, "What do you want with me, Yesu, Son of the Most High God? I beg you, don't curse me!" {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
For Yesu said evil spirit to go out of the man. Many times evil spirits attacked him and people bound with chains on his hand and legs and was under the guard, [but]he broke the chain and evil spirit drove him into the clear places.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
Yesu asked him, "Who(What) is your name?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 He answered, "Many" because many evil spirits had come into him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
And they begged him repeatedly not to order that, 'We will not go to into the never ending hold.'
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
A large herd of pigs was feeding on the mountainside. Evil spirits begged Yesu to let them go into them, and he gave them power(permission). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
When evil spirits came out of the man, they went to the pigs, and they rushed down steep bank to the lake and was drowned.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
When the men looking for the pigs saw what had happened, they ran off and told this in the town and contryside. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 35\~}
And they came to see what had happened. When they came to Yesu, they found the man from whom evil spirits had gone out, staying at Yesu's feet. And he dressed and was with the straight mind. But they were afraid. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 36\~}
Those who had seen it told to the people how evil spirit possessed man had been became good(healed). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 37\~}
All the people from the Gerasanes begged Yesu to leave them, because they were full of fear. So they got into the bout to leave.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 38\~}
That man from whom the evil spirits gone out, he begged Yesu to go with him, but Yesu sent him with talk that, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 39\~}
"Return to the village and tell how much God has done for you." So the man went away and told through the city how much Yesu had done for him.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 A dead girl and a sick woman
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 40\~}
When Yesu went back, a crowd welcomed, because they were waiting for him with expecting. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 41\~}
The man name Jairus, a meeting house head man came and fell at Yesu's feet, begged him to go to his house {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 42\~}
because his only daughter, [a girl] 12 years old was dying.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 When Yesu was on the way, the crowds packed tightly around him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 43\~}
And a woman was there who had been bleeding for 12 years, but no one heal her. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 44\~}
She came him from backside and touched the edge of Yesu's clothes that time her bleeding stopped. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 45\~}
Yesu asked, "Who touched me?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 When they all denied it, Fit\u232? said, "Lord, the crowd are surrounding and pressing you."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 46\~}
But Yesu said, "Someone has touched me. I know [my]power has gone out from me."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 47\~}
When the woman came without watching man and without notice, she had a fear and knelt down at his feet. In front of all the people, she told why she had touched him and how she had been healed at once. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 48\~}
Then Yesu said to her, "Daughter, your big mind(faith) has healed you. Go in peace."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 49\~}
While Yesu was still speaking, someone came from house of Jairus, who was meeting house head man. He said, "Your daughter has died. Don't bother the teaching man anymore." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 50\~}
When Yesu heard this, he said to Jairus, "Don't be afraid. Believe and she will be good." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 51\~}
When he arrived at the Jairus' house, he didn't permit anyone to go with him except Fit\u232?, Jon and Jems and her father and her mother. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 52\~}
While all the people were crying and shouted with sadness for her(moured for her). Yesu said, "Don't cry, she is not dead but asleep." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 53\~}
They laughed at him because she was dead. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 54\~}
But he took her by the hand and said, "My child, get up!" {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 55\~}
Her spirit returned, immediately she stood up. Then Yesu told them to give the food. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 56\~}
Her parents were surprised, but he ordered them not to report [anyone] what had happened.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 9
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu sent out 12 following men
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
One day Yesu called his 12 following men together and he gave them power and authority to cast out evil spirits and to heal diseases. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
And he sent them to preach about ruling of God and to heal the sick. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
He told them, "Don't take anything in journey- no staff, no bag, no food, no money, no extra clothes. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
Which house you enter, stay in there until you leave that town. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
If people do not welcome you, shake the dust from your feet, must leave their town, [as] a it will be warning to them as God's punishement comes because they rejected his talk. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
So they left and went from the village to the village, proclaiming God's good talk and healing people in every places.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
Erod the ruler heard [about] all what was happening. And he worried because some were saying, 'This is Jon who had been raised from the dead,' {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
other people thought, 'Elaija appeared,' and other people thought that one of the God's people who make know(prophets) of long ago had come back to life. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
But Erod said, "I had Jon's head cut off. Who is this I hear many talks about him?" And he wanted to see Yesu.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu fed 5,000 people
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
When the men with Yesu's authority(apostles) returned, they told to Yesu what they had done. He took them and they went to rest to the town called Betsaida. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
But many people knew about it and followed him. He welcomed them and spoke to them about the ruling of God and healed them who needed healing.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
Late in the afternoon 12 following men came to him and said, "Send the crowd, they will go back to the close village and countryside in order to find food and sleeping place, because we came in remote place here.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
He answered to them, "You(plural) give them something to eat."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 They answered, "We have 5 bread loaves and two fish, if we want to feed these people, we will [have to] go and buy their food." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
There were about(?) 5,000 men. But he said to his following men, "Have them sit down groups make about(?) 50 each." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
So following men did, and all the people sat down. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
Yesu took 5 breads and two fish, and looked up the heaven, gave thanks and broke them. Then he handed them to the following men to give to the people.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
All the people ate [and] were satisfied, and the following men picked up 12 basketfuls of broken pieces which were left over.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fit\u232? said clearly that Yesu is the Keriso
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
One day Yesu left the crowd for talking with God alone and his diciples were with him, he asked them, "Who do people say I am?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
They answered, "Some say Jon the baptist, other people say Elaija, but other people say one of God's man who make know(prophet) of long ago has come back to life."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
He asked them, "But what about you? Who do you say I am?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fit\u232? answered, "God's Keriso."
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu spoke about his death
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
Yesu strictly warned them not to tell about this to anyone. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
And he said, "The Son of Man must suffer many things and the head people, the leading sacrifice burning people(high priests) and the teaching men of the law rejected him, and they surely kill and after the three day he will rise to life."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
Then he said to them all: "Whoever start to follow me, they must deny themselves and take their cross every day and follow me. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
Whoever wants to save his life will lose it, but whoever loses his life because of me will save it. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
And how good is it someone to gain the whole world, but lose or destroy themselves? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
Whoever is with shame about me and my talk, the Son of Man will be with shame of him when he comes back in his strong light(big light) and in the big light(glory) of his Father and of the without.dust(holy) men carrying heavenly message(angels). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
I tell you the truth, some who are standing here, they will see the ruling of God before they will die."
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Three following men saw Yesu's big light(glory)
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
8 days later Yesu took Fit\u232?, Jon and Jems with him [and] went [up] on a mountain to talk with God. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
While he was talking with God, his face changed [its appearance], and his clothes became like as bright as lightening. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
Two men, Moses a Elaija, appeared with big light(glory), [and they] talked with Yesu. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
They spoke about his journey, which he would fulfill God's wanting by dying in Jerusalem. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
Fit\u232? and his group were very sleepy, but when they woke up, they saw his big light(glory) and two men standing with him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
As Moses and Eliaja were about to leave Yesu, Fit\u232? said to him, "Lord, it looks good we are here with you. We will make three house, one for you, one for Moses and for Elaija." He didn't know what he said.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
While he was speaking, a cloud appeared and covered them, and they were afraid when they entered the cloud. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 35\~}
A voice came from the cloud, said, "This is my son, whom I have chosen, listen to him." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 36\~}
When talk finished, they saw Yesu alone. They did not tell anyone at that time what they saw.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu Healed a child with evil spirit
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 37\~}
The next day, when they came back from the mountain, a large crowd met him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 38\~}
A man cried out from the crowd, "Teacher, I beg you to look at my son, because he is my only child. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 39\~}
The evil spirit attacked him with a sudden shout, he throws him make strict and make him to foam at the mouth. The evil spirit does not leave and kept on destroying him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 40\~}
I begged your following men to drive it out, but they are impossible [to do]."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 41\~}
Yesu answered, "You without big mind(faith) and without hearing people, how long must I stay with you and endure you? Bring your son here."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 42\~}
While the child was coming, the evil spirit threw him to the ground twisting. But Yesu rebuked the evil spirit, healed the child and gave him back to his father. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 43\~}
And they were amazed at God's big things doing.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu spoke about his death a second time
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 While all the people were amazed and they said Yesu's action doing, he said to his following men, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 44\~}
"Listen carefully to what I am about to tell you. The Son of Man is going to be gave teeth(betrayed) into the hands of men." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 45\~}
But they did not understand what is meaning. Because it was secret to them, they did not know it, and they were afraid to ask him about it.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Who will be big
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 46\~}
His following men were arguing who will be big. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 47\~}
But Yesu knew their thoughts, so he had a little child stand there beside him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 48\~}
Then he said to them, "Whoever welcomes this little child in my name welcomes me, and whoever welcomes me welcomes the one who sent me. Who is little among all of you, he is big."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 49\~}
Jon said, "Lord, we saw the man driving out evil spirits in your name and we tried to stop him, because he is not one of us."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 50\~}
Yesu said, "Don't stop him because whoever is not against us, he is for us."
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Samaria people rejected Yesu
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 51\~}
Yesu's day became close to go back to the heaven, Yesu strongly decided to travel to Jerusalem. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 52\~}
He sent messengers on ahead, who went to a Samaria village to prepare things for him, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 53\~}
but the people there did not welcome him, because he was going to Jerusalem. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 54\~}
When the following men Jems and Jon saw this, they asked, "Lord, do you want us to shout to the heaven fire down to destroy them?" {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 55\~}
But Yesu turned and rebuked them. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 56\~}
And they went to another village.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Real following men/followers of Yesu
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 57\~}
As they were walking along the road, a man said to Yesu, "I will follow you wherever you go."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 58\~}
Yesu answered, "Wild dogs have holes and birds have nests, but the Son of Man has no place to sleep and to rest."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 59\~}
He said to another man, "Follow me."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 But man answered, "Lord, first I will go back to home. After my father dies I will bury him, after I will foloow you."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 60\~}
Yesu said to him, "Those who are spiritually dead will bury the dead, but you go and proclaim talk of the ruling of God."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 61\~}
Another still said, "I will follow you, Lord, but first let me go back to my family to say goodbye."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 62\~}
Yesu answered, "Anyone who starts to work to plow and looks back, he is not able to work for the ruling of God."
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 10
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu sent out 72 following men
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
After this the Lord chose 72 other following men and sent them two by two to every town and place where he wanted to go. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
He told them, "Harvest season original food are ready to Dig are many but workers are few. Therefore ask the Lord of the harvest in the harvesting season, to send out workers into the origin food field. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
Go! I am sending you out like helpless baby sheeps(lambs) among wild dogs. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
Do not take money bag and traveling bag. Do not take other sandols, do not [spend] long [time] to greet with people on the road.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
When you enter a house first say, 'Blessed to this house.' {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
If this blessing is [with] man there, your blessing will rest on him, if not, it will return to you. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
Stay that house, eating and drinking whatever they give you, because workers should take their pay. Do not move around from house to house.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
When you enter a town and are welcomed, eat what is ready to you. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
Heal the sick who are there and tell them that, 'The ruling of God is near to you.' {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
But when you enter a town and they don't welcome you(are not welcomed), go into the road and say, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
'We wipe the dust of your town [that] stick to our fee, we give warning to you. But remember about this: The ruling of God has been near.' {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
I tell you, it comes little on the judging day for Sodom, but there will be very high judgement in that town.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
How bad will be to you, Korasin! How bad will be to you, Betsaida! For if the special workings(miracles) were did to you had been did in Taire and Sidon, they would have turn away long ago, sitting with sackcloth and ashes. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
On the judgement day Taire and Sidon, their punishment will be very big, but your.p punishment will surpass their punishment. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
And you, Kapenam, will you lift to the heaven? No, you will go down to never ending hole(hell).
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
Yesu said to his following men, "Whoever listens to you, he listens to me, but whoever rejects you, he rejects me, but whoever rejects me, he rejects him who sent me."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
72 following men returned with joy and they told, "Lord, even evil spirits obeyed us in your name."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
Yesu answered, "I saw S\u225?if\u232?r fall like lightening from heaven. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
Listen, I gave you authority to step on snakes and scopions and to overcome the power of the enemy, anything will not hurt you. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
But do not rejoice because evil spirit submit you, but it is joy for you because your name are written in heaven."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
At that day the God Spirit filled with joy to Yesu and he(Yesu) said, "I praise you, Father, Lord of heaven and earth, because you have hidden these things from the wise and intelligent, but revealed them to without-knowledge/intelligent men like children. Yes, Father, this was with your good blessing.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
My Father has given me all things. No one knows the Son only the Father [knows], and no one knows who the Father is only Son [knows] and those to whom the Son chooses to reveal him."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
Then Yesu turned to his following men and said privately, "Blessed are them who see what you see. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
For I tell you that many God's people who make know(prophets) and ruling men(kings) wanted to see what you see, but they didn't see, and to hear what you hear but didn't hear it."
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The parable of the good Samari man
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
One day a teaching man of the law stood up to test Yesu and asked, "Teacher, what I must to do to receive the eternal life?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
