\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
He answered, "'Love the Lord your God with all your heart, with all your spirit, with all your power and with all your mind' and 'Love your neighbor like as yourself how do you love.'"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
Yesu answered, "Correct, do this and you will live."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
But he wanted to justify himself, so he asked Yesu, "And who is my neighbor?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
Yesu answered, "A man went to from Jerusalem to Jeriko, on the road robbers attacked him. They stripped him of clothes, beat him and leave him almost died and went away, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
A burning sacrifice men was going that road but when he saw the man, he passed by through the other side. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
Like this a man belong to Lefi family came and saw him, passed by the outside. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
But Samari man was going like as, when he saw half dead [man] and he felt pity for him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
He went to him, painted on olive oil and alcohol, bandaged wounds. Then he put him on his donkey and brought him to an inn and looked after him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 35\~}
The next day he gave two silver coins them to the house manager. He said, 'Look after him, when I return, if you use many money, I will pay you.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 36\~}
Which of these three do you think become a neighbor to the man who was striked by robbers?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 37\~}
The teaching man of the law answered, "The man who had mercy to him."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu told him, "Go and do like this."
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Mata and Meri
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 38\~}
Yesu and his following men were on the way, they arrived to the village, woman name Mata welcomed Yesu to her house. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 39\~}
Mata's small sister name Meri who sat the Lord's feet listening to what he said. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 40\~}
But Mata worried about her many works. So Mata came to Yesu and asked, "Lord, you know Meri has left me to do the work by myself? Tell her to help me!" {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 41\~}
The Lord answered, "Mata, Mata, you are worried and made a trouble to mind about many things, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 42\~}
but one thing is necessary. Meri has chosen what is good, and it will not be taken way from her."
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 11
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Talking with God(Prayer)
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
One day Yesu was talking with God in a different/certain place. When he finished, one of his following men said to him, "Lord, teach us to talk with God, just as Jon taught his following men." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
Yesu said to them, "When you talk with God, say like:
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Father,
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Be honored your without.dust(holy) name,
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 your kingdom will come.
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
Will give us food in every day.
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
Forget us our sins,
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 because we forget their sins those who did against us.
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 And do not bring us in temptation."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
Then Yesu said to them, "If one [of you] have a friend, and you should go to him at midnight and say, 'Friend, give me three loaves of flaw\u232?, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
because my friend has come to me from long distance, and I have no [food] to prepare for him!'
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
Who was inside answered, 'Don't bother me. The door is already locked, my children and I went to sleep. I can't get up and give you.' {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
I tell you, if he will not get up and give a bread because you are his friend, but he will get up and give you all what you need, you are not shame because you continue to ask him.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
So I say to you: Ask and it will be given to you; seek and you will find; knock and the door wll be opened to you. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
Because every people who ask will receive, every people seek will find; the one who knocks, the door will be opened.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
You father, if your child asks for fish, will you give him a snake, is it possible? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
Or if he asked an egg, what will you give him a scorpion? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
So even though you are evil, you know [how]to give good things to your child. How much more good will your Father in heaven give the God Spirit to those who beg him!"
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu a Beljebab
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
One day Yesu drove out a evil spirit from mute man, and when evil spirit left, the man who was mute began to speak. The crowd was surprised. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
But some of them said, "By name of Beljebab, the head man of evil spirit, Yesu is driving our evil spirits." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
Others tested Yesu [and] they asked asking talk doing somethings from heaven.
