\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Turn away or die
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
At that day some people were there who told Yesu about the Galili region people whose blood Failet mixed with their sacrifices. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
Yesu answered, "How do you think those Galillans' sin which they did surpass the sins that other men from Galili region did, that's why they saw pains this way? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
I tell you, no! But If you don't turn away to God, all of you will die. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
Or those 18 who die when tower of Siloam fell to them, what do you think their sin surpass of the other men who were in Jerusalem? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
I tell you, No! But if you don't turn away to God, all of you will die way."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
Then he told this parable, "A man have a fruit tree growing in his garden, and went to take fruit, but he find none. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
So he said the man who looked after the garden, 'For three years now I have been coming to take fruit on the fruit tree, but I haven't found any. Cut it down! Why should it grow and eat the land? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
The man answered, 'Lord, Leave it alone for one more year, and I will dig around it and fertilize it. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
If it bears fruit next year, good! If not, cut it down.'"
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Crippled woman was healed on the Safat
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
One Safat Yesu was teaching in one of meeting houses, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
and a woman was there who had been crippled by evil spirit for 18 years. She was bent over and can't straighten up. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
When Yesu saw her, he called her and said, "Woman, you are good." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
Then Yesu put his hands on her, and immediately she straighten up and praised God!
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
The meeting house head man was angry because Yesu healed her on the Safat, he said to the people, "There are 6 days for working. So come to heal on those days, not on the Safat."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
The Lord answered him, "You liar! You always untie cow and donkey from the stall and lead it out to give it water on the Safat. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
Then this woman, a daughter of Ebraam, whom S\u225?if\u232?r has kept to bound for 18 years. She should be saved on the Safat from what bound her."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
When Yesu said this, his enemies was full of shame, but the people rejoiced what Yesu did good.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Parables of the small seed and the Yeast
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
Then Yesu asked, "How is like the ruling of God? What shall I compare it to? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
[It is] like small seed, a man took and planted in his garden and grew and became a tree, and the birds make nest in this branches."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
Again Yesu asked, "What shall I compare the ruling of God to? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
It is like yeast a woman took and mixed into 3 bags of flour. So all the flour rises [and] become big dough."
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The narrow door
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
When Yesu went to Jerusalem, he taught them through the town and village. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
Someone asked Yesu, "Lord, are only a few people possible to be saved?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 He said to them, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
"Work hard in order that you will enter small door, because I tell you, many people will try to enter and will not happen. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
When house owner will get up and will close the door, you will stand outside, knocked and said, "Lord, open the door for us.'
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 But he will answer, 'I don't know you or where you come from?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
Then you will say, 'We ate and drank with you, and you taught us on the roads.'
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
Then he will answer, 'I don't know you or where you come from. Get away from me, all of you evil doing people!
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
There will be weeping and gnashing of teeth, when you see Ebraam, Aisak and Jeikof and all the God's people who make know(prophets) in the ruling of God, but you are thrown. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
People will come from east and west and north and south, and will take their places there at the feast in the ruling of God. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
Who are last they will be first, who are first they will be last.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu' sorry for Jerusalem
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
At that time some Farasi men came to Yesu and said to him, "Leave this place and go the other place. Erod wants to kill you."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
He answered, "Go tell that small wild dog(fox), 'I will cast out evil spirit, and heal people today and tomorrow, and on the third day I will finish my work.' {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
But I must keep on going today and tomorrow and next day, any God's man who make know(prophet) cannot die outside of Jerusalem!
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
"O Jerusalem, Jerusalem, you who kill the God's people who make know(prophets) and strike whom sent to them by stone, I wanted to gather your people, like as hen gather her chicks under her wings, but you did not want it! {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 35\~}
Look, your city will be left. I tell you, you will not see me again until you say, 'Blessed is the one who comes in the name of the Lord!"
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 14
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu at a Parasi men's house
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
One Safat, when Yesu went to eat in the house of respected Farasi men, the people were watching him very close. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
There was a man whose arms and legs were swollen came to Yesu. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
Yesu asked Farasi men and the teaching men of the law, "What is lawful to heal on the Safat or not?" {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
But they remained silent. Yesu took man and healed him and sent him.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
Yesu asked them, "If one of you has child or cow fallen into a well on the Safat, will you not rush to get it out? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
And they didn't say any talk.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
When he noticed the guests chose the good place at the table, he told them this parable: {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
"When someone invites you to a wedding feast, don't take a high place. May it not be that that place is already reserved for a man that he has invited who has a high reputation & surpasses you.s {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
If he did, one who invited you will come and say to you, 'Give this person your place.' How he is shameful, you should take last place. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
But when you are invited, take low place, [so that]when your host comes, he will say to you, 'Friend, move up to high place.' You will be honored in front of the guests. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
Those who make themselves big will come down low, those who come down themselves will go up high."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
Then Yesu said to his host, "When you give a lunch or dinner, you don't invite your friends and brothers and relatives or the rich friends, if you do, you will be invited and will be repaid. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
But when you give a food [banquet], invite the poor, the crippled, the lame, [and] the blind. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
They cannot repay you. But God will bless you and repay when his people rise from death.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Parable about big feast
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
After Yesu finished teaching, one of guests said, "Blessed is the one who will eat at the feast in the ruling of God!"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
Yesu answered, "A man prepared a big feast and invited many guests. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
On the feast day, he sent his workers to tell those who had been invited, "Come, everything is now ready.'
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
But they began to make excusing talk. The first man said, 'I have bought a field, and I will go to see it. Excuse me.'"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
Another said, "I have bought 5 cows, and I'm on the way to try them out. Excuse me.'
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
Still another said, 'I just got married, so I can't come.'
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
The workers returned and told to his master. Then house's owner became angry and ordered his workers, 'Go out quickly small roads and ouside/bush roads in the town and bring the poor, the crippled, the blind, and the lame.'
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
The worker said, 'Lord, what you said has been done, but there are still place(room).'
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
Then the master told his workers, 'Go out to small roads and bush roads and demand strong them 'Come in,' so that my house will be full. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
I tell you, those who were invited first will not get taste of my food(banquet)'"
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Being a following man
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
A large crowd went with Yesu, and he turned them and said to them. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
"If anyone comes to me to be my following man, he should love me a lot, secondly he should love father and mother, wife and children, brothers and sisters, yes, even his life. If not, he cannot be my following man. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
And if anyone who don't carry his cross and follow me and he can't be my following man.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
"If the man who wants to build a big house, he will sit first and estimate and see how much money to finish it. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
He will start to build the house, but he cannot finish. So every people [who]see what he does will make fun of him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
They will say, "This man began to build but could not finish."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
What king will do if he has 10,000 soldiers could defend himself against a king who is about to attack him with 20,000 soldiers? Before he goes out to battle, he should first sit down and decide if he can win? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
If he is not able to, he send messanger while other is still a long way and he will asked terms of peace. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
Like this way, you leave everything, you will be my following man.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
Salt is good, but if its flavor is finished, how can it be made to taste salty again? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 35\~}
It is not good for the soil or for anything, [so]people throw it out.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Whoever has ears, he must hear this talk."
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 15
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The lost sheep
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
The tax collectos and sinners were all gathering to hear him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
But Farasi men and teaching men of the law began to gramble, "This man welcomes sinner to eat with them."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
Then Yesu told them this prarble, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
"If one man has 100 sheep and loses one, what does he do? He surely leave 99 in open place and go to find lost sheep until he finds. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
When he finds it, he is happy, [and] put it on his shoulder. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
He will go the house. Then he called his friends and his neighbors and told them, "Rejoice with me. I have found my lost sheep." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
I say to you.p, in heaven the same kind of big happiness will happen when a sinner turns away. Truly the rejoicing about 99 straight men who have no sin, it is very little, but the rejoicing about one sinner who turns away will be very big.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The lost coin
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
"What will a woman do if she has ten silver coins and loses one. She surely lights a lamp and begens to sweep the house [and] looks carefully until she finds it. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
Then when she find it, she calls friends and neighbors and told to them, "Make a feast with me, I have found my lost coin." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
I said to you in the same way there is rejoicing in the front of the men carrying heavenly message(angels) of God when one sinner who turns away
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The lost son
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
Yesu began to say again, "There was a man with two sons. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
The younger son said to his father, 'Father, I will not wait until you die. Now give me your things what will belong to me.' Then he divided things(property)between his two sons.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
So not a long later, the younger took his [things] what had, packed up and went to long country and began to waste money in bad living. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
After this when ran out everything, there was famine in the land, so he began to feel starving. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
So he went to work and asked to a man in that land, and the man sent him to feed pigs. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
He was very hungry, he want to eat pigs' food. But no one who gave him anything.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
When he came back to thought, he said, 'All of my father's workers have enough food, and here I am dying! {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
I will go back to my father and say, "Father, I had sinned to the heaven and you. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
I am not enough to be called your son; treat me like your worker. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
So he stood up and went to his father.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 But while he was still a long way, his father saw him and full of mercy for him; he ran to his son and hugged him and kissed him.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
The son said to his father, 'Father, I had sinned to the heaven and you. So I can't be called your son.' {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
But his father said to his workers, 'Hurry! Bring new clothes and put it on him. Get a ring for his finger and sandols on his feet. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
Bring the fattened cow and kill it. Let's make feast and rejoice, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
for this son of mine who was dead and now he is alive; He was lost and now he has been found.' So they rejoiced.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
At that time, the first son was in the field. When he came close the house, he heard singing sound and dancing. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
So he called one of the workers and asked him what was happening. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
He answered, 'Your small brother has arrived, and your father has killed fattened cow because he is here and is good.' {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
So first born son became angry and would't go into the house. His father came out and begged him to enter. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
But he answered his father, 'Look! All years I have worked for you and have never disobeyed your talk. But you didn't give us to young goat in order that we will do feast with friends. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
But when this your son who wasted your money in bad living [and] come back to the house, you killed the fattened cow for him!
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
His father said, "My son, you are always with me. Everything I have is yours. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
But we celebrate and rejoice because your younger brother was dead and now is alive. He was lost and now is here."
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 16
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The clever manager
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
Yesu told his following men, "A rich man chose a man to look after his things. But the rich man was told that his manager had wasted your money. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
So he called him and asked him, "What is this I heard about you? Give me knowledge(report) about your work how did you look after, because you cannot be manager after this."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
The manager said to himself, 'What shall I do now? My master is taking away my work. I'm not strong to dig, and I am shame to beg. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
I know what shall I do so that people will continue to welcome me into their houses when I lost my work'
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
So he called one by one his master's people to pay back. He asked the first man, 'How much pay do you put my master's? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
He answered, '20 drums of olive oil.' Manager told him, 'Take your paper, sit down quickly, and write 10 drums.'
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
He asked again the second man, 'How much is to you? He answered, '1,000 flaw\u232? bags .' He told him, 'Take your paper. Write 800 flaw\u232? bags.'
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
The master praised his dishonest manager because he deal with well. The people of this world deal well but the people of the light are not like them. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
I tell you, become friend for yourself with worldly things. When it is gone, you will be welcomed into an eternal village.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
Whoever is faithful in small things, he is also [faithful]in large things. Whoever lies in little things, he is also[lying] in large things. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
So if you are not true(faithful) to manage worldy things, how will be true(faithful) with true riches? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
And you are not true to manage someone's things, who will give you your own things?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
A worker cannot stay under two owners ruling. He will hate the one and love the other. You will obey to the one and deny the other. Therefore you cannot stay under two ruling, God and money.'
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
The Farasi men are money lovers. When they heard this talk and made fun of Yesu. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
Yesu said to them, "You are ones who make yourselves look good in the eyes of people, but God knows your heart. What is value highly to people's thought is without.meaning to God's sight.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
Moses' law and God's people who make know(prophets)' teaching were proclaimed until Jon's day. From that time, the good talk about the ruling of God started to preach, every people is trying to get in to the ruling of God. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
Heaven and earth will disapper, but little talk in God's talk will not remove.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
Anyone who divorces his wife and marries another man commits adultery and man who marries a divorced woman commits adultery.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The rich and Lajarus
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
There was a rich man who wore very good clothes and lived in good every day. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
At the gate of his house there was a beggar name Lajarus who was with sores, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
and wanted to eat what fell from the rich man's table. At that times the dogs came and licked his sores.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
The begger died and men carrying heavenly message(angels) took him there to Ebraam. So the rich man died and was buried. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
In the without-sun hole(hell), the rich was suffering, when he looked up and saw Ebraam far off, with Lajarus by his side. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
So he cried out, 'Father Ebraam, have pity on me and send Lajarus to dip his hand in water and become cool my tongue, because I am suffering in this fire.'
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
But Ebraam answered, 'Son, remember there your living days(lifetime), you lived in good [things], while Lajarus had nothing, but now he is resting here and you are suffering. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
Another reason, it is impossible because big hole seperate between us, anyone who want to cross from here to you are difficult.'
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
He answered, 'Then I beg you, father, send Lajarus there to my father's house, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
because I have 5 small brothers. Let them know they will not come to this suffering place.'
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
Ebraam answered, 'There are books Moses and the God's people who make know(prophets) wrote, they should listen/obey to them.'
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
He said, 'No, father Ebraam, if the dead returns to them, they will turn away.'
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
He said to him, 'If they do not listen/obey to Moses and the God's people who make know(prophets), they will not turn away also same way if someone returns from the dead to life.'"
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 17
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Teaching about forgetting(washedess) and Faith
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
Yesu said to his following men, "Which things always cause people to sin, but[how] painful to this person whom people cause. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
To tie the person a big stone around neck and throw into the sea, even this would be a small heavy for you.s. But Who cause this children to sin, your.s heavy would be big. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
So watch yourselves.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 "If your big brother do sins, correct him, and if he turn away, wash him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
If he do sins against you 7 times in a day and 7 times come back again to you and saying, 'I had turn away,' you wash them."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
The men with Yesu's authority(apostles) said to the Lord, "Lord, add our big mind(faith)!"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
Yesu answered, "If your big mind(faith) is like a small seed, you can say to this big tree, 'be uprootes and planted in the sea,' and it will obey you.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
If your worker comes back from plowing or from looking after the sheep. Will master say, 'Come [and] sit down to eat.'? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
But he will say, 'Cook my food, and get ready and wait on me while I eat. After that you may eat.' {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
Will he give thank his worker because of his work what he was told to do? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
It is same with you, when you have done everything what you were told to do, say, 'We are only your workers. We have only done our work."
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 10 men with leprosy
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
Yesu were walking to Jerusalem, traveled between Samaria and Galili region. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
When he entered a village, 10 lepers met him. They stood at a distance, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
and shouted loudly, "Yesu, Yure, have mercy on us!"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
Yesu saw them and said, "Go, show yourselves to the burning sacrifice man." And while they went, they were made clean.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
One [of them], when he saw he was healed, came back, praising God loudly. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
He knelt down at Yesu's feet, gave thank him and he was man from Samaria.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
Yesu asked, "What were cleased all of ten? Where is other 9 men? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
Why only this foreigner came back to praise God?" {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
Then Yesu said to him, "Stand and go. Your big mind(faith) has made you heal." '
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The ruling of God
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
One day Farasi men asked Yesu, "When the ruling of God would come?" Yesu answered, "The ruling of God does not come this way you see with your eyes. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
You can't say, 'Here it is' or 'There it is' because the ruling of God is inside you.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
Then Yesu said to his following men, "The day comes here when you will wish to see one of days of the Son of Man, but you will not see it. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
People will tell you, 'There he is, or 'Here he is.' Don't follow after them. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
Because when the Son of Man comes, all the people will see him like the lightening flashes [and] light up from one side to the other. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
But first he will see/have many suffering and be denied by this generation.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
Just as it was the days of Noa, it will same way in the days of the Son of Man. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
People ate food and [drinking] water, men married to women up to the day Noa entered very boat. Then the flood came and destroyed them all.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
It was the same in the days of Lot. People were eating food and [drinking] water, exchanging things, planting food and building house. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
But in that day Lot left Sodom, fire and buring stone fell down from heaven like a rain, and destroyed them all.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
It will like this on the day of the Son of Man is revealed. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
On that day those who are outside of house must not go inside to get things. In the same way, who is in the field must not go back to take things. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
Rembember Lot's wife! {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
Whoever try to keep his life will lose it, whoever loses his life will save it {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
I tell you, on that night two people will be sleep on the one sleeping place, God will take away one, [and] the other will be left. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 35\~}
Two women will prepare food together, he will take one and the other leave. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 37\~}
They asked, "Where, Lord?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu answered, "Where is the dead body, there the eagles will gather."
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 18
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The parable of the widow and judging man
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
Yesu told his following men a parable to show them they should always talk with God and not to stop. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
Yeus said, "In a town there was a decision maker(judge) who was without-fearing God and without-respecting people. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
There was a widow in that town who continue to [come] always to him with talk, 'Give me justice in this arguing with enemy.'
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
The judge ignored her to some day, but finally he said to himself, 'I am without-fear to God and without-respect to men, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
but this widow keeps on bothering me, I will see it that she gets her justice, so that she won't keep on coming to me!'
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
Then the Lord said, "Listen to what that unjust judge says. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
God surely will bring about justice for his chosen men, who cry out to him day and night. He will not continually deny them. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
I tell you, he will see that they receive justice quickly. But the Son of Man comes back, will he find anyone with big mind(faith) on earth?
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Farasi men and tax collectors
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
Yesu told this parable to some one who look down as they think, 'I am straight man and he is not,' {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
"Two men went to the worshipping house to talk with God, one was Farasi man and the other is tax collecter. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
Farasi man stood [and] talked with God, 'God, thank you that I am not like other men, robbers, sinners, adulterers, or like that tax collecter over there. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
I fast two days a week, and I always give offering [that] Moses law require for God.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
But the tax colletor stood a distance. He would not even look on to heaven, but beat his breast and said, 'God, mercy on me, I am a sinner.'
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
I tell you, this sinner, not Farasi man, he went back home with joy in front of God. If you exalt yourself to other people, you will be put down, and if you are down yourself, you will be ontop."
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The children and Yesu
