\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
He went to tell the people this parable, "A man planted a vine tree in the field, left it to the workers and went away for a long time. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
At harvesting time he sent a worker to people [who] look after the field(tenants) so that they will give him some fruit of vine tree from that field, but the tenants striked him and sent him back empty without things(empty-handed). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
He sent second worker like that, but they also beated this man and treated with shame and sent him empty-handed. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
He sent third man and they hit him with blood and threw him.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
The owner of the grape fruit vine garden said, 'What shall I do? I will send my son whom I love. Surely they will respect him.'
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
But when the tenants saw him, they said to each other, 'This is the son of the owner of the grape fruit vine garden. Let's kill him, and farm things will be ours.' {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
So they threw him out of the grape fruit vine garden and killed him.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 "What will owner of the grape fruit vine garden do to them? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
He will come and kill those men and give the grape fruit vine garden to other people."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 When the people heard about this, they said, "From here it won't be."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
Yesu looked to them straightly and asked, "Then what is the meaning of that which is written,
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 'The post which the builders rejected and became the middle post.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
Everyone who falls on the stone will be broken pieces, and when it falls on to them, they will be destroyed.'"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
The teaching men of the law and the leading sacrifice burning people(high priests) looked for a way to arrest him quickly, because they knew that he spoke this parable about them. But they were afraid of the people.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Paying taxes to [Rom high ruling man] Kaisar
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
They watched him, and send checking man(spies) who pretend to be good. They tried to think to catch Yesu so that he will say diffent saying, so that they might hand him over to the governor. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
The spies asked him, "Teacher, I know that you speak and teach what is straight and you are not influenced by people's thinking, but you teach the way of God truthfully. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
Is it straight for us to put the money to [Rom high ruling man] Kaisar or not?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
Yesu saw their lying/trick and said to them, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
"Show me his money. Whose face and name are these on it?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 They reanswered, "[Rom high ruling man] Kaisar's"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
Yesu said, "Give to [Rom high ruling man] Kaisar what is his, and give to God what is his."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
They became without-way to catch Yesu saying anything wrong there in front of the people. They were amazed at his answer, and they became silent.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The rising and marriage
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
Some of Saduki men, who say that there is no rising, came to him. They came to ask Yesu. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
They said, "Teacher, Moses wrote a law for us that if a small brother's big brother dies and leaves a wife but no children, his small brother must marry the widow and must produce children for his big brother.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
There were 7 sons. The first one married and died childless. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
The second married the widow, but he also died, leaving no children. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
And the third married the widow, in the same way that 7 died, leaving no children. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
Lost of them, the woman died. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
At the resurection whose wife will she be? Because the 7 married her.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
Yesu answered them, "Men will marry in this earth. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 35\~}
But in the future, those who can rise from death will not marry. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 36\~}
And they will not die. They will be like the men carrying heavenly message(angels). They will be God's children because God will rise them from death. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 37\~}
But when Moses wrote about burning bush fire, he showed that the dead will rise to life. He called the Lord 'The God of Ebraam, the God of Aisak and the God of Jeikof.' {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 38\~}
He is not God of the dead, but God of the living, because they all are alive to him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 39\~}
Some of the teaching men of the law responded, "Well said, teaching man!" {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 40\~}
And no one[dared to] ask him any question talk.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Whose son is Keriso
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 41\~}
Yesu asked them, "Why [do] people say that Keriso is the son of Deifid? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 42\~}
Deifid himself put in clear in the book of Psalms and said,
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 'The Lord said to my Lord:
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Sit here at my right hand.
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 43\~}
until I put your enemies
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 under your feet.'
\par\pard\plain \s61\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 44\~}
Deifid called him 'Lord.' How can he be his son?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 45\~}
As all the people were listening, Yesu said to his following men, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 46\~}
"Protect yourselves from the teaching men of the law. They like to walk around with long clothes and to be respected in the markets, and their mind were sitting in the respecting places in the synangogues and they like to find the respecting places at feasts. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 47\~}
They take widows' things with cheating and they pretend to be good by making long talking with God in front of people(in public). These men will carry the pains most high.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 21
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 A widow's offering
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
As Yesu looked up, he saw rich people putting offering things in the worshipping house. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
He saw a poor widow putting in two small coins. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
He said, "Truly I tell you, this poor widow surpasses them who put the money. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
All these people put the little things from many things, but widow put every thing for his living."
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Signs of last days
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
Some of his following men were talking about how worshipping house decorated with good stone and offered things to dedicate God. but Yesu said, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
"Everything what you see here, the day come where one stone will not leave from another people, everything will be thrown down to land."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
They asked, "Teacher, when will these things happen? And what will be the surprising thing in order that this things are about to happen?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
He answered, "Be careful of deceiving. Be alert because many people will come in my name, with talk that, 'I am Yesu,' and 'The day is near.' Don't follow them. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
When you hear of wars and surprising things, don't be afraid. These things will have to happen first, but land's end will not come yet.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
Then he said to them, "One nation and other nation, they will fight, one kingdom and other kingdom, they will fight. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
There will be big earthquakes, and famines, serious deseases in many places and fearful events and big surprising thing in heaven.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
But they will hand you over and put you into suffering after [this] these things will happen. You will be tied in meeting houses and you will be put in darkness house, and you will be taken in front of ruling men(kings) and governers for my name. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
But this will be time to tell about your big mind(faith). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
But don't worry in the mind beforehand how will defend yourselves. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
I will give you talk and wisdom in order that your enemies will not remove you or tell you are liar. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
You will be gave teeth(betrayed) by fathers, mother people, brothrs, family, friends and they will put some [of you] to death. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
Everyone will see you with hate because of me. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
But your one hair of your head will not be lost. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
You will stand firm in order that you will see real life. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
When you see Jerusalem being surrounded by soldiers, you will know that its destruction is not.far. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
Know [those] who are Judia people must go to the mountain, [those] who are in the city must go out, [those] who is outside of city must not enter the city. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
Those day become with body(fulfilled) which it has been written about suffering. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
How painful it will be pregnant women these day and nursing mother people! There will be big suffering in the land and anger to this people. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
They will be cut by the bush knife to kill and other people will be taken as darkness house men(prisoners) to all the nations. Jerusalem will be trampled by Side people until outside man's day are finished. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
There will be surprising things in the sun and moon and stars. On the earth, through all nations will be mental pain and in worring because wave roaring sound of the sea. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
People fell down with fear, because pain what comes to the land, because the body of heaven will be shaken. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
In that day they will see the Son of Man coming back in a cloud with power and big big light(glory). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
When these things began to happen, stand up and lift up your head, because your salvation is near.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
He told them this parable, "Look at the fig tree and all the trees. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
When they begin to come up new leaves, you can see for yourselves and know that sunny season is near. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
Like this, when you see these things happening, you will know that the ruling of God is near.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
I tell you the truth, some of the people of this generation will still be arive when all the things happens. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
Heaven and earth will pass away, but my talks will never pass away.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
Be careful, don't let your hearts be dulled by drinking alcohol and singing feast and by world mind because this day will arrive suddenly like a trap. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 35\~}
Because this day will come on all those who live in this earth. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 36\~}
Always watch out and talk with God that you can be saved from what are happing, and you can stand firmly in frnt of the Son of Man."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 37\~}
Every day Yesu was in teaching at the worshipping house, and he spent every night on the mount of Olif. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 38\~}
All the people came early each morning to hear him at the worshipping house.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 22
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Judas went to Betray Yesu
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
The festival of unleavened/without yeast flaw\u232?, called Passover became near. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
The leading sacrifice burning people(high priests) and the teaching men of the law were looking for catching Yesu, because they were afraid of the people. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
Then S\u225?if\u232?r entered Judas Iskariot who was one of 12 following men. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
And Judas went the leading sacrifice burning people(high priests) and worshipping house guarders and discussed with them how he might give teeth(betray) Yesu. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
They were pleased and offered to pay him some money. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
Judas went back and looked for the way to catch Yesu in place without-people.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The last feast
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
The day came for unleavened flaw\u232? which is Passover lamb being sacrifice. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
Yesu sent Fit\u232? and Jon and said, "Go to prepare for us to eat Passover food."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
They asked, "Where do you want us to prepare for it?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
Yesu answered, "When you enter the city, you will see a man carrying a jar of water. You follow him the house that he enters, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
and say to the owner of the house, 'Teacher asks, "Where is the guest room, where I may eat the Passover food with my following men?"' {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
He will show you a largh room upstairs, all furnished. Be ready(Prepare) there."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
They left [and] found things like as Yesu how told them. So they prepared the Passover food.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
When the time came, Yesu and his men with Yesu's authority(apostles) sit at the eating place. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
And Yesu said them, "I wanted very much to eat the Passover food with you after [this] I will see the suffering. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
I tell you, I will not eat again until this fulfill in the ruling of God.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
After taking a cup, he gave thanks and said, "Take this and divide it among you. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
I tell you I will not repeat [to drink] alcohol again until the ruling of God arrives."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
He took flaw\u232?(bread), gave thanks and broke it, and gave it, with this talk, "This is my body which is given for you. Do this for remembering me."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
In the same way, after the supper he took a cup, saying this, "This cup is the new without.lying talk(promise) in my blood which is poured out for you. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
But the man who will be give teeth(betray) me is with me here. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
