\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 God's Lamb
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
The next day Jon saw Yesu coming to him, and said, "Look, here is God's Lamb, who takes away the sin of the world! {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
This is he who I was talking about and I said, "A man who is coming after me, he surpasses me, because he first existed I was born after." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
I did not know about him, but I came batizing with water in order that it might put him clear to Israil people."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
And Jon said this talk: "I saw the God Spirit(God Spirit) come down like as mamu/Note:looks like dove white bird/ from heaven and stay on him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
I did not know still that he was the one, but God, who sent me to baptize with water, had said to me, 'You will see the God Spirit come down [and] stay on a man; he is [the one] who will baptize with the God Spirit.' {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
Jon said, "I have seen this things and I tell you that he is the Son of God."
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The first Disciples of Yesu
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 35\~}
The next day Jon was standing there again with two in/of his following men, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 36\~}
when he saw Yesu walking, he said, "Look That's the Lamb of God"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 37\~}
The two following men heard(dual) him say this and went with Yesu. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 38\~}
Yesu turned, saw them(2 of them) following him, and asked (to 2 of them), "What are you(dual) looking for?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 They.d answered, "Where are you staying, Rabai? (This name's meaning is "Teaching man(Teacher.")
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 39\~}
He answered, "Come and to see." (It was 4 o'clock in the afternoon.) So they.d went with him and saw where he was staying and spent that day with him.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 40\~}
There is one of them was Endru, Saimon Fit\u232?'s younger brother, who heard what Jon had said and who had followed Yesu. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 41\~}
At once he went and saw his big brother Saimon and told him, "We have found Mesaya."(His name's meaning is "Keriso.") {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 42\~}
Then he took Saimon to Yesu. Yesu looked at him and said, "Your name is Saimon son of Jon, but will be called Sifas." (This can translate Fit\u232? and its meaning is "a rock.")
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu called Filif and Nataniel
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 43\~}
The next day Yesu thought to go to Galili region. He found Filif and said to him, "Follow me!" {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 44\~}
(Filif was from Betsaida, the town Endru and Fit\u232? lived.) {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 45\~}
Filif found Nataniel and told him, "We have found the one whom Moses wrote in the book of the law and who the God's people who make know(prophets) also wrote. He is Yesu the Josef's son from Najaret."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 46\~}
Nataniel asked, "Can anything good come from Najaret?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Filif answered, "Come and see."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 47\~}
When Yesu saw Nataniel coming to him, Yesu said about him, "Here is a real Israil man; to him there is no deceit!"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 48\~}
Nataniel asked him, "How do you know me?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu answered, "I saw you when you were in the shadow of the breadfruit tree before Filif called you."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 49\~}
Nataniel answered, "Teacher, you are the Son of God! You are the ruling man(king) of Israil!"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 50\~}
Yesu said, "Your truly approve(believe) is it because I told you that I saw you in the shadow of the fig tree? Later you will look very big things happen that will surpass what you have seen now!" {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 51\~}
And he said to them, "I am telling you the truth: you will find heaven open and God's men carrying heavenly message(angels)(heaven talk carring men) will go up and come down through the Son of Man."
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 2
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The wedding in Kana
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
Two days later there was a wedding feast in Kana town in Galili region. Yesu's mother was there, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
and they invited Yesu and his following men to the wedding feast. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
When the alcohol finished, Yesu's mother said to him, "Their alcohol has already finished."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
Yesu answered her, "Mother, why do you tell me this? My day has not come."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
Yesu's mother told the workers, "Do if what he tells you."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
There were rules of Ju people about ritual washing, and so there were 6 stone jars for water carring, each one can hold between 80 lit\u232? or 120 lit\u232?. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
Yesu said to the workers, "Fill these jars with water." They filled them to the brim, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
and he told them again, "Now draw some water out and take it to the man who is looking after feast." They took him the water, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
which had turned into alcohol, and he tasted it. He did not know from where this alcohol had come (but workers who had drawn out the water knew); so he called the bridgegroom {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
and said to him, "Everyone brings out the best alcohol first. When people have had plenty to drink, then they give people cheaper alcohol. But you.s are different. You.s have kept the best alcohol until now.\u8217?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
Yesu did this first surprising things in Kana in Galili region; there he revealed his strong light(big light), and his following men truly approved(believed) in him.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
After this, Yesu and his mother, small brothers and following men went to Kafenam and stayed there not for a many days.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu went to the worshipping house
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
It was very close day for the Passover festival, so Yesu went to Jerusalem. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
There in the worship house (worshipping house) area he found people exchanging cow, sheep and doves and also the money exchanging men sitting at their tables. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
So he made a whip from the ropes and drove the all the people from the worshipping house, with their cows and sheep; he scattered their coins and turned over their money changing tables, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
and he said to them who sold doves, "Take them out of here! Stop changing my Father's house a open space(market)!" {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
His following men remembered like that the verse says, "My love to your house burns in me like a fire."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
The Ju head men came back at him with a question, "What surprising thing can you do to show us that you have the power(authority) to do this?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
Yesu answered, "Destroy this worshipping house, and in three days I will raise it up again."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
They asked him, "What are you going to build it again in three days? To build this worshipping house took 46 years!"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
But when Yesu said the worshipping house he said his body. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
So when he was raised from death, his following men remeberd that he had said this, and they truly approved(believed) the Buk(scripture) and what Yesu had said.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu know people's heart
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
While Yesu was in Jerusalem during the Passover festival, many truly approved(believed) in him because they saw the surprising things he did. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
But Yesu did not depend on himself to them, because he knew all people. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
There was no need any talk in order to say about them, because he himself knew what was in their hearts.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 3
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu and Nikodimas
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
There was one Ju head man name Nikodimas, who was in a Farasi group. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
One night he went to Yesu and said to him, "Teacher, we know that you are a teaching man who God sent. No one can perform the surprising things you are doing unless God were/Note:dual/ with you."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
Yesu answered, "I am telling you the truth: no one can see the ruling of God(God's reigning) unless he is born again."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
Nikodimas asked, "How can a grown man be born again? He cannot enter his mother's womb and be born a second time!"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
Yesu answered him, "I am telling you the truth, no one can enter the ruling of God unless he is born by water and the God Spirit. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
A man is born in body from parents, but is born in spirit by the God Spirit. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
You should not be surprised because I tell you that you must all(of you) be born again. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
The wind blows to where it wants; you.s hear its sound which it makes, but you.s don't know from which way it comes or where it is going again. It is like that to them every people who is born by the God Spirit.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
Nikodimas asked, "How this is?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
Yesu answered him, "You.s are a big teaching man in Israil, and you.s don't know about this? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
I am telling you the truth: we speak what we know and report what we have seen, but still none of you.p willing to accept our talk. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
Your.s big mind(faith) is not to me when I tell you.s about things of this world; how will you.s truly approve(believe) me when I tell you about things of heaven? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
And no one has gone upto heaven except the Son of Man, who came down from heaven."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
Just as Moses lifted up the steel/metal snake with a post in a desert, in the same way they must lift the Son of Man up/Note: there is no passive form in Nama/. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
As a result, every people who truly approve(believe) him may have eternal life/note: literally they may be with eternal life/. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
Because God loved the world so much, so he gave his only one Son, so that every people who truly approves(believes) in him may not die but have eternal life. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
For God did not send his Son into the world in order to be his judging man, but to be his saving man.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
Those who truly approve(believe) the Son are not judged; but those who do not truly approve(believe) have in judgement, because they did not truly approve(believe) God's only one Son. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
This is how the judgement works: the light has come into the world, but people like the darkness and not the light, because their deeds are evil. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
Those who do evil hate the light and will not come to the light, because they do not want their sin to put clear. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
But those who do what is true come to the light so that other people can see that they do what God wants.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu and Jon
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
After this, Yesu and his dicsiples went to Judia area, there he stayed with them and washed them with water.(baptized them) {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
Jon like that(also) was baptizing in Aeron village not far from Salim village, because there were plenty of water in that place. People were going to him and he was baptizing them. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
After this was, [they] put Jon into darkness house.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
Some of Jon's following men began arguing with a Jew about the matter of ritual washing. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
So they went to Jon and told him, "Teacher, you remember the man who was with you on the east side of the Joden river, he is the one you spoke about? So he is baptizing now, and every people is going to him!"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
Jon answered, "No one can have anything unless God gives him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
You yourselves are my watching men how I said, 'I am not him Keriso, but God sent me ahead of him.' {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
The new marrying man(bridgegroom) has new marrying woman, but the new bridgegroom's friend, who waits for and listens to him, he is joyful when he hears the new bridgegroom's voice. That joy is mine, is full. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
He must become big but I must become low."
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 He who comes from heaven
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
He who comes from above surpasses all things. He who is from the earth belongs the earth and speaks about land things, but he who comes from heaven he is above all. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
He reports what he has seen and heard, but no one accept his talk. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
But whoever accept his talk confirms by [this]that God is truthful. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
He whom God has sent speaks God's talk, because God gives him the fullness of God Spirit. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 35\~}
His Father loves his Son and has put everything in his power. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 36\~}
Who truly approves(believes) in the Son he has eternal life; whoever denies the Son will not be with life, but will leave into God's anger.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 4
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu and the Samaritan woman
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
The Farasi men heard that Yesu made people following him and baptizing so many people and his people became many and was surpassing Jon's following men. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
But, Yesu himself did not baptize anyone; only his following man [do] {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
When Yesu heard this talk, he left Judia and went back to Galili region; {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
his returning was through Samaria area.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
