Yesu told Fit\u232?, "Put back your sword to it's sheath. I should drink this cup of pain which the Father has given me."
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 They took Yesu to Anas
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
Then the soldiers and their head man and worshipping house guards they caught Yesu. They bound him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
And they brought him first to Anas. Kayafas was married to daughter of Anas. Kayafas was leading burning sacrifice men that year. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
Kayafas was the one who told Ju people that it will be good if one man dies for all people.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fit\u232? first denial
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
Saimon Fit\u232? and another follower followed.dual Yesu. This leading burning sacrifice men knew this Yesu's following man, so he went with Yesu into leading burning sacrifice men's house yard, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
but Fit\u232? still waited outside at the door, but the other Yesu's following man who the leading burning sacrifice man knew, he came back, told the girl who was the door keeper, and brought Fit\u232? in.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
The girl who was at the door she asked Fit\u232?, "You are one of his following men, true you are?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 But Fit\u232? answered him, "I am not."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
It was cold, workers and the worshipping house guards stood on the side of the fire which they tried to keep warm. Fit\u232? himself stood warming by the charcoal fire.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The leading burning sacrifice men asked Yesu
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
Next, the leading burning sacrifice man asked Yesu about his following men and about his teaching.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
Yesu answered him, "I have spoken openly this world, I always taught in the gathering houses(meeting houses) and in the worshipping house area, where all the Ju people gathered one place, I did not speak anything secretly. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
Why do you ask me? Ask those heard me, they know what I said."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
When he said this, one of the worshipping house guard who stood close to him hit him on the face and said, "You should not speak to the leading burning sacrifice man in that way."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
Yesu answered him, "If I have said wrongly, just say where is the wrong. But if I have said truly, why did you hit me?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
Then Anas sent Yesu bound to Kayafas the leading burning sacrifice man.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fit\u232?'s denied again
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
While Saimon Fit\u232? was standing warming by the fire, they asked him, "You must also be one of his follower."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 He denied and said, "I am not."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
One of leading burning sacrifice men's without.payment working men(servants), the family of whose ear Fit\u232? cut off, he asked him, "What I did not see.dual you with him there in the garden?" {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
Again Fit\u232? denied, at these time the rooster cried out.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu before Failet
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
So Ju people led him from the house of Kayafas to a Rom governor's house. It was early in the morning, but they still did not go into the house, because they would become unclean, they would not allow them for passover meal to eat. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
Then Failet came out to them and asked, "What wrong thing do you say that this man has done?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
They answered him, "If he was not a wrong doer, we would not hand him over to you."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
Failet said, "Take him yourselves and ask him by your law. "
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The Ju people answered him, "But we have no straight to put someone to death." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
This fulfilled what Yesu spoke how he will die.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
Failet went back into the house, called Yesu to himself and asked him, "Are you the ruling man(king) of the Ju people?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
Yesu asked him, "What this asking talk came from you, or did other people report about me?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 35\~}
Failet answered him, "I am not a Ju man. Your own people and your chief burning sacrifice men they handed you to me. What did you do?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 36\~}
Yesu said, "My reigning place is not of this world. If it was, my without.payment working men(servants) would fight and prevent me from Ju people arrest. But now my reigning place is of another place."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 37\~}
Failet said, "So, you are the ruling man(king), really?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yesu answered him, "You are straight as you say that I am the ruling man(king). Rightly, for this reason I was born came to this world to report about the truth. All those are from the truth listen to me."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 38\~}
Failet asked him, "what is truth?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 After Failet had said this, he again went out to the Ju people and said, "I did not find anything bad from which he will pay. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 39\~}
But this is your own custom for me in order that I will take out to you.p one darkness house man(prisoner) this Ju people's Passover day. Do you want I am going to take out the ruling man(king) of the Ju people?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 40\~}
They answered him loudly, "Not him, but Barabas!" Barabas was a thief.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 19
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 They sent Yesu to be hung on the cross
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
Failet sent soliders to whip Yesu. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
The soldiers took some branches with thorns and they made a crown for Yesu. They put it on his head. Then they took a purple coat and they put that on him. They did all this as if he was the ruling man(king). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
and came up to him, repeatedly saying, "Ei(making fun of him), the ruling man(king) of the Ju people!" And they continue to hit him on the face.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
Once more Failet went out and said to the Ju people, "Look, I am bringing him again to you.p in order to let you know that I did not find anything bad from which he will get a payment/charge." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
When Yesu came out wearing the crown of thorn on the head and wearing purple cloth, Failet said to them, "Here is the man!"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
When the leading sacrifice burning people(high priests) and the worshipping house guards saw Yesu, they shouted, "Nail on the cross! Nail on the cross!" But Failet answered them, "You take him and hang him. As for me, I didn't find any badness which he should get a payment/charge."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
The Ju people replied, "To us here is a law, and in this law he should die, because he claimed that he was God's Son."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
When Failet heard this, he filled afraid very much, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
and he went back into the house. He asked Yesu, "Where are you from?" But Yesu gave no answer. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
Failet said to him, "You do not want to talk to me? Remember that I have authority. I can let you go free, or I can let them kill you on a cross.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
Yesu answered him, "You would not have this power to overcome me unless he(God) gave them to you.s from heaven. Therefore he who handed me to you, his sin surpasses your sin."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
Then form there Failet tried to make take Yesu out, but the Ju people still continually shouting, "If you let this man go, you will not be a friend of big the ruling man(king) Kaisar! Which people who claim that they are the ruling man(king) oppose Kaisar!"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
When Failet heard this, he brought Yesu and sat down a seat for judging man This seat was a place called the Wide stone, Gabata in Ibru talk." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
This day was a preparing day for the Passover feast; it was midday.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Failet said to the Ju people, "Your.p the ruling man(king) is here!"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
But they shouted, "Kill him! Kill him! Nail him on the cross!"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Failet asked them, "What I will nail the ruling man(king) on the cross?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The leading sacrifice burning people(high priests) answered him, "To us are no other ruling man(king) but only Kaisar!"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
Finally Failet handed him over to them in order to be nail on the cross.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The nailing
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Then the soldiers took Yesu. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
He was carrying his own cross, to this place called the Skull, (this is Ibru language which is called "Golgota." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
There they nailed Yesu on the cross. They put two other men on crosses near to Yesu. They were on each side of him and Yesu was between them.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
Failet also wrote a letters/notice and put it on the cross. He wrote like this; "Yesu of Najaret, the ruling man(king) of the Ju people." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
Many Ju people read notice, because there on this place where they nailed Yesu on the cross was not far to the town, this notice was written in Ibru, Latin and Grik. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
The leading sacrifice burning people(high priests) of Ju people went to Failet and said, 'Do not write like, "The ruling man(king) of the Ju people." But, write, "This man said that he is the ruling man(king) of the Ju people."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
Failet answered him, "What I have written, I must have written."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
And when the soldiers nailed Yesu to the cross, they removed the clothes and divided them into four groups and each soldier got one. They did that and then they got the long cloth worn inside and saw that cloth was not sewn from many pieces, but it was done from one piece from the top to the down.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
They said among themselves, "We will not tear it, we will play dice game and see who will get it." This happened in order that it will become true which says, "They divided my garment among themselves and played dais game for my clothing." So like this the soldiers did.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
Near the cross of Yesu stood his own mother, his mother's younger sister, and Meri who was a wife of Klofas, and Meri Makdalin. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
When Yesu saw his mother there, his following man whom he loved was standing close to them, he said to his mother, "Woman, this is your son." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
Then he said to that following man, "Here is your mother." From that time, that following man of Yesu looked after Yesu's mother in his house.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The Death of Yesu
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
After this, Yesu knew that he had finished the work. And in order to make the Scripture become true, Yesu said, "I am thirsty." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
There laid a jar of sour alcohol; then they made a sponge there they soaked it and with a stick of Isof tree lifted it to Yesu lips. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
When he drank this alcohol, Yesu said, "It is finished!"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 With that talk he bowed his head and died.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
There was on the preparing day, and the next day was Safat. Because the Ju people did not want dead bodies to hang on the cross on the Safat, they asked Failet to break the legs to die quickly and to take down the bodies. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
The soldiers went there. They broke the legs of the two men who were on the crosses next to Yesu. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
But when they went to Yesu and found that he had died they did not break his legs. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
But one of soldiers pierced side of Yesu with a spear, at once, blood and water poured out. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 35\~}
The man who saw this thing made to report/testfy, and his report/testimony is true. He knows that he reports the truth, and he reports in order that you will also truly approve(believe). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 36\~}
This thing happened in order that the Buk(scripture) would become true: "Not one of his bones shall be broken," {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 37\~}
and another Buk(scripture) says, "They will look on him whom they pierced with the spear."
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Making land for Yesu
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 38\~}
Later, Josef from Aramatia town asked Failet for the body of Yesu. Josef was a following man of Yesu, but secretly because he fell with fear the Ju people. With only Failet's permission, he came and took the body of Yesu. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 39\~}
Nikodimas, who at first visited Yesu in the night, he himself brought about(like) 34 kilogram mixtured special smelling liquid from mir\u232? and aloe. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 40\~}
These two men took and wrapped Yesu's body with cloth with special smelling liquid, they did these in the way of the Ju's burial. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 41\~}
At this place where they nailed Yesu on the cross, there was a garden, in this garden was a new hole in the rock, where no one was made land(buried). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 42\~}
Because it was Ju people's preparing day and the tomb was close, they laid Yesu.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 20
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The rising
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
On early Sunday morning, when it was still dark, Meri Makdalin came to the tomb and saw the stone had been moved from the door. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
Then she ran found Saimon Fit\u232? and the other following men of Yesu, whom Yesu loved, and said, "They have taken the Lord out of the tomb, and we do not know where they have put him!"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
