Then Filif ran up to carriot and heard the man reading a book of Aisaya the God's man who make know(prophet). Filif asked him, "Do you understand what you are reading?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
He said, "How can I know, unless some man explains it to me?" So in this reason he allowed Filif to come up and to sit with him.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
This part(passage) of Scripture he was reading,
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 "They led him like a sheep to killing,
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 and as a lamb before the fleece cutting people without-saying,
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 he did not open his mouth.
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
They put him down and took his straight/justice away.
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 He was without.children, so no one can speak of his descendants.
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Because his life was taken from the land."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
The man asked Filif, "Tell me, who is the God's man who make know(prophet) talking, about himself or other man?" {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 35\~}
So Filif began to preach with that passage of Scripture of Aisaya and told him the good talk about Yesu.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 36\~}
As they.d travelled along the road, they.d reached to some water and the man said, "Look, water is. I'd like to be baptized"{\super r{\footnote \pard\plain \s212\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28  {\super r}{{\cs214\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 8.37 }
{\cs215\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Some knowledge men think this: another part of this talk is here in this verse, but many knowledge men think not. This talk is, "Filif said to him, 'If you believe Yesu with all your heart, I can baptize you.' He answered, 'I believe that Yesu Keriso is the Son of God.'}
}}}
 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 38\~}
And he said to driver to stop the chariot. Then Filif and the man went down into the water, and Filif baptized him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 39\~}
When they.d came out of water, the Lord's Spirit suddenly took Filif away, and the eunuch did not see him again, but went on his way with joy. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 40\~}
But Filif arrived at Ajotus town and he went preached the good talk in all the towns until he arrived at Kaisaria.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 9
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Sol's repentace from sins
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
Sol kept on start to kill the Yesu's following people. He went to the leading burning sacrifice man {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
and he asked him for letters to the meeting houses in Damaskos city, so that if he found any men and women who followed the Way of Yesu, he will take them immediately as darkness house men(prisoners) to Jerusalem. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
When he became close Damaskos, suddenly a light from heaven flashed and surrounded him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
He fell to the ground and heard a sound of talk that, "Sol, Sol, why are hitting me?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
Sol asked, "Lord, who are you?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 He answered him, "I am Yesu, whom you are hitting. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
Now get up and go into the city, and there is a man he will tell what you must do."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
Those men were going through the road with Sol stood there speechless; they heard the sound of talk but did not see any[one]. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
Sol got up from the ground, but when he opended his eyes he could not see anything. So they took him by the hand and led him to Damaskos. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
For the three days he was blind, and did not eat or drink anything.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
In Damaskos there was a following man name Ananias. The Lord called to him in a eye passover thing, "Ananias!"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 He answered him, "Yes, Lord."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
The Lord told him, "Go to the Judas' house on Straight streets and asked for a man from Tarsus name Sol, there he is in talking with God. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
In a eye passover thing he saw a man name Ananias came to him and [his]put hands and his [Sol's]eyes opened and got sight again."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
Ananias answered him, "Lord, I've heard many talk about this man because he gave the pains to your people in Jerusalem. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
And he came here with authority from the leading burning sacrifice man in order to arrest them all who says your name."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
But the Lord said to Ananias, "Go! This man is my chosen to carry my talk to the Side people and their ruling men(kings) and to the people of Israil. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
I will show him how bad he must feel for my name's sake."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
So Ananias went and entered into the house. He put hands on Sol, he said, "Friend Sol, the Lord Yesu, who appeared to you on the road when you were coming here, he sent me so that you might see again and be filled with the God Spirit." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
Immediately, something like a scale fell from Sol's eyes, and saw. He stood up and was baptized, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
and after (he ate) his food and his strengh recovered.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Sol stayed in Damaskos and Jerusalem
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Sol stayed with the following men in Damaskos few days. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
Immediatly he began to preach in the meeting houses that Yesu is the Son of God!" {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
All who heard him amazed and asked, "This man is the one who was killing Yesu's following people in Jerusalem. He came here to arrest following men as darkness house men(prisoners) to the leading burning sacrifice man. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
Sol's preaching became very powerful and Ju people in Damaskos without.possible to answer to Fol because he showed Yesu is Keriso.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
After many days, some of Ju people made plans to kill Sol, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
but Sol learned of their thought/plan. Day and night they watched on the city gates to kill Sol. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
But his following people took him at night and lowered Sol with a big basket from back of the town fence(wall).
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
When Sol came to Jerusalem, he tried to meet with the following men, but they were all afraid of him, they did not truly approve(believe) that he is already a following man. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
But Banabas brought Sol to the men with Yesu's authority(apostles). Banabas told them how Sol saw the Lord on the road and how Lord said to him, and how he preached without.fear in the name of Yesu in Damaskos.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
Sol stayed with men with Yesu's authority(apostles) and moved around without fear in Jerusalem, saying without fear in the name of the Lord. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
Sol talked and argued with the Greek-speaking Ju people, but they tried to kill him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
When approving truth people learned of this, they took Sol to Kaisaria city and sent him away to Tarsus city.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
Then the Yesu's family(church) throughout Judia, Galili region and Samaria, they enjoyed the peace in that time. There were strengh and encouragement of the God Spirit, many people added and lived with the fear of the Lord.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Enias and Dorkas
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
While Fit\u232? went around some area, he went there to visit God's approving truth people to Lida village. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
There he saw a man name Enias, paralyzed man who was paralyed for 8 years. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
Fit\u232? said to him, "Enias, Yesu Keriso will make you good. Get up and rolled up your mat." Immediately Enias stood up. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 35\~}
All those who lived in Lida and Saron, they saw him and began to turn into the Lord.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 36\~}
In Jofa city there was a following man(disciple) woman name Tabita, Greek name is Dorkas, who was always doing good things and helping the poor. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 37\~}
At that time woman felt sick and died, and they washed her body with water and laid it up in the house. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 38\~}
Lida village was near Jofa city, so when the following men heard that Fit\u232? was in Lida village, they sent two men to him and told him, "Come quickly!"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 39\~}
Fit\u232? returned with them, and when he arrived, they took him up into the house. All the widows surrounded him, crying and showing him clothes and other clothing which Dorkas made while she was still alive with them.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 40\~}
Fit\u232? sent them all out from the inside of the room, then he knelt down and talked with God. Then he turned toward the dead woman, he said, "Tabita, get up." Immediately woman opened [her] eyes, and then woman saw Fit\u232? and she sat up. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 41\~}
He hold her with hand and supported her get up. Then he called the approving truth people and wodows, showed them living woman. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 42\~}
The story about raising from the death became wide to all over Jofa city and many people truly approved(believed) in the Lord. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 43\~}
Fit\u232? stayed in Jofa city for many days with a man [who] took the skin animal skin(tanner) name Saimon.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 10
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Konelias called for Fit\u232?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
At Kaisaria city there was a man name Konelias, a Rom solidiers' headman who was taking care of 100 soldiers this name is Italia soldiers group. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
He was God-fearing man with all his family and was worshipper; he gave things widely to those in need and always talked with God. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
One day afternoon about three o'clock, he had a eye passover thing(vision). He saw a man carrying heavenly message(angel) of God, who came to him and said to him, "Konelias!"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
Konelias saw him in fear and asked him, "What is this, Lord?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The man carrying heavenly message(angel) answered him, "God is pleased with your talking with God(prayers) and giving things to the poor. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
Now send men to Jofa city to bring back a man name Saimon who people call other name Fit\u232?. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
He is staying with Saimon, a leather maker with animal skin(tanner), whose house is by the sea."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
When the man carrying heavenly message(angel) who spoke to him disappeared, Konelias called his two without.payment working men(servants) and a God fearing soldier. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
Konelias told them all what happened to him and sent them off to Jofa city.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fit\u232? saw eye passover thing(a vision)
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
The next day about noon Konelias's without.payment working men(servants) were on the way and coming near the town, Fit\u232? went up on sitting place on the roof to talk with God. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
There he felt hungry, and wanted something to eat, and while food were preparing, he saw a eye passover thing from God. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
He saw the heaven opened and something looked like wide clothes coming down by 4 corners to the land. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
In this wide clothes there were all different animals and animals crawling with belly(reptiles), and birds. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
Then God said to him, "Get up, Fit\u232?. kill and eat."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
Fit\u232? answered him, "No, Lord. I never eat somethings to bad to me."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
God spoke to him again that, "No. You should eat it. Don't say that bad what God has made them good."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
These things happened three times, and suddenly this clothe went back into heaven.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
When Fit\u232? was still confusing about the meaning of the eye passover thing(vision), the man sent by Konelias they asked where Saimon's house was and stopped at the gate of house. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
They called, "Is there a guest here his name of Saimon Fit\u232??"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
While Fit\u232? was still thinking about the eye passover thing, the God Spirit said to him, "Saimon, three men are looking for you. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
So get up and go down. Don't hesitate to go with them, because I have sent them."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
Fit\u232? came down and said to this men, "I am the man who you are looking for. Why have you come?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
These men answered him, "We came from Konelias Roman soldiers head man(the centurion). He is a straight and God-fearing man, who all the Ju people respect. A without.dust(holy)/holy man carrying heavenly message told him to send people to his house so that he can hear what you will say." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
So Fit\u232? invited these men to his house. So they became his guests.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fit\u232? there at Konelias's house
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The next day Fit\u232? was preparing to go with them, and some of approving truth people from Jofa city went with them. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
The next day he arrived at Kaisaria city. Konelias was waiting for him and called all his family and close friends. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
When Fit\u232? entered his house, Konelias met him and fell at his feet with respect[worshiped him]. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
But Fit\u232? caused/made him rise and said to him, "Got up, don't worship me. I'm definitely just as you are."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
Fit\u232? a Konelias were talking [together], after this Fit\u232? went inside and found people group. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
Fit\u232? told them, "You Side people know well our Ju people's law, Ju people should not enter a outside man's house and should not associate with Side people. But God has shown me that I should not reject that you are bad or with dirty. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
So when you.p sent for me, I came without question. I ask you.p, "Why did you.p call me?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
Konelias answered him, "Before four days I was talking with God in my house this time, 3 o'clock in the afternoon. Suddenly a man appeared with shining clothes in front of me. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
And the man carrying heavenly message(angel) said, "Konelias, God heard your talking with God and remembered your giving things(gifts) to the poor. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
Send people to Jofa city to Saimon who they call Fit\u232?. He is a guest of Saimon animal skin tanning man, who is(lives) beside the sea.' {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
So I sent for you at once, and it was good of you to come. Now we are all here before God to listen every talk what the Lord sent you to tell us."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
Then Fit\u232? began to speak: "I now realize [that] it is true God does not show way only some part like {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 35\~}
but accepted from every nation those who fear him and do what is straight. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 36\~}
You.p know the talk God sent to the people of Israil, preached the good talk of the peace through Yesu Keriso, who is Lord of all people. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 37\~}
You.p know what has happened throughout Judia, beginning in Galili region after the baptism Jon preached. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 38\~}
How God chose Yesu of Najaret with God Spirit and power, and how he went around doing good and healing all who were under the power of the S\u225?if\u232?r(Satan), because God were.d with him.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 39\~}
We are watching men of everything he did in the land of Ju people and in Jerusalem. They killed him through that they hung him on a cross, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 40\~}
but God raised him from dead three days later to be seen, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 41\~}
all the people did not see him, but only watching men whom God appointed long time ago saw, that is, we ate and drink with him after he rose from dead. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 42\~}
He commanded us to preach to the people and to tell that he is the one who God appointed as judging man of the living and the dead. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 43\~}
All the prophers tell about him that every people who truly approves(believes) in him found he forget sins through his name."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 44\~}
While Fit\u232? was still speaking these talk, the God Spirit came down to them all who heard this talk. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 45\~}
The Ju approving truth people who came with Fit\u232? were amazed that the gift of the God Spirit in the same way had been poured out on the outside men, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 46\~}
because they heard them speaking in other talks(languages) and praising God.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Then Fit\u232? said, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 47\~}
"They had received the God Spirit just as we did. No one can stop them from being baptized with water." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 48\~}
Therefore told them be baptized in the name of Yesu Keriso. Then they asked Fit\u232? to stay with them for a three/few days.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 11
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fit\u232? explained his actions
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
The men with Yesu's authority(apostles) and the approving truth people thoughout Judia region heard that the Side people also received the talk of God. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
When Fit\u232? went back to Jerusalem, Ju approving truth people rebuked him {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
and said, "You.s went to the house of Side people and ate food with them."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
Fit\u232? said all talk to them what had happened there from the beginning. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
"I was in the town of Jofa in talking with God, and I saw a eye passover thing. I saw something like a wide clothes coming down from heaven by 4 corners, and it came down to where I was. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
I looked into it [and] saw animals with 4 legs, wild animals, crawling animal with belly(reptiles) and birds. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
I heard talk telling me that, "Get up, Fit\u232?. Kill and eat them.'
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
I answered, "No, Lord. With dirty and with dust animal has not entered my mouth."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
God said from heaven again, "No. You should eat it. Do not say what God has made them good." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
This happened three times, and that clothes went up to heaven again.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
Suddenly three men who had been sent from Kaisaria city stopped at the house where I was staying. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
The God Spirit told me not hesitate to go with them. These 6 friends also went with me, and we entered Rom soldier's head man Konelias's house. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
Konelias told us how he saw a man carrying heavenly message in his house and that man carrying heavenly message said, 'Send the people to Jofa town to Saimon who they called Fit\u232?. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
Fit\u232? will carry you.p talk through which you and all your family/household will be saved.'
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
"As I began to speak, the God Spirit came to them in the same way how it came to us at first. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
Then I remembered what Lord said, 'Jon baptized with water, but you.p will be baptized with the God Spirit.' {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
It is in the light(clear) that God gave them the same kind gift he gave us, who truly approved(believed) in the Lord Yesu Keriso; therefore I was not going to stop what God was doing.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
When they heard this, they stopped objecting [and]only praising God, said, "So then God gave thought to the Side people to turn away from sins to life."
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The Yesu's family(church) in Antiok city
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
Those who had been scattered by Stif\u232?n's death went like as Fonesia, Saifras, and Antiok, telling talk to Ju people only. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
But some people from Saifras and Sairene cities, went to Antiok and began to speak good talk to Side people about the Lord Yesu. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
The Lord's hand was with them, and many Side people truly approved(believed) and turned from their sins to the Lord.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
When the Yesu's family(church) in Jerusalem heard about this [that] many Side people turned to the Lord, so they sent Banabas to Antiok city. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
When he arrived and saw God's blessing, he was in joy and he encouraged all of them to be true to the Lord with all their hearts. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
Banabas was a good man, full of God Spirit and big mind(faith), he brought many people to the Lord.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
Then Banabas went to Tarsus city to look for Sol, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
and when he found Sol, Banabas brought him to Antiok city. For a whole year, Banabas and Sol met with Yesu's family(church) and taught many people. People called the following men first as Keriso's People(Christian)at Antiok city.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
At that day some God's people who make know(prophets) came from Jerusalem to Antiok city. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
One of them name Agabus stood up [and] through the God Spirit he said that a big famine would spread over Roman county. (This happened during the time when Klaudius was leading.) {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
The following men wrote mind(decided) to help their friends who lived in Judia area. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
They collected the money and gave it to Banafas and Sol, who took it to the head men in Judia area.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 12
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The man carrying heavenly message(Angel) took out Fite from darkness house
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
At that time the ruling man(king) Erod caught people from the Yesu's family(church), thinking to kill them. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
Erod sent/ordered soldiers to kill Jems, the brother of Jon with a sword to death. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
When Erod killed Jems make happy Ju people, so he also went to arrest Fit\u232?. This happened during the festival of bread [made] without yeast. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
After arresting, he put him in darkness house, guarding with 4 groups of soldiers which one group had 4 soldiers, totally 16 soldiers. Erod thought to bring him out for asking(trial) after the Passover feast.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
So they put Fit\u232? into darkness house, but the Yesu's family(church) was really big talking with God for him.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
That same night Erod thought mind(decided) to bring him to the court, Fit\u232? was sleeping between the two soldiers, with two chains, and some guards stood at the door. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
Suddenly a man carrying heavenly message of the Lord appeared and a light shone into the darkness house. He struck Fit\u232? on the side and woke him up and said, "Get up quickly!" and the chains fell off his hands.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
Then the man carrying heavenly message(angel) said to him, "Tie/Put on your clothes and sandols." And Fit\u232? did these things. The man carrying heavenly message said, "Put on your clothes and follow me." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
Fit\u232? followed him they.d went out of the darkness house, but he did not know what the man carrying heavenly message was doing but really happened; he thought it might be a eye passover thing. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
They.d passed the first and second guarding people group and came to the iron gate which was road to the city. It opened them by itself for them.d, and they.d went through the road. When they had walked through that road, suddenly the man carrying heavenly message left him.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
Fit\u232? came back to his senses and said, Now I know without a doubt that the Lord has sent his man carrying heavenly message to rescue to me from Erod's hands and from every Ju people's hope."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
When he realized this, he went Meri's house, the mother of the Jon Mak, where many people gathered for talking with God. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
Fit\u232? began to knock in the gate, and working girl name Roda came to answer it. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
When girl recognized Fit\u232?'s voice, joy came surpassed her, she ran back quickly without opening door and told, "Fit\u232? is at the door!"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
They told her, "Your mind is tricking you." When she kept talking that it is true, they said, "It must be a man carrying heavenly message(angel) for helping him."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
But Fit\u232? kept on knocking. When they opened the door and saw Fit\u232?, they were amazed. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
Fit\u232? motioned with hand for them to be quiet down and described them how the Lord had brought him out of darkness house. He said, "Tell Jems Yesu's younger brother and the other friends about this." And then he went to another place.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
The next morning there was big counfusion among the soldiers what had happened to Fit\u232?. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
Later Erod tried to start to find Fit\u232? but did not see him, he started to ask/court to the guards and put them to death.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Erod was died
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Then Erod went from Judia area to Kaisaria city so he stayed there. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
He was angry to the people of Taire and Sidon country, so they went together to see Erod. Firstly they asked Blastus, the chief of guard of Erod's house in order to help them. Then they went to Erod and asked not keep on stopping food because the country of Taire and Sidon always were taking food from the ruling man Erod's country.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
On the appointed day Erod dressed in his titlename cloth; sat on his ruling sitting place and gave a public talk(speech) to the people. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
They shouted, "This is the voice of god, not of a man." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
Immediately, because Erod did not give praise to God, so a man carrying heavenly message of the Lord struck him, so worms began to eat Erod and he died.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
But the talk of God grew with healthy and became wide.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
When Barabas and Sol had finished their.d work, they returned from Jerusalem to Antiok with Jon Mak.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 13
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 They sent Banabas and Sol
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
In the Yesu's family(church) of Antiok there were God's people who make know(prophets) and teaching men. They were Banabas, Saimon [called] black [skin]man, Luses from Sairia city, Manaen(who was close relatives of Erod), and Sol. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
When they were worshiping the Lord with fasting, the God Spirit said, "Set apart Banabas and Sol for me for the work which I chose for them.d." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
So after their fasting and talking with God, they laid hands on them and sent them.d off.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fol and Banabas preached them good news at Saifrus
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
They two went on their way in the God Spirit, went to Selosia town and traveled to Saifrus town from there. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
When they.d arrived to Salamis town, they.d began to preach the talk of God through the Ju meeting houses(meeting houses). They were with Jon [as]their helper.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
They traveled around whole region until they arrived at Fafos village. There they met Bar-Yesu. He was a Ju sorcery man and false word telling man(prophet) name Bar-Yesu. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
He worked for Sergius Faulus, who has many knowledge and was the head man of Rom soldiers in this land. Sergius Faulus wanted to hear the talk of God and he sent them to/for them Banabas and Sol. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
But sorcery man Elimas(this is meaning of Bar-Yesu's name) told him and tried to turn away from the big mind(faith) of the big man. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
Then Sol, who was also called Fol, filled with the God Spirit, looked straight him at Elimas and said, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
"You are the child of S\u225?if\u232?r and the fighting man(enemy) of all straight! You are full of all kinds of deceit and liers. Stop, do not turn away people from Lord's straight way with lying! {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
Now the Lord's anger will get you. You will be blind, and for a while you can't see the light of the sun.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Immediately mist and darkness covered him, and he lost(was blind) then he was looking for someone to lead him by the hand. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
When the Rom soldiers' head man saw what had happened, he was amazed at the teaching of the God's talk, he truly approved(believed) in the Lord.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fol and Banabas preached them good news at Antiok city in Fisidia big area(district)
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
From Fafos, Fol and with his group traveled with big boat to Fargat in Famfila, but Jon left them and went back to Jerusalem. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
From Fargata they went on to Antiok city in Fisidia big area. On the Safat they endered Ju people's meeting house(synagogue) and sat down. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
After reading the law of Moses and the God's man who make know(prophet)'s talk, the head men of meeting house sent the talk to them, "Friends/Brothers, if you have any talk of encouragement for these people, please speak."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
Fol stood, lift up his hand and said, "People of Israil and you Side people who worship God, listen to me! {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
The God of the Israil people chose our ancesters and made the people wide during their staying in Ijif, and God took them out and led from that country with his power, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
