In the past when people did not know what God wanted them to do, God did not put them into pain because they have no knowledge, but now God says every people everywhere to turn away from sins. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
God has appointed a day when he will judge the world. He has appointed a man to judge us straightly. God has shown this man, whom God has appointed to judge the world, he is able to judge the world because God raised him from death."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
When they heard about a man's rising from the death, some made fun of him, but some said, "We want you talk to us again about this talk's meaning." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
After this meeting Fol left. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
Some people became followers of Fol and truly approve(believe). Among them was Dionisus, who was from the group of Areofagus, also woman name Damaris and also other people.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 18
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fol preached the good news in Korint
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
After this, Fol left Aten city and went to Korint city. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
There he met a Ju man name Akwila from Fontus. He came from Italia with his wife Frisila, because Rom high leading man(Emperor) Kaisar Klaudias said, "You Ju people, you.p should leave Rom." Fol went to see Akwila a Frisila, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
because Fol was a canvas huose making man(tentmaker) as they were, Fol srayed and worked with them. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
Every Safat Fol discuss with them in meeting house, in order that he make heart soft(convince) the Ju people and Side people.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
When Sail\u232?s and Timoti arrived from Makedonia, here Fol was trying to make known Ju people that Yesu was Keriso. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
But Ju people opposed Fol and said to wicked talk. So he shook the dust from his clothes and said, "If God put you in suffering/pain, it will be your fault, not my fault. From now I will go to the Side people."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
Then Fol left the Ju people's meeting house and went to next house, to Taitus J\u232?stus' house who was a worshipper of God. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
Krisfus, the head man of Ju people's the meeting house, and his family truly approved(believed) in the Lord and many of Korint people who heard him, truly approved(believed) and we baptized them.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
One night the Lord said to Fol in a eye passover thing, "Don't be afraid, keep on talking, do not be silent and not stop. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
Because I am with you, and someone cannot make stop and spoil/harm you, because there are many my people in this city." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
In this reason Fol stayed in Korint for a year and a half he taught them the talk of God.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
When Galio became governor of Akaya big area, some Ju people got together to stop Fol and brought him to the court. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
They said, "This man is leading the people to worship God in different way in this way he broke our law."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
Fol was about to speak, Galio said to ju people, "If you Ju people made a complaint about this problem, show me well, I will listen to you.p. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
But this included about a question of speakings and names and your.p law, settle/solve this things by yourselves. I will not be in your.p court about this things. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
So he took/sent them off from the court. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
Then they all caught/hold Sostenes the Ju people's meeting house leading man [and] began to beat him in front of the court. But Galio did not think about it.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Frisila, Akwila and Afolos
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
Fol stayed on with the believers in Korint for many days. Then he left the people who truly opprove(believers) there, and went with Frisila and her husband Akwila. They went down to Sens\u232?ri. There Fol had his head shaved in order to follow his without.lying(promise) to God. Then they went to Siria area with big bout. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
They stopped at Efesos city, Fol left Frislia and Akwila. He himself went into the Ju people's meeting house and was discussing with Ju people. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
When they asked him to stay with them, [but] he declined. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
But when Fol left, he said without lying talk(did without-lying talk), "I will come back in the God's willing." Then he left Efesos and was coming to Kaisaria. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
When he arrived at Kaisaria area, he went to Jerusalem and gave a greeting the Yesu's family(church), and went back to Antiok area.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
After staying some days, Fol walked from Antiok around the region of Galatia area and Frigia area, gave strength to all the following men.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
Ju people name Afolos from Aleksandria region, came to Efesos. He was with the knowledge of the Buk(scripture). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
He taught the way of the Lord, spoke with buring heart and taught about Yesu well, but he knew only the baptism of Jon. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
He began to speak without.fear in the Ju people's meeting house. When Frisila and Akwila heard him, they invited him to their house and explained to Afolos the way of God straightly.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
When Afolos wanted to go to Akaya big area, friends encouraged him and wrote the letter to the following men in Akaya big area to accept him. In his arriving, he became a big help to those who had truly approved(believed) through God's grace. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
He discussed with the Ju people in public, he tried to put clearly from the Buk talk(Scripture) that Yesu was Keriso.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 19
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fol speaks in Efesos about Yesu
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
While Afolos was in Korint city, Fol walked through the bank/interior and he arrived at Efesos city. There he found some following men {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
and he asked them, "Did you.p receive the God Spirit when you truly approved(believed) Yesu?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 They answered him, "No, we did not hear that there is a God Spirit."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
So Fol asked them, "What baptism did you.p receive?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 They answered him, "Jon's Baptism."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
Fol said, "Jon's baptism was to turn from sins. Jon told the people to truly approve(believe) Yesu, who was coming after him." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
On hearing this, baptized them in the name of Lord Yesu. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
When Fol placed his hands on them, the God Spirit came to them, and they spoke with other talks(languages) and proclaimed God's talk. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
There were perhaps 12 men.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
Fol went into the Ju people's meeting house and spoke without fearing there for three months. He was discussing with them and tried to cause to truly opprove(believe) about ruling of God. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
But some men became heart-harden(stubborn); they rejected to truly approve(believe) and publicly said evil talk about the way of God. So for this reason Fol left them. He took the following men with him [and] discussed everyday in the teaching house of Taranus. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
He spend two years in talk, so that all Ju people and Side people who lived in Esia heard the talk of Lord.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
God gave Fol the power to do special workings(miracles). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
People put handkerchiefs or clothes that Fol touched to the sick people, they became good and evil spirits were going out.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
Some Ju people went [and] tried to chase out evil spirits in the name of Lord Yesu over those who evil spirit possessed. One [of them] said, "In the name of Yesu, whom Fol preaches, I command, "Come out." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
A Ju chief burning sacrifice men(chief priest) Skefa's seven sons were doing this work. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
One day the evil spirit answered them, "I know Yesu and I know Fol, but who are you.p?" {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
Then the man with the evil spirit jumped on them and chased them all and beated them. They ran from the house naked and bleeding.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
There Efesos when the Ju people and Side people in the Efesos heard about this, they were afraid, they honored Lord Yesu's name. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
Many who bacame truly appove people(believers) started to report(confess) their evil things. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
Some people who learned/practiced sorcery they brought thier sorcery books and burned them publicly. When they counted the price of people's books was several million kina. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
So the talk of the Lord became widely and became with power.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
After all this had happened, Fol decided to go to Makedonia and Akaya and Jerusalem. Fol said, "After that I must go to Rom." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
So he sent his two helpers, Timoti and Erastus, to Makedonia, but he stayed more in Esia.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Trouble in Efesos
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
At that time trouble developed in Efesos because of God's Way. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
There was a man name Demetrios, who made silver models of the worshipping house of the Artemis the goddess. Those who worked they found/earned a lot of money. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
Demetios gathered his workers and said, "Friends, listen, you.p know we find/earn a lot of money for this work. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
You.p have seen and knew how Fol has make them inside softly/convinced and led many people to other teaching in Efesos city and through whole Esia area. He said that gods made by man are not god. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
This thing is without.joy because our way to find money will finish. Like that the worshipping house of the big woman god Atemis will be without.meaning, to whom they worship in Esia and the world. People will not think that the woman god Atemis is god."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
When they heard this talk, they were angry and started shouting like with talk, "Great is big woman god Artemes of Efesos." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
The city joined and shouted because there were one mind. People grabbed Gayus and Aristakus, Fol's travelling friends came from Makedonia area, and people forced them to the meeting place. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
Fol wanted to go meeting place, but following men did not allow him to go to there. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
Some government workers who were Fol's friends, they sent talk him urgently not to go to the meeting place.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
The crowds were wondering because they were various shouting. Many people did not know the reason/why they were there. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
The Ju people sent Aleksand\u232? to them to say. He motioned for silence with hand. He wanted to tell them that Ju people had not developed the problem. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
But when they realized that he was a Ju, they were shouting for two hours like that, "Big is Atemis of the Efesos!"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 35\~}
A city government working man stopped them and said, "People of Efesos, You.p know that the city of Efesos is guarding man of the worshipping house of the big woman god Artemis and this woman's face image came down from heaven. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 36\~}
Nobody can say that she did not come down from heaven. Be calm. Do not rush into anything. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 37\~}
You brought these men here, they did not say badly to our god and they did not steal anything from our god's worshipping house. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 38\~}
Then if Demetrius and his worker have a case against them, the court are open and there are a judge. They can say about this things. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 39\~}
If there are more complaint, they take to the court. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 40\~}
And so we know, that if head people hear what we did today, they will still talk to us about creating big trouble. We did it without.reason, so what we will say if they ask us about this. " {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 41\~}
After saying this, he sent people.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 20
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fol traveled through Makedonia and Grik country
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
When the noising ended in the city, Fol went to the following people, and encouraged them. Then he said, "Goodbye" and went to Makedonia region. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
He traveled through those regions, after speaking many talks of encouragement to the people Fol arrived in Grik country, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
there he stayed three months. He decided to go back with big boat(ship) to Siria region, but he heard that some Ju people decided to kill him. So he decided to return through land [through] Makedonia. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
Sofata Firus's son from Berea area, Aristakus and Sekudus from Tesalonika area, Gaius from Derbe area, Timoti also, Tukikus and Trofimus from province of Eisia went with Fol. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
These men went on ahead and waited for us at Traus town. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
But we came from Filifi city after the Festival of without.yeast bread. 5 days later we joined them at Traus city, where we stayed 7 days.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yutikus raised from the death at Traus town
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
On Sunday we came together to eat bread . Fol spoke to the people and kept on speaking until midnight, because he was making to go the next day. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
There was many lights in the house where we gathered. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
There a young man name Yutikus sitting on the window. As Fol continued talking for a long time, Yutikus was feeling sleepy. Finally he felt a sleep on the third floors and from there fell down to the ground. When they picked him up, he was dead.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
Fol went down to the ground, bent over [and] put his hand to him. So Fol said, "Don't worry, he is alive!" {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
Then Fol went up again ontop, and ate bread. After Fol continued to talk until daybreak, he left. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
The people took the young man to the house and were very happy because he raised from the death.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fol meets the Efesos head people
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
Fol had said he would meet us at Asos, because he was travelling by walking. So firstly we went on to the boat and travel to Asos town. There we wanted to meet him and to take him on the boat. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
When he met us at Asos, we took him aboard and went on to Mitilan town. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
The next day we left from there and went to Kios town with big boat(ship). The day after we crossed again to Samos, two days later we arrived at Miletus town. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
Fol does not want to stay on the province of Esia, so he decided not to stop Efesos. Because he wanted to go Jerusalem quickly in time for the remembering festival name Fentikost.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
From Miletus town, Fol sent a talk to Yesu's family(church) head people from Efesos city to come to talk with him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
When head people arrived, Fol said to them, "You know how I worked among you from first day when we arrived the province of Esia. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
I worked with big low mind( humility) and with tear. I have endured pains because the Ju people made plots to kill me. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
You know that I was without fearing preaching which were helping you but I taught you publicly all through the houses. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
I preached them, to [both] Ju people and Grik people in order that they must turn from sins to God and truly approve(believe) our Lord Yesu.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
Now in the talk of the God Spirit, I will go to the Jerusalem, I don't know what will happen to me there. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
But I only know this in all cities God Spirit said that in Jerusalem people will put me into the darkness house and will put me in suffering. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
But my bodily life is without.meaning but this is meaningful to me: that I will finish the race which the Lord Yesu gave me, of the work/task of preaching to the good talk about the grace of God.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
I have gone among you.p, preached the talk of the kingdom of God. But now I know that you will not see me again. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
Therefore now I talk strong talk(declare) to you.p. If some of you die truly without.opprove(without trusting)Yesu, you will not able to blame me for that. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
I was not afraid to proclaim to you whole will of God. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
Keep watch yourselves and all the Yesu's family which God Spirit has appointed you looking.after people(caretakers). Be God's Yesu's family(church) guarding people, [which]he bought them with his own blood. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
I know that, when I leave wild dogs will arrive in among you and will not spare you but strike to kill. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
So some men from your group will arise and lead the approving truth people to follow their false teaching. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
Carefully watch guard yourselves! Remember that for three years I warned each of you without.stop with tears all day and night.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
Therefore now I commit you.p to God and to the talk of the grace, which talk can stand you up and bless all of you.p whom has set apart for himself. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
I did not desire your clothing or money to me. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
You yourselves know whole that I worked with my hands for my clothes and money and also for my friends. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 35\~}
In everything I did, I showed work to you.p in order that we should help poor people, we should remember the talk of the Lord Yesu said: '\u8216?The happiness of the man who gives things surpasses the happiness of the man who gets things.\u8217? '
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 36\~}
When Fol finished talk, they all knelt and talked with God. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 37\~}
Then they hugged with weeping and kissed Fol. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 38\~}
They were without joy because which Fol said that later you.p will not see my face again. Then they accompanied him to the big boat(ship).
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 21
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fol went to Jerusalem
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
We said goodbye to them, after this we went aboard the big boat(ship) and were traveling to island of Kos. The next day we went to island of Rodas and from there to Fatara area. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
We found a big boat(ship) crossing to Fonisia area, we went on board and went again. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
After we saw Saifrus area, and passing to the south to Siria area. we landed at Taire area, there people unloaded cargo from big boat(ship). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
We saw the following men there, [and] stayed with them 7 days. By the power of the God Spirit they said to Fol not to go Jerusalem. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
When it was time to leave, we left and went to boat with all the following men and their wives and children from the city. There in the beach we knelt and talked with God. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
After they said goodbye to each other, we went aboard the big boat(ship) and they went back homes.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
After this we continued to travel from Taire and landed at Tolemais town. There we saw with joy with friends there we stayed for a day. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
The next day we arrived Kaisaria city and stayed at the Filif's house. This Filif was a preacher and one of 7 men who had been chosen to help widows. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
He had 4 single/unmarried daughters who proclaimed God's talk.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
We had been there many/several days, the God's man who make know(prophet) name Agabus came from Judia. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
He came to us, he took Fol's belt. The he tied up his own hands and feet and said this talk, "The God Spirit said, 'Like this Ju people in Jerusalem will tie the owner of this belt up and will give him the Side people's hands.'"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
When we heard this talk, we and other people said to Fol not to go Jerusalem. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
Then Fol answered us, "Why are you weeping and making pieces(breaking) my heart? I am ready to be bound and to die in Jerusalem for the name of Lord Yesu." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
How could not we make soft(persuade) him, so we stop and said, "The Lord's will be done."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
After this, we prepared and went to Jerusalem. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
Some of the following men from Kaisaria followed us and took us to the house of Nason, where we were to stay there. He was a man from Saifros and one of the early/first following men.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fol arrived at Jerusalem
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
When we arrive at Jerusalem, the belivers welcomed us with joy. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
The next day Fol and other people went to Jems, and all the head people were there. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
Fol greeted them and told everything what God had done to the Side people in his work.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
When they heard this talk, they praised God. Then they said to Fol, "Friend, you.s see how many thousands of Ju people have truly approved(believed), they all follow the law very strongly. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
These Ju people heard what you preached Ju people who live among the Side people. They think that you.p say to them, "You must not obey Moses's law any longer. You must not cut skin of your children. You must not live in the way that Ju people usally live." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
What shall we do? They will hear that you have come. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
So do what we are telling you.s. Here are with us 4 Ju men who truly opprove(believers)who said without.lying talk to God. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
Take these men to the worshipping house, join in their washing ceremony(ceremony of purificaton) and pay for the offering sacrifice. After that they will shave their heads. Then every people will know there is not truth in their reporting talk about you.s, but you.s yourself are living as how law said. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
As for the side approving truth people, we wrote to them our thought that they must not eat food for idols, and blood, and meat without taking out blood, and also sex out of (marriage)."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
The next day Fol went with the men and they did what was spoken for washing. After they did that, he went to the worshipping house area and told the man who burn the sacrifice(priest), "When the amount of days for becoming without.dust are finished, we will bring sacrifices for that."
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 They held Fol
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
When the 7 days passed almost, some Ju people from the province of Esia saw Fol in the worshipping house area. They get angry and gathered the crowd [and] grapped Fol. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
And they said that, "Men of Israil, help us! This is the man who teaches every people everywhere spoiled our people and our law and this worshipping house. He brought Grik men into the worshipping house and defiles this without.dust(holy) place." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
For the reason they spoke this way was because they had seen outside man Trofimus from Efesos with Fol in the city and they thought that Fol escorted him into the worshipping house.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
The whole city people ran from all directions. There they caught Fol, they dragged him from the worshipping house. Immediately they closed the worshipping house gate. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
They began to strike Fol when the Roman soldiers big head man heard that the whole city of Jerusalem was in the noise. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
He at once took some soldier's head men and soldiers and ran to the crowd. When the killers/riots saw the soldiers' big head man of soldier and his soliers, they stopped striking Fol.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
The Soldiers big head man went and held Fol and commanded him to bind with two chains. Then he asked, "Who is he and what he did?" {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
Some in the crowd shouted he did this thing and others he did different things. But because they continued shouting so loudly, soldiers' big head man could not pick the truth. So he said to them, "Take this man into the soldier place." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 35\~}
When Fol came to the steps, the crowd became very angry. So soldiers lift him to protect him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 36\~}
The crowd who were following [and] kept shouting, "Kill him, Kill him!"
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fol spoke to the crowd
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 37\~}
When the soldiers were about to take Fol into the soldier's place, he asked the soldiers' big head man(commander), "May I say something to you?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The soldiers' big man(commander) asked Fol, "Oh, you know Grik language? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 38\~}
Are you the Ijif man who led arguing recently [and] led 4,000 soldiers into the desert?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 39\~}
Fol answered him, "No, I am not! I am a Ju man, there I was born in Tarsus city, which is famous city in Silisia. Please let me speak to these people."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 40\~}
The soldiers' big head man allowed him to talk, Fol stood on the steps and stop/make silent people. When they became quiet, he spoke to them in Ibru language
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 22{\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
"Brothers and fathers, listen to my defending talk."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
When they heard Fol speak to them in Ibru language, they became quiet.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Then Fol said, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
"I am Jew, born in Tarsus city in Silisia region, but grew up in Jerusalem. I learned the law of our fathers and Gamalel is my teacher. I have wanted to obey God carefully as all of you do today. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
I hit to death the people who followed this Way, [and] held men and women and threw them into darkness house. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
The leading burning sacrifice man and all the Ju head men's meeting can testify of this talk is true. They gave me letters to Ju people in Damaskos. So I went there to bring these men as darkness house men(prisoners) to Jerusalem to put punishment.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
One day about noon, when I was getting close to Damaskos, suddenly strong light from heaven shone around me. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
I fell to the ground and heard a voice and said to me that, 'Sol! Sol! Why are you hitting me?'
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
I asked, "Who are you, Lord?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 He answered me, "I am Yesu from Najaret. You are hitting me,' {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
My companions saw the light, but they did not understand his voice who was speaking to me.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
I asked him, "What shall I do, Lord?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The Lord said to me , "Get up, go into Damaskos. There a man will tell everything what you do.' {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
My groups/companions led me by the hand to Damaskos, because strong light had me blind.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
A man name Ananias came to see me. He was God worshipper and highly respected by the Ju people who were all living there. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
He stood close me and said, 'Brother Sol, see!' At once I saw [and] found Ananias!
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
Then Ananias said, 'The God of our fathers chose you to know his will and to see straight man and to hear talk from his mouth. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
You will be his watching man to all people of what you have seen and heard. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
Now why are you waiting? Get up, they will baptize you and God will forgive your sins by talking with God in Keriso's name."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
After this I went back to Jerusalem, I was talking with God in the worshipping house. I saw a eye passover thing {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
and the Lord said me, "Quickly go & leave Jerusalem because they will not accept your reporting/testifying talk about me.'
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
I answered him, "Lord, these people know about me that I went from one meeting house to another. I held them to put in the darkness house and beat people who truly approve(believe) you. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
When people killed Stif\u232?n because he said to people about you, I stood there and was one mind with them. I took care of the clothes of those who were killing Stif\u232?n.'
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
Then the Lord said to me, "Go, I will send you far away to the Side people."
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fol reported I am a Rom man
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
The crowd were listening carefully to Fol until (when) he spoke about Side people. Then they raised voices with angry and shouted, "Remove this man from this land! He is not fit to live!"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
They were shouting and shaked his clothes and threw dust into the air. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
The soldiers' big head man sent his men to take Fol to the Soldiers' place(fortress). He told his men to beat Fol. In this way he wanted his men to find out why the crowd shouted at Fol. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
When the soldiers were about to beat Fol, he said to the soldiers' head man, "It is illegal to beat a Roman people whose evil they has not found!"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
When the soldiers' head man heard this talk, he went to the soldiers' big head man(commander), asked him, "Do not do this to this man. This man is a Roman citizen."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
The soldiers' big head man(commander) went to Fol and asked him, "Tell me, are you really a Roman citizen?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fole answered him, "Yes, I am really."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
Then the soldiers' big head man(commander) said, "I paid a lot of money for becoming Rom people."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fol answered him, "But I was born as a Roman citizen."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
Soldiers who were about to whip and to ask Fol, at once they didn't do it. The soldiers' big head man was afraid, because he told his men to bind Fol, but Fol was a Roman citizen.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fol stood before Ju head men's meeting
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
The next day, the soldiers' big head man were looking for the reason why the Ju rejected Fol. So the next day the soldiers' big head man take the chains off Fol. He also said to/ordered the leading sacrifice burning people(high priests) and whole Ju head men to gather. He brought Fol and had him stand before Ju head men.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 23{\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
Fol looked straight to Ju head men' meeting and said, "My brothers, I did my work to God until now with good thinking/conscience." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
Then Ananias the leading burning sacrifice man commanded men who were standing close Fol to strike him on the mouth. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
Then Fol said to him, "God will strike you, you look good outside but inside you rotten! You sit to judge me according to Moses's law, but you break the law by ordering them to strike me."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
Those who were standing near Fol said, "You are insulting God's leading burning sacrifice men!"
