But I have not found his bad action which he is put to death. But because he said again he wanted Kaisar to his his complaint(case). So I have made mind(decided) to send him to Rom.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
I don't know what I should write to the Roman Rom high ruling man(emperor) about him. Therefore I have brought him to all of you. The ruling man(king) Agrifa, I ask you to listen carefully to what Fol says. Then we can talk about the problem together. Later I will write a straight letter to Kaisar. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
I say that because if we send a darkness house man(prisoner) to the Roman high ruling man without reason, then that would not be good."
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 26{\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
Then Agrifa said to Fol, "Speak now."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 So Fol raised his hand and said his defending talk, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
"King Agrifa, I am glad before you.s today as I make defence against all complaints of all the Ju people, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
because you know well about how Ju people live and their different doing. So you listen to me patiently!
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
"All the Ju people know about me since I was a child. They knew what kind of life I have lived in my own country and in Jerusalem. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
They knew about me for a long time. They will tell that I was a Farasi man. I straightly followed God's law like as all Farasi men are doing. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
My hope is by what God had said to our ancesters, this is the reason I am on trial today. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
He promised a big thing to our 12 Israil families. We all expect to receive what God has promised to us. That is why we Ju people always worship God in the day and in the night. Like these Jews here, I believe in God's promise. But that is the reason that they complained to me. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
God can cause dead people to become alive again. You should believe me when I say this.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
I wanted to work and to oppose Yesu of Najaret. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
That is what I did in Jerusalem. On the authority of the leading sacrifice burning people(high priests), I put many of God's people into darkness house. When our leading men said, "These truly approving people must die," I became one thought/mind(agreed) [with] them. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
Many time I went around meeting house to punish them. I forced them to wicked talk to God. I was pursuing to angry with them and chased them through foreign people cities.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
One day I was on the way to Damaskas with the authority and sending of the leading sacrifice burning people(high priests). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
Ruling man(King) Agrifa, about noon, when I was on the road, I saw a light from heaven, not like the light of the sun, but surpassing that, shone and surounded me and traveling people with me. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
We all fell down to the ground, and I heard a voice saying in Ibru language, "Sol, Sol, why are you beat me? When you bump your foot for sharp point of stick, you will feel pain."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
Then I asked him, "Who are you, Lord?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The Lord answered me, "I am Yesu, whom you are hitting. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
Get up and stand on your feet. I have appeared to you and chosen you for my works and a witness. You will tell about me what you have seen and will see contiually. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
I will save you.s from the Ju people and the Side people. I am sending you.s to Side people {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
to open their eyes and turn them from the darkness to light, and from the power of S\u225?if\u232?r to God. So they will receive throwing the sin and be given a place among God's people who truly approve(believe) me."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
So King Agrifa, I was obedient in the eye pass thing(vision) from heaven. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
First I told to whom were in Damaskos, also to them in Jerusalem and all Judia and all the Side people. I preached in order that they must turn from sins to God and do the things that would show by thier turning action. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
For this reason some Ju people held me in the worshipping house courts and tried to kill me. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
But God helped me every day until now. So I stand here and testify the true talk to without.name people and with.name people. I am saying this what the God's people who make know(prophets) and Moses said would happen: {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
Keriso would suffer, and be first to rise from the death, would bring the talk of light to his own people and to the Side people.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
While Fol was still speaking, Festus shouted, "Fol, you are crazy. Your big learning caused you crazy!"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
But Fol answered him, "Big respectful Festus. I am not crazy. What I am saying is true and with.meaning/reasonable. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
The ruling man(king) knows about these things. I speak without fear to you. I know that the ruling man(king) know what I am saying, because this thing did not happen secretly in a corner. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
King Agrifa, do you truly approve(believe) the God's people who make know(prophets)? I know you do."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
Then Agrifa said to Fol, "Do you think in a not.long(short time) you can make me quickly a truly approve man(believer)?"
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
Fol answered, "Short or long time, my talking with God for you and all who are listening to me today may become truly approve people(believers) like I am, but I do not want you to become darkness people(prisoners) like me."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
The ruling man(king), the governor, Bernis and all who was with them stood up. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
After they left and they began saying among themselves, "This man is not doing anything that put do death or putting into darkness house."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
Agrifa said to Festus, "If this man had not spoken to Kaisar to hear his talk, then we could take him out."
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 27
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fol traveled to Rom with big boat(ship)
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
When it was decided that we would go to Itali, they gave and some other darkness house men(prisoners) to a soldiers' head man (named) Juli\u232?s . He belonged to high ruling man's soldiers group(Emperor's Army). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
We went on to a big bout that had come from Adramitum. This ship was prepared [to go]. It would travel to towns on the coast of Esia region. We got on that ship. A man name Aristakus who was from Tesalonika city in Makedinia province, we went with him.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
The next day we arrived at Sidon. Juli\u232?s was kind to Fol and allowed him to see to the friends so that they could give him his wanting things. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
When we left Sidon city, [and] because strong wind were pushing us back, so we sailed through the side of the island of Saifr\u232?s where the wind did not blow strongly. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
After this we crossed over the sea to the coast of Silisia and Famfilia area, we arrived at Mira town, in Lisia region. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
In Mira town, there the soldiers' head man found an Aleksadria people's bout which it was preparing go to Italia, so he put us on the bout.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
We traveled slowly for several days, and had a hard time arriving off S\u232?nidus region. The wind would not let us go that place, so we traveled to the southern of the island of Krit, passing by Cape(point) Salmone. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
We went slowly along the coast and arrived at the place name Safe Harbors, not far from the town of Lasia.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
By now we had spent a lot of time. so it would be bad(dangerous) if you still traveled by boat because after Ju people's big fasting day sea became very stomy. So Fol said to people in the boat, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
"Friends, listen to me if we go now our big boat(ship) with cargoes will be problem, and we will lost many lives." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
But the soldiers' head man not listen to Fol what he said, but followed the so boat driver(captain) and its owner's talks. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
Because the harbor was not good to spend the raining season(winter) for their staying, many people wanted pass to the harber name Foniks to spend the raining season(winter). Foniks harbor was open to the sea in two ways and strong winds did not blow there.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The big wind
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
When a gentle south wind began to blow, they saw good time to go. So they pulled up anchor and went along the coast of Krit. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
But a big wind(storm) name Northeast wind suddenly came them and blew from the island. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
The wind blew strongly against the boat. It was not possible for the bout drivers(sailors) to sail the boat straight into the wind. Then they let boat the wind took it. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
We went along the island of Kauda. The sailors lifted the boat's ndingi out of water for the safety. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
so they lift ndingi up to big bout. After this they started tying around big bout with rope to make strong. Because they were afraid that might be hitting on the stone off the Siritis, they lowered the holding the holing metal of bout(anchor) and let the big boat(ship) be carried by the wind. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
The storm brew so strong, so the next day they began to throw the thing(cargo) from the big boat(ship). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
On the third day they began to throw some big boat(ship) working things. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
For several days we could not see the sun and star. The storm kept blowing strongly and so we came to finish our hope of being saved.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
In this reason we did not eat any food for a long time. Fol stood and said to the people: "You should have listened to me when you were in island of Krit, you would not see this damage and spoiled/lost things. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
But now I ask you, don't be afraid because no one will be lost, only the big boat(ship) will be destroyed. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
I belong to God, and I worship him. Last night he sent a man carrying heavenly message {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
said to me, "Fol, don't be afraid! You will stand trial before the Rom high ruling man(Roman emperor). Because of you.p God will save all who were on the big boat(ship)." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
So don't be afraid! I know that God will do exactly what he said. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
But big bout will bestroyed we will on some island."
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The big boat(ship) destroyed
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
In 14th night wind drove us around over the Mediterian sea. But midnight the bout working men(sailers) realized we were getting near land. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
They measured depth of water was 40 meter. After this they measured again and found there was 30 meter. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
the bout working men(Sailers) were afraid because we might hit some rocks. Then they let down 4 anchors from the back and they started talking with God for daylight.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
The sailers wanted to leave the big boat(ship). So they lowered the ndingi into the sea. They tried to go away secretly. They said, \u8216?We are going to the front of the big bout to put big bout's holding metal(anchors) down into the sea.\u8217? But they cheated. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
But Fol said to the soldiers' head man and the soldiers, "If the boat working men(sailers) don't stay on the big boat(ship), you have no hope for us to be saved. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
Then the soldiers cut the ropes which held the nding and let it fall into the sea.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
Just before dawn Fol asked them to eat food, and said. He said to them, "For 14 days you have been so worried and you haven't eaten food. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
I ask you, then, eat food, your so you will live. Do this and you will be fine."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 35\~}
After talk, Fol took a piece of bread and gave thanks to God. Then in front of every people, he borke the bread and ate it. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 36\~}
They all peased and ate some food. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 37\~}
There were 276 people on the big boat(ship). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 38\~}
When they eat and satisfied, they threw the flawabaik(bag of wheat) into the sea to make (bout)light.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 39\~}
In the next morning, they did not recognize the land, but they saw a bay with sandy beach. So they saw mind(decided) to run through the sand. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 40\~}
They cut the ropes of anchors so left them in the sea. At the same time they untied the ropes which were holding the stears. Next they stand up the saimai(Note. this word means sail from Nemo language) at head/front of the big boat(ship) and the wind started to carry the big boat(ship) to the beach/sand. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 41\~}
But the big boat(ship) hit a sandbank. The front of the big boat(ship) stuck there and could not move, and strong waves struck the back of the big boat(ship) and everything was destroyed.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 42\~}
The soldiers did not want to no one swam to land and ran way so they planed to kill the darkness house men(prisoners). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 43\~}
But the soldiers' head man wanted to save Fol and he didn't allow doing this things. Instead he said, "Everyone who can swim, jump into the water first. Then swim to the land. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 44\~}
You other people must follow them. Hold on to pieces of wood, or pieces of the ship.\u8217? So they were reached to the land safely.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 28
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fol was on the island of Malta
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
When we safely arrived, we learned the island name Malta. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
The island people who were living they accepted well and became friend. They made a fire and accepted us all because it was raining and cold.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
Fol carried some fire sticks and put them on the fire. The heat of the fire caused a snake to came out and bit him on the hand. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
When the island people saw the snake hanging from his hand, they said among themselves, "This man must be a murderer! He didn't drown in the sea, but god has not allowed him to live." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
But Fol shook a snake off into the fire and there was no problem. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
The people kept thinking that he would swell up from wound or suddenly dying. But after waiting a long time and nothing happened to him, they reached(changed) their mind and said, "He is a god."
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
There was governor Fablis in the island, he owned some of the land around there. Fablis was graciful to us and invited us into his home for three days to stay. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
His father was sick in matress(bed) with fever and stomach troblem. Fol went into talking with God and he placed his hands on him and was became good. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
When this thing happened, the sick people from the island came and became good. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
They were honoring us in many ways, and when we were [time] to go, they gave us [everything] we needed.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fol arrived at Rom
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
Three month after wind destroyed the big boat(ship). The big boat(ship) docked at Malta for wind in the winter. It was Aleksandrian big boat(ship) and there were two gods on the head of the big boat(ship), a we traveled in a big boat(ship). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
We traveled through the sea and arrived Sirakus town and stayed there three days. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
From there we arrived at Regium town. The next day the south wind began to blow up, and two days later we arrived at Fotioli. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
There we found some Yesu's following men, who invited us to spend 7 days with them. And so we came to Rom. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
Some of Yesu's following men in Rom heard about us and came to meet us at the market of Afius and at the village name Three guesthouse. When Fol saw them, he thanked God and received blessing. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
When we arrived at Rom, they allow Fol to live by himself with a soldier was guarding him.
