But there is a very big difference between Ed\u232?m's sin and God's giving grace. This one man, Ed\u232?m's sin brought death to all the people. But how very big is God's grace and gift [that] came throuth the other one man, Yesu Keriso who brought very big blessing for all the people. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
Also God's gift is not like the payment(result) of Ed\u232?m's sin. Ed\u232?m's sin led to spoil(condemnation), but we have free gift which God allowed, even though we are trouble(guilty) of many sins. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
Ed\u232?m's sin brought death, through this one man. How much more will those who receive God\u700?s grace and his gift of straight thing, because all who receive it will live in triumph over sin and death through this one man, Yesu Keriso!
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
So, Ed\u232?m's sin brought trouble(condemnation) to all people, but Keriso's one action of straight thing brings a straight friendship with God and new life for them every people. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
Because one man rejected God, all the people became sinner. But because one man obeyed God, all the people will become straight.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
God gave them the law so that sin might increase. But where sin increased, God's grace increased very big. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
Just as sin ruled people in death, now God's grace rules us like this, giving us straight standing with God and bringing us to eternal life through Yesu Keriso our Lord.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 6
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Dead in sin but life in Keriso
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
Someone might say, 'We should keep on doing sin so that grace may increase.' {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
Never! We have died from sin, how can we continue to sin? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
You.p should know that all of us who were baptized into Keriso Yesu joined him into his death. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
We have been buried with him through baptism into his death in order that, just as Keriso was raised from the dead through the big power of his Father, we also may live a new lives.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
Because if we are one with him together through his death, we will also rise from death just as he rose from death. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
We know that he(God) nailed our old bodly desire in the cross with Yesu. This happened so that bodily desire will not lead us sin, and so that we are no longer without.payment working men(servants) of sin. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
Because anyone who died from sin has stopped it.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
So, if we have died with Keriso, we think that we will also live with him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
We know that because Keriso was raised from the dead, he cannot die again. Death go without.power over him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
When Keriso died, he died once to destroy the power of sin forever. Now that he lives again, he lives to serve God.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
In the same way, look to yourselves that you have died from doing sin but live for God in Keriso Yesu. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
Therefore, do not allow sin lead your.p mortal body so that you.p follow desires of sin. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
Do not allow any part of your body to do sin, as working tool for wickedness, but offer yourselves to God, just as those who came back to life. And allow your body part for God's straight thing doing. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
Sin shall not be your.p lord, because you.p are not under the law, but under God's grace.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Without.payment working men(slaves) to straight thing
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
What shall we say then? Shall we contine doing sin because we are not under the law but under God's grace? Not at all! {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
You truly know that you.p become the without.payment working man(servant) if you.p become to obey. You.p can become a without.payment working man(servant) of sin, which leads to death, or you can choose to obey God, which leads to straight thing. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
But thanks to God, though you.p were without.payment working men(servants) of sin, you.p put in heart this teaching which we have given you. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
You.p are free from sin and have become without.payment working men(servants) to straight thing.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
I am using this picture from everyday life because it is hard to understand. Previously, you.p have allowed your.p body parts to be without.payment working men(servants) of sin, you lived for sin. But now you must give yourselves as without.payment working men(servants) of straight thing to do that which is without.dirty(holy).
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
When you.p used to be without.payment working men(servants) of sin, you.p did not have to think about what was straight. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
What fruit/result did you.p receive at that time from those things? None. You.p are now ashamed of. Those things happened to death! {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
But now you.p are free from sin but became without.payment working men(servants) of God. Those things bring you life which is only for God, and those things give you enternal life. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
For the pay of sin is death, but the gift of God is eternal life in Keriso Yesu our Lord.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 7
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Example of marriage
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
My friends, do you.p not know I am speaking to the people who know the law, that the law has power for a man only while he lives? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
Showing talk(example), by law a married woman is still with her husband while his husband is alive, but if her husband dies, she finish from the marriage law. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
If she has sexual relations with another man while her husband is still alive, woman break adultery law. But if her husband dies, she is free from that law and is not an breaker of adultery law if she marries another man.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
My friends, you.p also died to the law through the body of Keriso, so that you.p might belong to another man, to him who was raised from the dead, so that we might produce fruit for God. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
When sin's desire led us, the law arouse the desire of sin which were at work in our body. In the end, sin lead us to death. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
But now, death from which bound us, we have been released from the law so that we will serve God in the new way in the God Spirit, and not by old way of the written laws.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The law and Sin
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
So, someone might say, \u8216?The law is sinful.\u8217? No! Without that law, I would not have known what sin really is. One rule says, \u8216?You must not covet other people's things.\u8217? Without this law, I would not have known what it is wrong to covet other people's things. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
But that rule gave sin a chance to come into my thoughts. In this reason, I started to want all the bad things. If there is no law to tell us what is wrong, sin is without.power.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
In the past I used to live before I know law, but later the law came, sin now had power in my life, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
and I died. God gave that law to people so that they could live in a good way, but that law brought death to me. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
That law gave sin a chance to deceive me. So, I died in the reason of that rule. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
Then, the law and its commands are without.dust(holy), and straight and good.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
So, someone might say, \u8216?This means that something good brought death to you.p.\u8217? Never! Sin brought death to me. Sin used God's good law to show that I was in trouble(guilty). Because of that, we can see that sin is really bad. Through God's good law sin works for very evil.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
We know that the law is spiritual, but I am a weak man. I am like a without.payment working man(servant) of sin. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
I do not carry what I say. For what I want to do I do not do, but what I hate I do. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
And if I do what I do not want to do, I agree that the law is good. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
So when I do things, this is not me myself doing them, but that is sin living in me.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
I know that there is nothing good in me. I am a weak man. I want to do what is good. But I am unable to do it. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
I don't do good things which I am willing to do, but I continue to do the bad things that I do not want to do. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
If I do what I do not want to do, I do not do this, but sin in me does it.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
So I understand what is happening in me. Whenever I want to do good thing, I can only choose bad thing. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
With all my heart I love God\u700?s law. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
But I see another law at work in me, making war to the law in my mind and making me darkness house man(prisoner) of the law of sin which is working in me. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
What an miserable person I am! Who will save me from this body going to die? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
Thank God, who saves me through Yesu Keriso our Lord!
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 So then, with my mind I want to follow God's law. But, immediately, I serve sin as my lord, because I am weak and human.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 8
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Life in the God Spirit
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
Therefore, for them there is not with trouble/judge who are in Keriso Yesu. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
Because living God Spirit's law through Keriso Yesu has made you.p free from the law of sin and death. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
The law which God gave to Moses could not make us well like that. We were without.power to follow his laws because we are ordinary people. But God has done what his law could not do well. He sent his own Son to become a man like us. His body was like the body of people who do wrong things. God's Son died as a sacrifice to take away the suffering for our sins. In that way, God destroyed the power of sin over people who are bodily without.power. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
God did this so that what the law require might be happened to us, who don't live in action of sinful desire but in leading of the God Spirit.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
Those who sinful desire ruled only think about only evil things. But those who live in the God Spirit think about what the Spirit wants. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
Sinful desire leads us to death, but thought of God Spirit leads us life and peace. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
The sinful desire is always fighting with God, because it does not follow God's law, and it cannot follow it. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
Those who is led by sinful desire cannot please God.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
But you.p are not led as sinful desire, God Spirit leads you.p, if God's Spirit are inside you.p. To whom the Spirit of Keriso are not inside them do not belong to Keriso. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
But if Keriso is in you.p, even though your.p bodies are going to die because of sin, but the God Spirit gaves life for you.p because Keriso has made you straight with God. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
And if the Spirit of God who raised Yesu from death lives you, he who raised Keriso from death will also give life to your.p mortal bodies by his Spirit who is in you.p.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
Therefore, my friends, we will not to live to satisfy bodily desire. We will not live like that. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
If you.p live by the bodily desire, you.p will die. But if by the Spirit you.p put to death your.p sinful actions, you.p will live. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
Because those who God Spirit leads are God's children. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
You.s have not received this spirit to make you.s fear but you.s received him become His child and in Him we shout, \u8220?Father! my Father!\u8221? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
God Spirit also agrees with our spirits that we are God's children. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
Because we are God's children, we also know that we will receive good things from him. Those things are which he has done without.lying talk(promise) to give to his children. Together with Keriso, we will receive the things that God has kept for him. That is true if we agree to have troubles like Keriso did. Then we will also enjoy life in heaven like Keriso does.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Today suffering and future big light(glory)
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
I am thinking that today suffering will not match with later big light(glory) will happen to us. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
All thing God made waits to where God's children will put clearly. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
All things God made turned without.meaning, not by his will but because God's will. But there was a hope, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
created thing(creature) looks forward to this day when it will join God's children in big light(glorious) freedom from death and mortal.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
We know that all of created thing are in pain just like the pain which they experience in childbirth until today. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
This is the same for us who are approving truth people(believers). We have received God Spirit as the first of his gifts to us, but we also cry inside ourselves. We are waiting for the time when God will finish his big work. Then we will belong to him completely as his children. Our bodies will be free from the power of sin. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
In this hope he had saved us. But hope which we see is this hope without.meaning. Who hopes for these things they already have? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
But if we hope for this thing which we do not see, we wait for it patiently.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
In the same way, the God Spirit also helps us in without.power place. Because we do not know how to talk with God. But God Spirit himself talks with(prays) God for us. He shouts to God on our behalf in a way that nobody could say with words. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
God sees what is in our hearts, and he knows what the thought of the God Spirit is, because the God Spirit talks with God on behalf of his people according to the will of God.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
We know that in all the things God works for good with those who love him, those whom he has called to do his will. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
God always know who are his chosen, he had decided they will become like his Son, so that his Son will become the firstborn among many younger brothers. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
God had already chosen those people to be his children. In this reason, he called them to come to him. He accepted those people as straight with him. And those whom he accepted, he also caused them to become big name.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 God's love in Keriso Yesu
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
Then, because of all the things [that] God does for us, we can say that: If God is working for us, anybody cannot really do anything against us. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
He who did not even keep back his own Son, but gave his own Son to die for us all! So, God will give all the things what we need with his Son. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
Nobody can say that God's people who will say that God's people are with trouble(accuse). God himself has accepted us as straight with him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
So nobody can say that God should still put us in suffering(condemn). No one. Because Keriso Yesu himself died on our behalf. And God raised him to the life for us. Now Keriso is sitting at God's right side in heaven. He himself is talking with God on our behalf.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 35\~}
Who can separate us from the love of Keriso? Can trouble or hardship or striking or hunger or nakedness or close to death or sharp knife with both side(sword)? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 36\~}
As the scripture say,
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 \u8220?For your.p sake we see the death every day;
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 we are like sheep start to be killed.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s61\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 37\~}
