\par\pard\plain \s0\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 2CO - - Nama Back Translation
\par\pard\plain \s93\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb40\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs46 Fol's second letter to the people of Korint
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 1
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
This letter is from Fol, a man with Yesu's authority(apostle) of Keriso Yesu by God's will, and from our friendr Timoti.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 I am writing to the Yesu's family(church) of God in Korint, and to all God's people throughout Akaya region.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
May God our Father and the Lord Yesu Keriso give you.p grace and peace.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fol gives thanks to God
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
Praise to God and Father of our Lord Yesu Keriso, the merciful Father and the God of all comfort. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
He helps us in all our troubles, so that we can help other people who have various troubles with the same help that we have received from God. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
Just as we are in Keriso's many sufferings, so also through Keriso we are in God's big help. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
If we are in suffering, it is for your.p help and salvation. If we are helped, you too are helped and given the strength to endure with patience the same sufferings that we endure. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
So our hope in you.p is never shaken, because we know that just as you.p share in our sufferings, you also share in our help from God.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
Friends, we want to know you.p of the trouble we had in the province of Esia. The troubles laid upon us were so big heavy and {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
We thought that we were almost died. But this happened so that we should not rely ourselves, but only on God, who raises dead men. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
He save us from very bad death, and will save us. We have placed our hope in him that he will save us again. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
and you.p are continally helping us by means of talking with God for us. It will be answered that the many talking with God for us, and God will bless us and many people will raise their voices to God in thanksgiving for us.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fol's decision again
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
We are boasting how we live our life in this world as our mind shows. Our friendships with you have been done by God's holiness and sincerity. We have done by God's grace and not by human wisdom. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
For we do not write you anything you.p cannot read or understand. And I think that, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
as you.p have understood us some, you.p will come to understand fully that you.p can boast of us just as we will boast of you.p in the day of the Lord Yesu.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
I was sure of all this that I made plans at first to visit you, so that you,p might be blessed twice. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
I wanted to visit you on my way to Makedonia and to come back to you.p from Makedonia, and you send me to Judia. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
I did not decide this carelessly. I do not make my plans from selfish things, like someone who does not know God. I do not say "Yes," and then I immediately say "No." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
God always does what he says he will do. In the same way, my without.lying talk(promise) to you was not \u8220?Yes\u8221? and a \u8220?No.\u8221? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
Timoti, Sailes and myself we preached among you.p Yesu Keriso, the Son of God, he is not one who is \u8220?Yes\u8221? and \u8220?No.\u8221? But he is God's \u8220?Yes.\u8221? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
For no matter how many without.lying talk(promise) God has made, they are \u8220?Yes,\u8221? this is why through Yesu Keriso our \u8220?Amen\u8221? is said to the big light(glory) of God. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
God who makes both us and you stand strongly in Keriso. He anointed us, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
set his seal of ownership on us(note:owner put the seal on the door of yam storage), and put his Spirit in our hearts as the guaranteeing what is to come.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
I call God as my watching man. God knows my heart. In this reason I spare/guide you that I decided not to go to Korint. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
We are not trying to order to you what you must truly approve(believe). We know that you stand strongly in the big mind(faith). But we are working with you for your happiness.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 2
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
So I decided not to come to you again to make you without.joy. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
If I make you without.joy, who will make me joy? Certainly not someone I have grieved? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
That is why I wrote my letter to you. I did not want to come to you and be made without.joy by soem people who should make me joy. I am convinced that when I am joy, then all of you are joy too. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
I wrote you.p with a big trouble and painful heart and with many tears. My thinking thing was not to make you.p without.joy, but to make you.p know how much I love you.p all.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Forgiveness for the Offender
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
If anyone has made somebody without.joy, he has not done it to me, but to all of you. I say this because I do not want to be too much angry on him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
The punishment inflicted on him by many people is enogh. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
So now you should forget him and encourage him, not to make him without.joy and to give up totally. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
And I beg you.p to make him know that your.p love is still to him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
I wrote you.p this letter because I wanted to find out how well you would stand the test and you are always ready to obey my teachings. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
When you forget man's sin for what they have done, I forget them too. When I wash, if I need to forgive anything, I do it in the sight of Keriso because of you, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
so that we will not give the space to S\u225?if\u233?r. Because we know what his thinking and action are like.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fol's worry in Troas
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
When I arrived at Troas to preach the good talk about Keriso, I found that the Lord had opened the way for the work there. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
But I was deeply worried, because I could not find our friend Taitus. So I said good-bye to the people there and went to Makedonia.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Victory through Keriso
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
But thanks be to God, who always leads us in victory in Keriso. God uses us to spread his knowedge of him everywhere like a sweet-smellig liquid. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
We are Keriso's sweet smelling liquid before God, which spreads among those who are being saved and those who are being lost. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
We are an sweet smelling liquid to whom are being lost and an sweet smelling liquid to whom are being saved. Who is equal to this work? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
We are not like many people, who preach the talk of God for their benefit. We preach the word of God with sincerity and as without.payment working men(servants) of God.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 3
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
Does this sound as if we were again boasting about ourselves? Could it be like some other people, we need approving letters to you.p or from you.p? No. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
You yourselves are our letter, written on our hearts for every people to know and read. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
It is clear that Keriso himself wrote this letter and sent it by us. This letter is, not with acid for writing(ink) but with the Spirit of the living God, and not on stone but on hearts.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
We say because we are strong(confindent) in God through Keriso. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
There is nothing in us that allows us that we are capable of doing this work. The power we have comes only from God. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
He is who made us to work for the new covenant, which is by God Spirit, not by a written law because the written law brings death, but God Spirit gives life.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
The law was carved letters on stone, and God's big light(glory) appeared when it was given. Even though the light on Moses' face was fading, it was so strong that Israil people could not watch with eyes to him. If the law, which brings death by force, came with big light(glory), {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
how the big light(glory) is to the work of God Spirit? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
If this work that brought problem(condemnation) have big light(was glorious), how big light(glorious) is the work that brings straightness! {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
What was big light(glorious) has no big light(glory) now when we compare with new big light(glory). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
And if there were big light(glory) which are without.long, how big light(glory) is which reamins forver!
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
Because we have this hope, we are very bold in our speech. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
We are not like Moses, who had to put a cloth over his face so that the people of Israil would not see the light passed away and disappeared. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
Their minds were doubt, and to this very day, their minds are covered with the same cloth when they read the old covenant. The cloth is removed only by believing in Keriso. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
Even today, whenever they read the law of Moses, the cloth still covers their minds. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
But whenever anyone turns to the Lord, this cloth is taken away. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
The Lord is the Spirit, and where the Spirit of the Lord is, there is freedom. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
And we all, who with unveiled faces contemplate the Lord\u700?s big light(glory), are being transformed into his image with ever-increasing big light(glory), which comes from the Lord, who is the Spirit.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 4
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Treasure in clay Pots
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
God has given us this work to do in his mercy, and so we do not become discouraged. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
We put aside all secret and shameful deeds. We do not deceit, nor do we preach falsefy the talk of God. In the full light of truth we live in God's sight and try to commend ourselves to every people's good mind. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
If the good talk we preach is hidden, it is hidden only from those who are being lost. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
S\u225?if\u233?r, who is the god of this age has blinded the minds of people who do not truly approve, so that they cannot see the light of the good talk that displays the big light(glory) of Keriso, who is the image of God. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
We don't preach about ourselves, but we preach Yesu Keriso as Lord, and ourselves as your without.payment working men(servants) for Yesu' sake. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
The God, who said, \u8220?Out of darkness the light shall shine!\u8221? is the same God who made his light shine in our hearts, to bring us the knowledge of God's big light(glory) shining in the face of Keriso.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
But we who have this spiritual treasure in clay pots, in order to show that the very big power belongs to God, not to us. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
We are often in trouble, but not crushed. Sometimes we are in doubt, but are not never collapsed. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
There are many enemies, but we are never without a friend, and we become bad at times, but we are not destroyed. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
In all days we carry in our mortal bodies the death of Yesu, so that Yesu's life also may be seen in our bodies. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
Our lives are we are always thorugh death for Yesu' sake, so that Yesu's life may be seen in our mortal body. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
This means that death is at work in us, but life is at work in you.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
The scripture says, \u8220?I spoke because I truly approved(believed).\u8221? In the same spirit of big mind(faith) we also speak because we truly approve(believe). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
We know that God, who raised the Lord Yesu to life, will also raise us up with Yesu and take us together with you into him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
