\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Not only were we encouraged, how happy Taitus made us with his happiness over this way in which all of you helped his mind to rejoice! {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
I am in boasting of you.p to him, and you.p have not made me without.joy. But just as everything we always said to you was true, our boasting about you.p to Titus has proved to be true. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
And his love for you.p grow strong when he remembers how you.p were ready to do his encouring talk, how you.p received him with fear and trembling. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
I am happy because I truly approve you.p to do what is straight.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 8
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Truly approving men's gift
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
Our friends, we want you.p to know what God's grace has done in the Yesu's families(churches) in Makedonia. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
They have been severely tested by many troubles they went through, but their joy was so big that they were extremely generous in their gift, even though they are very poor. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
I know that they gave as much as they could, and even more than they could give. They gave them their own will. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
They begged us repeatly helping God's people in Judia. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
This was more than what we have thought! Firstly they gave themselves to the Lord, and then by God's will they also gave themselves to us. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
So we urged Titus, who began this work, to continue it and help you.p complete this work of love. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
You.p are very rich in all you have. In big mind(faith), in speaking, and in knowledge, in your.p willingness to help and in your.p love for us. And we want you.p to be generous also in this work of love.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
I am not laying down any rules. But I show how eager other truly approving people(believer) want to give their money. In that way, I want to see what your.p love is real. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
You.p know the grace of our Lord Yesu Keriso. How rich as he was, but he made himself poor for your sake, in order to make you.p rich by means of his poverty.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
I give my thought about what is best for you in this matter. Last year you.p were the first who want to help and you.p did. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
Now you.p should finish what you started and you also want to help, so now we see and you finish this work like as you decided and started it by what now have. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
If you.p want to give, God will accept your.p gift on the basis of what you have to give, not on what you don't have.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
Our desire is not that other people might be good and you must carry great heavies, but there might be equality. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
At this time when you.p are in need and they have plenty, they will help you.p. In this way both will help equally. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
As the scripture says, \u8220?The one who gathered muny did not have too many, and the one who gathered little did not have too little.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Taitus and his friends
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
We give thanks God who put into the heart of Taitus same thought which I have for you.p to help! {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
Not only did he welcome our request; he was so eager to help that he decided to go to you on his will. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
We are sending the friend who is highly respected through all the Yesu's families(churches) for his preaching the good talk. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
And besides that, he has been chosen by the Yesu's families(churches) to travel with us as we carry out this work of love for the sake of the Lord's big light(glory) and we show that we want to help.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
We are very careful not to stir up any complaints about this generous gift. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
We are careful to do what is straight, not only in the sight of the Lord, but also in the sight of other people.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
So we are sending our friend with them. We have tested him many times and found him with good willing to help. And now that he trust you very much, he wants to help even more. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
As for Titus, he is my partner and worker friend with me to help you, as for the other friends who are going with him, in the name of many Yesu's families(churches) and bring big light(glory) to Keriso. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
Show your.p love to them, so that all the Yesu's families(churches) will know it and know that we are straight in boasting about you.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 9
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Help for needy truly approving people(believers)
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
There is really no need for me to write you.p about the help being sent to God's people in Judia. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
I know that you.p are willing to help, and I have boasted of you.p to the people in Makedonia region. I said, \u8220?The truly approving people(believers) in Akaya region have been ready to help since last year.\u8221? Your.p eagerness has led many people to help. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
Now I am sending these truly approving people(believers), so that our boasting about you.p in this thing may not turn out to be without.meaning, but just as I said, you.p will be ready to help. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
If some truly approving people from Makedonia should come with me and find out that you.p are not ready, we would be shamed because we trusted you. And I think that you would be shamed as well. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
So I thought it was necessary to urge these truly approving people(believers) to go to you ahead of me and get ready the gift which you did without.lying talk(promise) to make. Then it will be ready when I arrive, and it will show that you give because you want to, not because you have to.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
Remember that the person who plants few seeds will have a small crop, but he one who plants many seeds will have a many crop. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
Each of you.p should give, as you have decided, not with dislike mind or with duty mind, because God's love is to the one who gives gladly. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
And God is able to give you.p more than you need, so that you will always have all you need for yourselves and more than enough for every good work. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
As the scripture says,
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 \u8220?He gives generously to the needy.
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 His straight thing lasts forever.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s61\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
And God, who gives seed for the sower and bread to eat, he will also give you.p with all the seed you.p need and will make it grow and produce a very much from your giving widely. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
He will make you rich enough to be giving widely at all times, so that many people will give thanks to God for your.p gifts which they receive from us. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
This work you.p do, not only meets the needs of God's people, but also produces an outpouring in many way of thanks to God. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
And because you showed yourselves to them, your work cause many people will give big light(glory) to God for your doing to the good talk of Keriso, which you say, and for your giving widely with them and every people. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
And so with deep love they will talk with God for you.p because of this without.counting grace God has given you.p. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
Let us give thanks to God for his without.counting gift!
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 10
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fol defends his work for Yesu's family(church)
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
I, Fol, make an appeal to you.p who is mild when I am with you.p, but am strong to you.p when I am away. By the gentleness and kindness of Keriso {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
I beg you.p not to cause me to be strong when I come. Because I know that I can do strongly to those who say that we work from worldly minds. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
It is true that we live in the world, but we do not fight from worldly minds. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
The spears we use in our fight are not the world's weapons, but God's powerful spears, which we use to destroy strong defending place. We destroy false arguments. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
We pull down every proud thing which is raised against the knowledge of God and we turn every thought to Keriso. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
And after you.p have proved truly, we will be ready to punish to them who are disobeying.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
You.p are looking at the outside of things. Who gave themselves to Keriso? Well, let them think again about themselves, because we belong to Keriso just as they do. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
I am not ashamed, if I have boasted too much about the authority that the Lord has given us. But our authority builds you.p up, doesn't tear you.p down. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
Don't think that I am trying to frighten you.p with my letters. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
Someone will say, \u8220?Fol's letters are heavy and strong, but when he is with us by body, he is weak and his talks are without.meaning!\u8221? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
Such a person must understand no difference between what we write in our letters when we are away and what we will do when we are there with you.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
We would not dare to classify or compare ourselves with those who estimate themselves highly. How without.knowledge they are! They make up their own knowledge to measure themselves by, and they judge themselves by their own knowledge! {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
But as for us, we are not boast beyond into other place, but it will be within the boundary of work which God has set for us, and this includes our work among you.p. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
And since you are within those marks, we were not crossing over this marks when we came to you.p, when we bring the good talk about Keriso. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
So we do not boast about the work that other people have done beyond the boundary God set for us. Instead, we think that your big mind(faith) may grow and that we may be able to do a much big work among you.p, always within the boundary that God has set. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
Then we can preach the good talk in other countries passover you(beyond you). We do not want to boast about work which we had done in someone else's field.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
But as the scripture says, \u8220?Whoever wants to boast must boast what the Lord has done.\u8221? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
Who is really good? It is not the person who thinks good himself. It is the person that the Lord thinks good about him.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 11
\par\pard\plain \s106\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fol and the False men with Yesu's authority(apostles)
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
I think you.p will tolerate me, when I am a little foolishness. Yes, toleate me! {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
I am jealous for you.p with a godly jealousy. You are like a without.dust(holy) virgin to him who I said without.lying talk(promise) you to engage to one husband, to Keriso. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
I am afraid that your minds may somehow be led astray from your sincere and without.dust devotion to Keriso just as If was deceived by the S\u225?if\u233?r's lying. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
You.p gladly tolerate anyone who comes to you.p and preaches a different Yesu, not the one we preached. You.p accept a different spirit and a good talk completely different from the Spirit, and the good talk you received from us!
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
I do not think I am last to those who told \u8220?very strong men with Yesu's authority(apostles).\u8221? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
I may be untrained as a speaker, but I have knowledge. We have made this clear to you.p all the time and in every ways. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
I did not charge you when I preached the good talk of God to you. I humbled myself in order to make you more good. Was that wrong of me? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
While I was working among you, I was paid by other Yesu's families(churches). I was robbing them, so to speak, in order to help you. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
And during the time I was with you.p I did not bother you.p for help when I needed money. The truly approving people(believers) who came from Macedonia brought me everything I needed. As in the past, so in the future I will never be a burden to you.p! {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
By Keriso's true talk in me, I say without.lying talk(promise) that this boast in my talk will not be silenced anywhere in all of Akaya region. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
Do I say this because I am not loving you? No, God knows I love you!
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
I will go on doing what I am doing now, in order to keep those other men with Yesu's authority(apostles) from having any reason for boasting and saying that they work in the same way that we do. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
These men are false men with Yesu's authority(apostles), deceitful workers, who lie about their work and disguise themselves to look like real men with Yesu's authority(apostles) of Keriso. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
No wonder, because S\u225?if\u233?r can disguise himself like a man carrying heavenly message(angel) of light. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
It is not surprising if his without.payment working men(servants) also disguise as without.payment working men(servants) of straightness. Their end will be what their actions deserve.
\par\pard\plain \s106\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fol's sufferings as man with Yesu's authority(apostle)
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
I repeat, no one should think that I am a fool. But if you do, then allow me like a foolish man in the reason my little boasting. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
What I am talking now is not talking as the Lord would, but as a fool. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
And because many men are boasting in the way the world does, I too will do. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
You.p yourselves are wise, so you.p gladly accept fools! {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
You.p accept anyone who orders you around or takes good of you or traps you or looks down on you or slaps you in the face. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
I am ashamed to say that we were too weak to do those things!
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 But if anyone dares to boast about something. I will boast. Now I am talking like a fool. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
Are they Ibru? So am I. Are they Israil people? So am I. Are they Ebraam\u700?s descendants? So am I. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
Are they without.payment working men(servants) of Keriso? I talk like without.mind people. I am more. I have worked hard, I have been put in darkness house many times, been beaten very much, and been near darth often. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
Five times I was given 39 smashing by the Ju people. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
Three times I was beaten with sticks, once I was stoned and three times I was shipwrecked, I spent a night and a day in the sea. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
In my many travels I have been in danger from floods and from stealing men, in danger from my own people and from Side people. There have been dangers in the cities, dangers in the deserts, dangers on the high seas, and dangers from false truly approves(believes). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
I worked hard and long, often I have gone without sleep. I have been hungry and thirsty and I have often been without enough food. I have been very cold and naked. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
And not to mention other things, every day I am under the pressure of my concern for all people in the Yesu's families(churches). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
When someone is weak, then I feel weak too. When someone is led into sin, I am fell down into pain.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
If I boast, I will boast of the things that show my weakness. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
The God and Father of the Lord Yesu, who is to be praised forever, knows that I am saying true. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
When I was in Damaskos, the governor under King Aretas placed guards at the city gates of Damaskos to arrest me. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
But I was lowered in a basket through the hole of the stone wall and escaped from him.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 12
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fol's eye passovering(visions) and revelations
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
I have to boast. Even though there is nothing to be gained, I will talk about eye passoverings(visions) and revelations which were given me by the Lord. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
I know a certain truly approving man(believer) man who 14 years ago was caught up to the very high heaven. I do not know whether this actually happened or whether he had a eye passovering. Only God knows. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
And I know that this man, whether in the body or apart from the body I do not know, but God knows. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
He was caught up to happy village and heard these things which cannot be put into talks, these things that man's lips may not speak. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
So I will boast about this man, but I will not boast about myself, but only these things that show I am weak. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
Truly, if I was thinking to boast about me, I will not speak like a crazy man, because I will speak the truth. But I put down myself and I don't praise myself. I am thinking that perhaps men won't think of my talk and my real behavior and they will talk also about some of my deeds that they didn't see and they will praise me and my name will go up high for without.meaning.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
But to stop from pride because of the many good things I saw, I was given a painful thorn in the body, which acts as S\u225?if\u233?r's messenger to beat me and stop me from being proud. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
Three times I talked with God to the Lord about this and asked him to take it away. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
But his answer was, \u8220?My grace is enough for you, for my power is very big when you are weak.\u8221? I am very happy, to be proud of my weaknesses, so that I will seek Keriso's power will work to me. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
I am happy with weaknesses, insults, hardships, persecutions, and difficulties for Keriso's sake. For when I am weak, then I am strong.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fol's feeling for the truly approving people(believers) in Korint
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
I am acting like a fool, but you.p have made me do it. You.p are the ones who ought to say good thing of me. I am without.meaning, but I can match with them \u8220?true men with Yesu's authority(apostles).\u8221? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
The many surprsing things(signs) and wonderous things(wonders), these things prove that I am a man with Yesu's authority(apostle) were did among you.p with much patience. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
What I do for the other Yesu's families(churches) that I have not done for you.p, I did not put to you.p for financial help. Forgive me for doing you wrong!
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
This is now the third time that I am going to visit you.p, and I will not ake anything to you.p, because I want you.p, not your money. Children should not have to provide for their parents, but parents should provide for their children. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
I will be glad to spend all I have, and to give myself as well, in order to help you.p. Will you love me less because I love you so much?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
You will agree that I was not a burden to you. But someone will say that I was lying man, and trapped you with lying talk. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
Did I take good things from you.p through any of the messengers I sent? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
I begged Titus to go, and I sent the other truly approving man(believer) with him. Do you think that Titus took good thing of you? He and I do same minds in the same way!
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
You.p think that all along we have been trying to defend ourselves before you. No! We have been speaking in the sight of God as those in Keriso. Heartful friends, everything we do is done to help you.p. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
I am afraid that when I come I will find you.p different from what I want you.p to be and you will find me different from what you would like me to be. I am afraid that I will find quarreling and jealousy, anger and selfishness, insults and gossip, pride and disorder. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
I am afraid that the next time when I go my God will put me down in your.p presence, and I shall weep over many people who sinned in the past and have not turn away of the immoral things they have done their bad sexual thinking and and their sexual sins.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 13
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Final warnings and greeting talk
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
This is now the third time that I am coming to visit you.p. The scripture says, \u8220?What accusation are must be received by the approval of two or more watching men.\u8221? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
I have already known you.p when I was with you.p the second time. I now repeat it while I am absent. On my return I will not spare those who sinned earlier or any of the other people. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
I will give you.p all proof you.p want that Keriso speaks through me. When he works to you.p, he is not weak, but he shows his power among you.p. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
Even he was put to death on the cross in weakness, he now lives by God's power. In Keriso we also are weak, but in our relations with you.p we shall share God's power in his life.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
Put yourselves to the test and judge yourselves, to find out whether you.p are living in big mind(faith) or not. Surely you.p know that Keriso Yesu is in you.p? Unless you.p have completely failed. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
I trust you.p will know that we are not failing men. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
We talk with God that you.p will not do wrong. It is not to show that we are enough, but so that you.p may do what is straight thing, even though we may seem to be failing men. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
We cannot do any thing against the truth, but only for truth. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
We are glad when we are weak but you.p are strong. And we also talk with God that you.p will become without.flaw(perfect). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
That is why I write this letter while I am away from you. It is that when I arrive I will not have to deal badly with you in using the power that the Lord has given me to build you up, not to tear you down.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
Finally my friends, good-bye! Rejoice! Grow to maturity. Listen to my enocouraging talk. Agree with one another and live in peace. And the God of love and peace will be with you.p.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
Greet one another with the kiss of peace.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
All God\u700?s people here send their greetings.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
May the grace of the Lord Yesu Keriso, and the love of God, and the fellowship of the God Spirit be with you.p all.
\page
\par\pard\plain \s0\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 GAL - - Nama Back Translation
\par\pard\plain \s93\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb40\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs46 Fol's letter to the people of Galasia
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 1
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
This letter is from me, Fol. I was called to be(lit. he called me)for the man who has Yesu's authority. This work does not come from people group or man's authority, but from Yesu Keriso and the Father God, who raised Yesu from the death. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
I and my friends send this letter to the you.p, Yesu's family(church) through Galatia region.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
The Father God and the Lord Yesu Keriso will give you.p grace and peace. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
Keriso gave himself for our sins. He did that to save us from the present evil people section(generation). This is what our Father God wanted he did. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
To God will be very big name forever! Amen.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Here is only one good talk, not other
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
God chose you.p in order to live in the grace of Keriso. But I became without.joy of you because so quickly you.p are quickly rejecting him and you accepted a different good talk. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
Actually, there is no different good talk, but I say this because some people cause you confusion and trying to make to turn the good talk of Keriso. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
But even if we or a man carrying heavenly message(angel) will preach to you a good talk which is different from we preached to you.p before, he will be cursed! {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
We have said it before, but now I say it again: If someone preaches a good talk to you.p, but it is different from that I gave you, he will be cursed!
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
When I say these things, I am not trying to make people happy, but only God I am trying to please. If I only wanted to try to make people happy, then I will not be without.payment working man(servant) of Keriso.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 How Fol became a Yesu strong man
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
My friends, I want you.p to know that this good talk which I preached is not made by man. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
I did not receive it from man, or none taught me. Yesu Keriso himself showed it to me.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
You.d know what I have been doing at first, when I followed the Ju people's way of doing. I treated badly Yesu's family(church) and wanted to destroy them. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
I used to work hard to follow my ancestor's initiative. Regarding following Ju people's doing, I surpassed my ages people who are Ju people and I followed them very strictly. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
But God chose me in my mother's womb and called me by his grace. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
God has made mind up to reveal clearly his Son to me, so that I will preach the good talk about him to the Side people. When God chose me this work I have not talk about this with other people. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
I did not go to Jerusalem to visit those who have became men with Yesu's authority(apostles) I was later(before me). But I quickly went into Arabia region, and later I went back to Damaskos town.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
Three years later I went to Jerusalem to get to know Fit\u233?, and there we(two of us) stayed with Fit\u232? for two weeks. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
But when I was there, I even did not see any men with Yesu's authority(apostles), but only Jems, who is the Lord's younger brother. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
God knows that what I am writing to you is very true. I am not lying to you.p.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
Later, I went to Siria and Silisia wide place(provinces). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
On that time a man in Yesu's family(church) in Judia has not met me or seen my face. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
But they.p were hearing only talk about me: "This man, Fol, who used to hit us is now preaching about the big mind(faith) which at first he tried to destroy!' {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
Then they were praising God because of me.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 2
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The men with Yesu's authority(apostles) accept Fol
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
14 years later, I came back again to Jerusalem with Banabas, and Taitus with me together. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
I went because God showed me that I should go. When I was there I met with Yesu family leaders and I explained this good talk's meaning which I have being preaching to the Side people for their agreement of me. I did not want my work from before and now to be without.meaning. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
Taitus was with me, and even though he was Greek man, no one forced him to cut skin, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
I said this to you.p because lying people joined scretly to our group. They examinde our free life which is in us Keriso Yesu and cause us to be without.payment working people to their rules. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
But we did not obey to them for a minute, so that the truth of the good talk will remain to you.p.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
Other people, they think that they are leaders, did not contribute anything to my talk. This does not look burden to me whether they are big or no, because God does not examine us with outside. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
Instead, they recognized that God gave me the work to preach the good talk to the Side people, just as he gave the work to Fit\u232? to preach the good talk to the Ju people. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
God worked through Fit\u232? to do his work as a Yesu strong man to the Ju people, and he also worked through me to make my work a Yesu strong man to the Side people. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
Jems, Fit\u232?, and Jon, who were known as the leading people, they knew that God gave me this different work, then they made us friends by shaking hands. We all made one agreement that Banabas and I will work through the Side people and they will work among the Ju people. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
Their one asking was that we should help poor people in their group, which sort of work I wanted to do.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fol rebuked Fit\u232?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
When Fit\u232? came to Antiok, I rebuked him in crowd, because he did wrong openly. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
When he first arrived in Antiok, Fit\u232? had been eating with the Side people believers. Then Jems sent other Ju believers from Jerusalem to Antiok. But after these people arrived, Fit\u233? withdrew and did not eat with the Side people, because he was afraid of Jems' people who wanted the side people should cut skin. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
The other Ju people who truly approve(Ju believers) joined Fit\u232? and Banabas also joined Fit\u233?'s two minds.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
When I looked that they were not following the truth way of the good talk, I spoke to Fit\u232? in face of all the people, \u8220?You.s are a Ju man, but you live like a Side people, not like a Ju people. How do you command Side people to live like Ju always doing(customs)?\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
We were born as Ju people and not Side people with sins. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
But we know that a man is never be put straight with God through obeying the law that says, but only faith in Yesu Keriso. We also truly approved(believed) in Keriso Yesu to be put straight with God through our faith in Keriso, and not these works what law says. Because no one will be put straight with God by doing what the law says. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
If we want to become straight with God in Keriso, we must see ourselves as sinners. Does this meaning that Keriso is doing work to cause sin? Never! {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
If I start to build again the way of law which I have destoyed, I show myself to be a law breaker. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
Through the law I died to the law so that I can live for God. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
I have died with Keriso on his cross, and I am not who lives, but Keriso who lives in me. This life I live now bodily, I live by big mind(faith) in the Son of God, who loved me and gave his life for me. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
I do not put aside God's grace. But if keeping the law could make us straight with God, Keriso's death is without.meaning!
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 3
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 law or big mind(faith)
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
You without-head(foolish) Galasi people! Who places this spell to you? In your eyes is clearly the death of Yesu Keriso on the cross. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
Tell me this one thing: You receive God Spirit by the works of the law, or by believing what you heard? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
How are you so without.head(foolish)! When you.p first became the Lord's people, you.p used to live according to the power of the Holy Spirit, but now are you.p trying to live again according to the power of body? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
Were all your knowledge(Note. knowledge is from the experience) without.meaning? Really there should be! {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
God give you.p God Spirit and makes surprsing things(miracles) in you. Does God do these because you follow law, or because you heard and believe good talk? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
Think about Ebraam. The Buk(scripture) says, \u8220?He truly approved(believed) God, and because result of his big mind(faith) God accepted him as straight man.\u8221? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
So you should realize that the real descendants of Ebraam are the people who have big mind(faith). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
The Buk(scripture) told that, in the future God will put the Side people straight because of their big mind(faith). The Buk(scripture) told this future good talk to Ebraam, \u8220?Through you.s God will bless all the people.\u8221? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
Therefore Ebraam truly approved(believed) and God blessed him, therefore all who truly approve(believe) are in blessing as Ebraam was.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
Those who rely on obeying the law will live under God's curse. So the Buk(scripture) says, \u8220?Whoever does not always obey everything that is written in the book of the law is under God's curse!\u8221? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
It is very clear that God puts no one become straight with himself by the law, because the Buk(scripture) says, \u8220?The straight people will live by big mind(faith).\u8221? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
But the law does not stand(base) on the big mind(faith). Instead the Buk(scripture) says, \u8220?Whoever does everything how the law says will live.\u8221? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
Keriso saved us from the curse of the law by he became a curse for us, because Buk says, \u8220?Anyone who they hang on a tree he is in God's curse." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
He saved us in order that the blessing which he gave to Ebraam might come to the Side people through Keriso Yesu, so that by big mind(faith) we will receive God Spirit which God said without.lying talk(promised)
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The law and the without.lying talk(promise)
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
My friends, I will take an everyday doing. If two people answer what make one mind(agree), no one can break it or add it. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
God said his without.lying talks(promises) to Ebraam and to his descendant. The Buk(scripture) does not say, \u8220?to descendants,\u8221? its meaning many people, but \u8220?to descendant,\u8221? its meaning one man who is Keriso. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
