Do not rebuke an old man, but say with respectful way to him as if he were your.s father. Treat the young men as your.s own friends/brothers, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
the old women as mothers might be, and the young women as sisters might be, with all good.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
Show respect for them widows who are alone. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
But if a widow has children or grandchildren, they should do first as approving truth people(believers)'s work in their own family, and in this way will repay their parents and grandparents, because in this way pleases God. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
A widow who is all alone, with no one to take care of her, has placed hope to God and continues to talk with God and ask him for her to help night and day. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
But a widow who gives herself to body pleasure has already died, even though she lives. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
Give them these instructions, so that no one will find fault with them. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
But if any people do not take care of their close friends(relatives), especially the members of their own real family, they have denied the big mind(faith) and his behaviour is below those of people who don't truly approve(believe) Yesu.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
Do not add any widow to the name of widows unless she is over sixty years of age, and she must have been married only once {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
and people said she is doing good things: a woman who brought up her children well, received strangers well in her home, did humble works for other approving truth people, helped people in trouble, and gave herself to doing good.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
But do not put young widows' name on the paper; because when their desires make them want to marry, they turn away from Keriso. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
So they will become guilty of breaker their earlier without.lying talk(promise) to him. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
They also learn to waste their time in going around from house to house; but even very bad, they learn in gossip people, and interfering to other people's things, and talking about things they should not. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
So then, I am thinking that the young widows get married again, for bearing children, and will take care of their homes, so as to give enemies no chance of speaking evil talk of us. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
Some widows have turned away and followed S\u225?if\u232?r. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
But if any believing woman has widows in her family, she must take care of them and not put the burden on the Yesu's family(church), so that Yesu's family(church) may take care of those widows who are all alone.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Church head people
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
The Yesu's family(church) head people who do their good work as leading men should be received pay well, especially those who work hard at preaching and teaching. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
The Buk(scripture) says, \u8220?Do not tie mouth of an cow when it is working for corn\u8221? and also \u8220?Workers should be given their pay.\u8221? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
Do not listen to an accusation against an head man, unless two or three watching men bring it. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
If a head man does sin, rebuke publicly so that the other people may be afraid.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
I tell you.s in thier presence of God and of Keriso Yesu and of the without.dust(holy) men carrying heavenly message(angels):You.s must carefully follow the words I am telling you.s. When you.s follow them.p you.s must show one behaviour to all people, you.s must not show different behaviour to your.s friends and other men. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
Be in no hurry to lay hands on people to dedicate them to the Lord's work. Don't take part in the sins of other people, keep yourself without.dust(holy).
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
Do not drink water only, but take a little alcohol as a medicine since you.s are sick so often.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
The sins of some people are obvious to see, and their sins go ahead to judgment; but the sins of other people are seen only later. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
In the same way good deeds are obviously seen, and even those that are not so obvious cannot be hidden.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 6
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
Those who are believing without.payment working men(servants) must think well their owners with all respect, so that no one will say bad talk to the name of God and to our teaching. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
Believing without.payment working men(servants) belonging to owner who are truly approving man(believer) must not despise them, for they are approving truth people too. But they should serve them well, because those who make happy in their work are approving truth people who is with their love.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 False teaching and true riches
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 You.s must teach and preach these things. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
Whoever teaches a different talk and does not suit to the true talk of our Lord Yesu Keriso and with the teaching of our godly life(religion) {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
they are boasting people and don't know about anything. They have an unhealthy desire to argue and quarrel about talks, and this thing brings on jealousy, disputes, saying bad talks(insults), suspicions, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
and constant arguments come from those people whose good minds do not work and to whom are not true. They think that religion is a way to become rich.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
Religion makes us very rich, if we are satisfied with these things what we have. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
What did we bring into the world? Nothing! What can we take out of the world? Nothing! {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
So, if we have food and clothes, that should be enough for us. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
But those who want to get rich fall into temptation and are caught in the trap of many foolish and harmful desires, which pull them down to ruin and destruction. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
For the love of money is a root of all evil. Some people have been so eager to have, became far from the big mind(faith) and broke to pieces their hearts in many unhappy things.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fol's teaching talk to Timoti
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
But you.s, a man of God, avoid all these things. Fight for straightness, godliness, big mind(faith), love, endurance, and gentleness. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
Run your.s best in the race of big mind(faith), and take hold of the eternal life; because for this life that God called you.s when you.s firmly said your.s big mind(faith) before many watching men. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
In the sight of God, who gives life to all things, and in the sight of Keriso Yesu, who firmly said his big mind(faith) before Fontius Failet, I command you.s strongly {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
to obey your.s command and keep them faithfully until that day when our Lord Yesu Keriso appears. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
His appearing is at the straight time of God. God is the blessed and only Ruler, the King of ruling men(kings) and the Lord of lords. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
He alone is immortal; he lives in the light that no one can reach close. No one has seen him; no one can see him. Only to him be honor and eternal power! Amen.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
Command those who are rich in the world not to be proud, but put their hope, not in such thing as riches, but in God, who widely gives us everything for our enjoyment. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
Command them to do good, to be rich in good works, be wide men and ready to help other people. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
In this way they will store up for themselves a treasure which will be a solid foundation for the future. And then they will be able to receive the life which is true life.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
Timoti, guard what I gave them to your.s hand. Avoid the without.meaning and foolish arguments of what some people wrongly call \u8220?Knowledge.\u8221? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
Some have said to possess it, but those meaning they have lost the way of big mind(faith).
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 God's grace be with you.p all.
\page
\par\pard\plain \s0\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 2TI - - Nama Back Translation
\par\pard\plain \s93\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb40\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs46 Fol's second letter to Timoti
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 1
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
I am Fol, a man with Yesu's authority(apostle) of Keriso Yesu by God's will, sent to proclaim the did without.lying talk(promise) life which is in Keriso Yesu,
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
To Timoti, my heartful son:
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 May the Father God and Keriso Yesu our Lord give you.s grace, mercy, and peace.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Thanksgiving and Encouragement
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
I give thanks to God, whom I serve truly, as my ancestors did. I thank him as I remember you.s always in my talking with God night and day. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
I remember your.s tears, and I want to see you.s very much, so that I may be filled with joy. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
I remember your.s big mind(faith), this kind of big mind(faith) that your.s grandmother Lois and your.s mother Yunias also had. I am thinking that you.s have it also. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
For this reason I remind you.s to keep alive the gift which God gave you.s when I laid my hands on you.s. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
For this Spirit God gave us does not make us to be scared, but his Spirit fills us with power, love, and self-control.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
Do not be ashamed of preaching talk of our Lord; neither be ashamed of me, because I became a darkness house man(prisoner) for Keriso's sake. Instead, take your.s working place in suffering for the good talk, which God gave the power for it. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
He saved us and called us to be his own people, not because of what we have done, but because of his own will and grace. He gave us this grace by means of Keriso Yesu before the beginning, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
but now it has been revealed to us through the appearing of our Savior Keriso Yesu. He has stopped the power of death and through the good talk has revealed without.death life.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
God has appointed me as a man with Yesu's authority(apostle) and teaching man to proclaim the good talk, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
so for this reason that I am in suffering these things. But I am still full of strong mind, because I know whom I have trusted, and I know well that he is able to guard until that day what he has entrusted to me until Yesu's return.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
Hold firmly to the true talks that I taught you.s, as I show for you.s to follow, and remain strong in the big mind(faith) and love in Keriso Yesu. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
Through the power of the God Spirit, who lives in us, keep this good things which I have given to you.s.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
You.s know that every people in the province of Eisia, with Fagelus and Emogenes, has deserted me. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
May the Lord show mercy to the family of Onesiforus, because he helped me in the problem many times. He was not ashamed that I am in darkness house, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
but as soon as he arrived in Rom, he started looking for me until he found me. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
May the Lord gave him his mercy on that day! And you.s know very well how much he did for me in Efesos.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 2
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 A good soldier of Keriso Yesu
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
My son, be strong in the grace which is in Keriso Yesu. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
Take the teaching talk that you.s heard me in preaching in the presence of many watching men, and entrust them to faithful people, who will also be able to teach other people.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
Take your.s place in suffering, as a good soldier of Keriso Yesu. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
Whoever is a soldier, he does not do mixed work. Instead, in order to make happy his big man who called him to work of soldier. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
Anyone who are in a race cannot receive the prize unless he follows rules. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
The hardworking farmer should eat first when it's produce is ripe. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
Keep think about what I am saying, because the Lord will give you.s bright mind(understanding) in all things.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
Remember Yesu Keriso, who was raised from death, and who was a descendant of Deifid, as it is my good talk which I preach. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
Because I preach the good talk, I am in suffering and they tied me with steal rope(chain) like as I might be a stealing man. But the talk of God is not tied. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
So then I endure in everything for the sake of God's chosen people, so that they may also receive the salvation which comes through Keriso Yesu and brings eternal big light(glory).
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
This talk is true:
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 \u8220?If we have died with him,
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 we will also live with him.
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
If we continue to endure,
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 we will also rule with him.
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 If we deny him,
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 he will also deny us.
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
If we are not faithful,
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 he keeps standing faithful,
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 because he cannot deceive himself.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 An approved worker
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
Remind your.s people of this, and give them a strict warning talk in God's presence do not fight about talks. It does not good, but destroys the people who listen. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
Do your.s best to give yourself to God as one approved, as a worker who is not ashamed and who correctly handles the talk of truth. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
Keep away from dirty talk, which things will flood and become far away from God. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
Their teaching will spread like cancer. There are two women, Emaneus and Filetus. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
They.d have left the way of truth and are destroying the big mind(faith) of some approving truth people by talk our rising has already happened. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
But the solid foundation which God has laid cannot be shaken and God wrote talk on this that: \u8220?The Lord knows those who are his,\u8221? and \u8220?Those who say that they are Lord's must turn away from wrongdoing.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
In a large house there are many dishes and bowls of all kinds: they make some with silver and gold for good use, other with wood and clay for everyday use. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
Those who wash themselves from all evil things, will be good using, because they have given and are good to their Lord, and they are ready to do every good work.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
Take away the evil desires of young people, and put a mind for straight things, big mind(faith), love and peace, together with those who are with a good heart call out to the Lord for help. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
But keep away from without.meaning and stupid arguments, because you.s know they produce quarrels. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
As the Lord's without.payment worker, you.s must not quarrel. You must be without.greed(kind) toward all the people, and be a good and patient teaching man. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
Teach gently those who oppose the truth, in order that God will give them the chance to turn away from sins and know the truth. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
And then they will come to their minds and save from the trap of the S\u225?if\u232?r, who had caught them and made them do his will.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 3
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Doing godlessness in the last days
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
Remember that there will be hard times in the last days. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
People will be selfish, greedy, boastful, and proud, insulted, disobedient to their parents, without thank talk, and with.dirty(unholy), {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
without love, not to forget bad things(unforgiving), gossips, without self-control, and fierce; they will hate the good; {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
betraying(lit. "making teeth"), doing without thinking, and very proud, love in body desire strongly but not love God; {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
will be like a religious people, but reject its real power. Keep away from them.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
Some people go into people's houses and look slow to weak women whom their sins step on(load) and all kind of evil desires lead, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
these women who are always trying to learn new things, but they are never able to understand the truth. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
As Janes and Jambres were opposing men to Moses, also these people are opposed to the true talk. Their.d minds do not work and who are failures in the big mind(faith). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
But they.d will not move far in knowledge, because every people will see how foolish they.d are. Just as what happened to them Janes and Jambres.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Last teachings
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
But you.s have carried my teaching, my conduct, and my way in life; you.s have observed my big mind(faith), my patience, my love, my self-control, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
my many persecutions, and my sufferings. You.s know all those happened to me in Antiok, Ikonium, and Listra, the very big sufferings I carried! But the Lord saved me from them all. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
Everyone who wants to live a godly life in Keriso Yesu will be in persecution; {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
and evil persons and sorcerers will become bad to very bad. They deceive other people and will be deceived themselves. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
But as for you.s, continue in the true talks that I taught you.s and firmly truly approve(believe). You.s know who your.s teaching men were, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
and you.s remember that since you.s were a child, you.s have known the Without.dust Scriptures, which are able to give you.s the wisdom that leads to salvation through big mind(faith) in Keriso Yesu. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
All Scripture is inspired by God and is useful for teaching the true talk, taking away bad things, correcting sins, and teaching for straight living, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
so that this man who works for God may be well prepared and trained to do every kind of good work.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 4{\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
In the presence of God and of Keriso Yesu, who will judge the living people and the dead people, and because he is coming to rule as King, I strictly urge you.s: {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
Preach the talk of God. Be prepared, whether the time is favorable or not. Patiently correct, rebuke, and encourage your people with good teaching. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
The time is coming when people will not listen to straight talk, but they will follow their own desires and will pick them for themselves many teaching men who will tell them what they want to hear. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
They will turn away from listening to the true talk and give their ears to legends. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
But you.s must control of yourself through all things, endure in trouble, do the work as a preacher of the good talk, and do your.s work as a without.payment working man(servant) of God.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
As for me, the day has come for me to be offered. The day is here for me to leave this life. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
I have fought the good fight. I have finished my w\u233?rse. I have kept the big mind(faith). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
And now there is waiting for me the reward of straightness, which the Lord, the straight Judging man, will give it to me on that day and not only to me, but to all people who have waited for his appearing.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Final talks
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
Do your.s best to come to me quickly. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
Demas has left me, because he loved the things of this world, in this reason he has gone to Tesalonika. Kresens went to Galasia, and Taitus to Dalmasia. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
Only Luke is here with me. Get Mak and bring him with you.s, because he can help me in the work. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
I sent Tukikus to Efesos. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
When you.s come, bring my cloth which I left at the house of Karfus in the town of Troas, the books also, especially the ones made of animal skin.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
Aleksand\u232? the working man with steal spoiled me by many ways. The Lord will give his reward to him according to what he has done. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
Be on your.s guard against him yourself, because he was so much opposed to our talk.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
No one stood close to me on the first time I defended myself. Every people left me. I talked with God that God will forget(forgive) their faults! {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
But the Lord stayed with me and gave me strength, so that I was able to be preacher of talk for all the Side people to hear. And he saved me from death. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
And the Lord will rescue me from all evil and take me into his heavenly kingdom. Only to him be the big light(glory) forever and ever! Amen.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Final greeting talk
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
I send greeting talk to Frisila and Akwila and to the family of Onesiforus. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
Erastus stayed in Korint city, and I left Trofimus in Miletus town, because he was sick. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
Do your.s best to come first & later(before) winter comes.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Yubulus send greeting talk to you.s, also Fudens and Linus, and Klaudia and all other approving truth people do.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
The Lord will be in your.s spirit.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 God's grace will be with you.s all.
\page
\par\pard\plain \s0\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 TIT - - Nama Back Translation
\par\pard\plain \s93\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb40\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs46 Fol's letter to Taitus
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 1
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
This letter from Fol, a without.payment worker of God and a man who has the authority(apostle) of Yesu Keriso.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 He chose and sent me to help the big mind(faith) of God's chosen people and to teach them to know the truth which shows them how to live godly lives, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
which is based on the hope for eternal life. God, who does not lie, said without lying talk(promised) before in creation. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
And at his chosen time he put it clearly in his talk. He put this to me, and I preached it as God our Savior had said.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
I am writing the letter to you.s, Taitus, my true son in the big mind(faith) which we share.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Grace and peace will be from God the Father and Keriso Yesu our Savior.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Taitus works there in Krete
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
I left you.s in Krete, so that you.s could prepare well what they keep on leaving well to do and and appoint Yesu's family(church) head people in every town. Remember my instructions: {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
an head man must be without fault. He must have one wife, his children must be approving truth people and have good life and obedient. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
A Yesu's family(church) head man is watching man to God's work, he should be without fault. He must not work for himself or quickly angry man, or who drink alcohol, or violent, or greedy for money. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
But he must be friend to visitors, love what is good, self-controlled, straight, without.dust(holy), and disciplined. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
He must hold firmly to the truly approving talk which we told you.s. In this way he can encourage other people in true teaching and also to show their wrong [talk] of those who are opposed men.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
Because there are many, who was from the cutting skin people group, who are without.hearing and deceive other people with their without.meaning way. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
They must stop, because they are turning whole families away from the truth by their false teaching, and all for the shameful thing about making money. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
One of Krete\u700?s God's people who make know(prophets) said, \u8220?Krete people are always liars, wild animals, and lazy greedy.\u8221? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
This talk is true. Therefore you.s must rebuke them strongly, so that they may be in big mind(faith) continually {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
and don't hold on to Ju people's legends and to human commands of those who have rejected the true talk. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
To them who are without.dirty(pure), everythings are without,dirty(pure); but to those who are spoiled and do not truly approve(believe), nothing is good, for their minds and consciences are spoiled. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
They told that they know God, but they keep on refusing it in their actions. They are hateful and without.listening, not fit to do anything good.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 2
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Doing good for the good talk
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
But you.s must teach how meaning is the sound of the talk. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
Teach the old men to be controlled, be strong mind(serious), and self-controlled; to be good in their big mind(faith), in love, and in endurance. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
In the same way teach the old women to live a without.dust(holy) life, not to be gossipping people about people or not to be people eating alcohol so much. They must teach what is good. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
Then they should teach the young women to love their husbands and children, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
to be self-controlled and without.dust(holy), and to be good housewives who are obeying to their husbands, so that God's talk is not be without.respectfully.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
In the same way, encourage the young men to be self-controlled men. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
And you.s yourself must be an good showing(example) by your every actions. And in your.s teaching be truly and with strong mind. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
Speak straight talks that they cannot criticize, so that your.s fighting men(enemies) may be put to shame and have nothing bad to say about us.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
Without.payment working men(slaves) should be to obeying people to their owners and pleasing men in all things. They must not talk back to their owners {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
or not steal. But they must show that they are good and faithful. And because of their good behavior, everyone will show great respect for the teaching about God our Savior.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
God has showed his grace to save all people. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
It teaches us to stop ungodly life and worldly desires, and to live self-controlled, straight and godly lives in the present days, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
while we wait for the blessed day who hope for, when the big light(glory) of our big God and Savior, Yesu Keriso will appear. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
He has given himself for us to save us from all sins and made us without.dust(holy) people who are his chosen people and eager to do good.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
Teach these things and do with your.s full authority to encourage and to make straight your.s people. Let none of them look down on you.s.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 3
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Do what is good
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
Make know your.s people they must submit to govenment ruling people and to the people with authority. They must be followed and be ready to do all kind of good work. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
They must not speak evil, and to be peaceful and friendly, and always to be a gentle toward every people. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
In that day we ourselves were without.meaning, without.hearing and wrong. We were without.payment working men(servants) to bodily desires and pleasurs of all kinds. We gave our lives to evil and jealousy, other peoples hated us and we also hated them. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
But when God our Savior showed his kindness and love for the people, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
he saved us, not because of our doing straight thing, but because he himself has mercy. He saved us through the God Spirit, who gives us new birth and new life by washing. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
God poured out his Spirit onto us widely through Yesu Keriso our Savior. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
so that by his grace he might put us straight with God and give us hope for eternal life which is for our place. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
This talk is a true. I want you.s to teach to these things, so that those who truly approve(believe) God may decide to do good thing. These which are good teaching and beneficial for every people. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
But avoid without.mind arguments, the list of long names of ancestors, quarrels, and fights about the law. These are without.meaning and without.grain. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
Warn two times to him who causes division, and after this, do not interact again with them. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
You know that these people are corrupted man, and their sins prove that they are not good.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
When I send Atemas or Tukikus to you.s, do good to come to me in Nikofolis town, because I have decided to stay in the winter there. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
Do your.s good to help Njenas the law person(laywer) and Afolos to get started on their travels and see that they.d have enough things for themselves.d. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
Our people must learn to spend their time doing good, in order to provide for real needs, and they should not live without.meaning.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
All who are here with me greet you.s. Greet to our friends in the big mind(faith).
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 God's grace will be with you.p all.
\page
\par\pard\plain \s0\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 PHM - - Nama Back Translation
\par\pard\plain \s93\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb40\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs46 Fol's letter to Filemon
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 1
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
This letter is from me, Fol. I am in the darkness house because I serve Keriso Yesu. Our friend Timoti is here with me.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 I am writing to you, Filemon our lovely friend and fellow worker, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
and to him Afia our sister, and Akifus our soldier, and also to the Yesu's family(church) people who gather in your.s house:
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
Grace and peace will be to you.s from our Father God and the Lord Yesu Keriso.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Fol's thanksgiving and talking with God
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
I always give thanks to my God when I remember you.s in my talking with God, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
