But Yesu still remains burning sacrifice man forever, and his burning sacrifice way will never end. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
Therefore he is able, now and always, to save every people who come to God through him. He lives forever to be middleman for them.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
Yesu is the the High burning sacrifice man who we need because he is without.dust(holy) and blameless, no sin. He has now live different from sinners and raised above the heavens. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
He is not like other leading burning sacrifice men. He does not need to offer sacrifices every day for his own sins first and then for the sins of the other people. He offered one sacrifice, once and for all, when he offered sacrifice himself. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
The law of Moses appoints men who are with.flaw(unperfect) to be leading burning sacrifice men. But God made without.lying talk(promise) strongly, which came later than the law, appoints the Son, who has become without.flaw(perfect) forever.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 8
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Keriso is our High burning sacrifice man
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
This is the foundation of the talk point: We have a High burning sacrifice man, who sits down in the table of high honor in there heaven at God's right hand. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
He serves as leading burning sacrifice man in the Most Without.dust Place, in the real canves house which Lord built, not by human hands.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
Every leading burning sacrifice man is appointed to offer gifts and sacrifices, and so our High burning sacrifice man, Yesu must also make an offerings. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
If Yesu were on earth, he would not be burning sacrifice man, because there are burning sacrifice men who offer the gifts because of the laws which the Ju people must follow. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
They work in worshipping place which is a copy, a shadow of its to real thing in heaven. This is the same as it was with Moses. When Moses was getting ready to build the worshipping canvas house, God told him: \u8220?Be sure so that you.s should make everything according to that I have shown you.s on the mountain.\u8221? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
But in fact the work God gave Yesu to do surpasses the work he gave the other burning sacrifice men to do, just as the new covenant surpasses the old covenant. Yesu is a middleman(mediator) of new covenant and he helped the new covenant to be strong. And the good things of heaven that the new covenant says it will give us surpasses the good things the old covenant said it would give us.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
If the first covenant had been faultless, there would have been no need for a second covenant to replace its place. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
But God himself saw fault with his people, and said,
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 \u8220?The Lord says, 'The days are coming,
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 when I will make a new covenant with the people of Israil and with the people of Juda.
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
This covenant will not be like the covenant that I made with their ancestors
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 when I took them by the hand and led them out of Ijif.
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 They didn't hold faithfully to my covenant
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 so I turned my back on them.
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
But this is new covenant I will make with the people of Israil
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 in that days, says the Lord:
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 I will put my laws in their minds
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 and write them on their hearts.
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 I will be their God,
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 and they will be my people.
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
And they will not teach their friends,
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 they will not teach their family, saying,
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 \u8216?You.p should know the Lord.\u8217?
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Because every people from small to big will know about me.
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
I will forget their sins
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 and I will never remember their sins.\u8221?
\par\pard\plain \s61\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
When God speaks of a new covenant, God has made the first covenant old, and anything which is becoming old like that will not.far disappear.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 9
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Old rules about worship
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
There are rules for worship in the first covenant had rules and a also special place for worship here on earth. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
There were two rooms in this canvas house. In first room there were the lampstand, and the table, and cooked without.dust(holy) bread put on the table. This was called the without.dust(holy) place. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
And there were hanging cloth(curtain), and behind the curtain was the second room called the Most Without.dust Place. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
In that room it were the gold-made incence burning table(altar) and wooden boks called covenat boks, which was covered with gold on all side, inside covenant ark were gold-made dish which were some Manna, Aron's staff that sprouted leaves, and the two stone tablets for covenant where 10 commandments were written on them. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
The big light(glorious) two men carrying heavenly message(angels) were above the boks's cover. Their wings spread over the boks's cover, the place of atonement. But we cannot explain all of this things now.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
When everything prepared like this, burning sacrifice men always go into the first room to start their works. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
But only the leading burning sacrifice man goes into the Most Without.dust Place, and he does so only once a year. He always takes with blood which he offers to God on behalf of himself and for the sins which other people have committed without knowing. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
By these rules the God Spirit showed that the Most Without.dust Place has not been opened for people this first room and the entire doing work which represents was still working. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
This is a showing thing pointing to the present time as gifts and sacrifices which are offered were not able to cleanse thinking of worshipper. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
Those gifts and sacrifices were only about food and water for special washing. These rules were only for body to be followed until that time God's new way.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 The blood of Keriso
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
So Keriso has now become the leading burning sacrifice man over all this good things which have come, he has entered that big and without.flaw worship place there in heaven, not made by human hands and not part of this created world. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
Once for all time he took blood to that Most Without.dust Place, but the blood of goats and cows, he took his own blood, and with it he secured our salvation forever. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
Under the old doing, the blood of goats and adult cows and the ashes of a young cows could clean people's bodies from Yesu's family(church) ceremony(ritual) impurity. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
Just think how much more the blood of Keriso will become good our hearts from deeds which lead to death so that we can worship the living God. By the power of the eternal God Spirit, Keriso offered himslef to God as a without.flaw sacrifice for our sins.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
So Yesu is the one who will settle new covenant between God and people, so that all who are invited can receive the eternal things for what God did without.lying talk(promise) them because Keriso died to make free them from sins' payment which they did under the first covenant.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
A man decided for later things that, "When I died, who will take my things?" So if one of his son want to get his father's things, he must first know his father died or not. After this he will take his father's things. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
If the man has indeed died, then the final talk becomes meaningful, but if the man is still alive, the final talk is meaningful. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
In the same God's first agreement with his people will be meaning with the blood of animal. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
When Moses told to the people all the commandments of God, he took the blood of young cows and goats, together with water, red wool and tree stick, sprinkled the book and all the people. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
He said, \u8220?This blood confirms the covenant which God had made with you.\u8221? {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
In the same way, he also sprinkled the blood on the worship canvas house(tabernacle) and over all working things. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
In fact, by the law of Moses, almost everything was made good by sprinkling with blood, if there in no blood, there is no forgiveness of sins.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
The tabernacle and its things can make clean with animal blood. Those were copies of what is in heaven. But animal blood can not clean the true things in Heaven. Only an offering which surpasses animal blood will make clean those things. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
Keriso did not enter a man-made Without.dust(Holy) Place which was a copy of the real one. He entered into heaven itself, now in order that he stands for us in the presence of God. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
The earthly leading burning sacrifice man enters the Most Without.dust Place year after year to offer the blood of animal. But when Keriso went into heaven to offer himself to God, he did not do that repeatedly. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
To do that, he would need to die repeatedly, many times since the creation of the world. No! It is not that way. Now he came once for that time at the end to destroy the power of sin forever by his sacrificial death for us. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
Everyone must die once and after that they will stand in judgement. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
In the same way Keriso died once as a sacrifice to take away the sins of many people. He will appear again, not for sin, but to bring salvation to those who are waiting for him.
\par\pard\plain \s52\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs42 10
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 Keriso\u700?s Sacrifice Once for All
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 1\~}
The old system in the law of Moses was only a shodow of other things to come, not the reality of the good things what Keriso did for us. The sacrifices under the old system were repeated again and again, year after year, but these things were never able to make without.flaw for those who came to worship. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 2\~}
If the old rules could make them without.flaw, the burning sacrifice would have finished, for the worshippers would have been without.dust(holy) once for all time, and their feelings of guilty would have disappeared. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 3\~}
But it's not like that, those yearly burning sacrifice things reminded them of their sins. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 4\~}
It is not possible for the blood of cows and goats to take away sins.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 5\~}
In this reason when Keriso came into the world, he said to God:
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 \u8220?You.s did not want animal sacrifices and giving things(offerings),
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 but you.s have given me body to offer.
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 6\~}
You.s were not pleased with animals burned on the sacrificing table(latar) or with other offering for sin.
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 7\~}
Then I said, \u8216?Look, I have come to do your.s will, O God
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 just as it is written about me there in the God's talk.
\par\pard\plain \s61\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 8\~}
First he said, "You.s don't want offering and the sacrifice of the animals. Any kind of sacrifice like that does not make you happy." He said this even though all these sacrifices are offered according to the law. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 9\~}
Then he said, \u8220?Here I am, I have come to do your.p will.\u8221? He cancels the first covenant in order to put the second into effect. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 10\~}
And by his will, he have made us without.dust(holy) through the sacrifice of the body of Yesu Keriso once for all.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
Every day, the priests do their work to serve God. They offer the same sacrifices to God again and again. But those sacrifices can never take away people's sins. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
But Keriso gave himself as a sacrifice for sin that is good forever, now he is sitting God's right side. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
And he will stay there until his enemies are put under his power. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
By his only one sacrifice he has forever made those people without.flaw from sin those who he made holy.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
The God Spirit also says this. For he says:
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
\u8220?When time reaches,
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 I will make an covenat with them.
\par\pard\plain \s78\ql\fi-540\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 I will write my laws there on their minds and hearts.
\par\pard\plain \s77\ql\fi-720\lin1080\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
Then I will forget about their sins and will not remember their evil doings."
\par\pard\plain \s61\ql\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
And when he forgets sins, there is no more to offer sacrifice.
\par\pard\plain \s105\qc\fi0\lin0\rin0\sb160\sa80\b\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 A Call to persevere
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
My friends, the blood of Yesu gives us confidence to enter the Most Without.dust Place, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
by a new way which leads us to life, and this way take us through the hanging wide cloth(curtain), which is his body. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
We have a big leading burning sacrifice man who rules over God's house, {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
So we should come near to God and we should not be afraid. But we must be honest and we must continue to trust him. He has made us clean from the dirt of our sins. Our thoughts no longer give us trouble about our sins. We have become clean. It is like he has washed our bodies with clean water. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
We must hold tightly to the hope which we truly approve(believe), because we can trust God who keep his without.lying talk(promise). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
Let us think other how to encourage other people to show love and good deeds. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
And let us no neglect our meeting together, as some people do, but encourage one another, as now the day of his coming back is becoming close.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 26\~}
If we keep on sinning after we have received the knowledge of the truth, no sacrifice for washing this sins is left. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 27\~}
There is only a fearful expectation of judgment and of raging fire which will consume the enemies of God. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 28\~}
Anyone who rejected the law of Moses died without mercy when two or three watching men testify. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 29\~}
Think how much terrible the punishment will be for those who turned against the Son of God and have treated the blood of the covenant, which made us holy, as if it were meaning and dirty, such people have insulted and put the shame the God Spirit who brings God's mercy to his people. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 30\~}
We know this man who said, \u8220?I will give back payment(take revenge), I will repay those who do this,\u8221? and he also said, "The Lord will judge his people." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 31\~}
This is a terrible thing to fall into the hands of the living God.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 32\~}
Don't forgot how you ware in the past when you.p received God's light. Remember how you.p keep on staying in big mind(faith) even though it was terrble suffering. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 33\~}
Sometimes you.p were publicly exposed in insulting and death, and at other times you.p helped others who were suffering the same things. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 34\~}
