\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 11\~}
The leading burning sacrifice man carries the blood of animals into the Most Without.dust Place where he offers this blood for sins, but the bodies of animals are burned outside the made village(camp). {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 12\~}
Yesu also suffered outside the city to make his people without.dust(holy) with his own blood. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 13\~}
So let us go to Yesu outside the camp and hold strong like he was when they insulted us. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 14\~}
Here on this world, we do not have a city which last forever, but we keep on looking for the city which is to come for us later.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 15\~}
Therefore Let us always offer praise to God as our sacrifice through Jesus, which is the offering presented by lips that confess he is Lord. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 16\~}
But do not forget to do good anf help one another, because these are the sacrifice which please God.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 17\~}
Respect your leaders and obey them. They watch over your lives on God's behalf. God will check to see if they have done their work well. So respect them, they will be happy in the God's work. Do not say bad things against them, because that will never help you.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 18\~}
Talk with God(pray) for us, we know that our minde is in light and desire to live honorably in every way. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 19\~}
I need your.p talking with God right now so that I can come back to you.p quickly.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 20\~}
The God of peace raised our Lord Yesu from death, the big watching man of the sheep. God made the eternal covenant with his people with Jesu's blood. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 21\~}
This God will give you.p all good things for doing his will. And God will work in us what is pleasing to him, through Yesu Keriso, to whom be big light(glory) forever. Amen.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 22\~}
My friends, I have written only a short letter to encourage you.p, and I beg you.p to pay close attention to hear what I have said.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 23\~}
I want you.p to know that they has released our friend Timoti from darkness house. If he arrives quickly, I will come with him to see you.p.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 24\~}
Kiss/Greet all your.p leading men and all the Lord\u700?s people. Who are from Italia send [their] greeting talk to you.p.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs28 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs28 25\~}
May God's grace be with you.p all.
